(3, 'April 2007', 'april2007', '', '<h2 name="news01" class="TopItem"> Long awaited reissue of Taro Gomi''s lost masterpiece</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">April 2007</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=29&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/april2007/tg_asecretinstrument_b.jpg" alt="A Secret Instrument" width="199" height="241" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a></td>\r\n                <td valign="top">\r\n                  <p>Taro Gomi''s second book, first published in 1975, is republished to celebrate Kaisei-sha''s 70th anniversary. </p>\r\n                  <p><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=29&Itemid=37">view details page...</a></p>\r\n                </td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h2 name="news02">Broadcast of Guardian of the Sacred Spirit animated series</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">April 2007</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=479&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/april2007/gothesacredspirit_b.jpg" alt="Guardian of the Sacred Spirit" width="199" height="279" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a></td>\r\n                <td valign="top">\r\n                  <p>The Japanese public broadcaster NHK has begun transmission of an animated version of Guardian of the Sacred Spirit. </p>\r\n                  <p>The fantasy world of Nahoko Uehashi''s story has been brought to the screen by Production I.G., who are active around the world, producing programmes such as ''Innocence'', and the animation director Kenji Kamiyama, who has directed key Japanese works such as ''Ghost in the Shell''.</p>\r\n                </td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <h2 name="news03">Review from Kirkus Reviews</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">April 2007</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=206&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/april2007/nk_singingshijimiclam_b.jpg" alt="Singing Shijimi Clam" width="199" height="250" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a></td>\r\n                <td valign="top">\r\n                  <p>&lsquo;Told and illustrated with equal spareness, this tender Japanese tale will please young readers who find the fate of the oysters in &ldquo;The Walrus and the Carpenter: discomfiting. </p>\r\n                  <p>Having left her &ldquo;mean and feisty&rdquo; years behind, an old witch not only can&rsquo;t bring herself to pour the bagful of small, gently snoring clams she&rsquo;s brought home into her boiling miso soup, but when they wake and begin to cry, she offers to take them back to the shore. </p>\r\n                  <p>Buying train tickets for so many, however, seems impossible &minus; until the clams begin to sing &ldquo;with pretty little voices, like tiny popping bubbles,&rdquo; charming enough contributions from passersby to finance the trip. </p>\r\n                  <p>By the end, not only have the faces that Kojima puts on the clam shells in her tiny, delicate line drawings gone from dismay to delight, but the habitual frowns on the witch and her bad-tempered cat have likewise changed to smiles. </p>\r\n                  <p>All live happily ever after on the beach, &ldquo;surrounded by the pretty voices of the clams, the gentle sound of the waves, and the warmth of the sun.&rdquo; </p>\r\n                  <p>A feel-good episode if ever there was one.</p>\r\n                </td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n            </table>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2007-04-01 13:45:54', 62, '', '2008-11-20 10:24:06', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2008-09-29 13:45:54', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 30, '', '', 0, 139, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(5, 'November 2007', 'november2007', '', '<h2 name="news01" class="TopItem"> The Latest Publication from Lindgren Award-Winner, Ryoji Arai</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">November 2007</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=509&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007knock-knockdoor_b.jpg" alt="The Knock-Knock Door" width="199" height="250" border="0" /></a></td>\r\n                <td valign="top">\r\n                  <p>After a long wait, <a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=creator&cid=ryoji_arai&Itemid=11">Ryoji Arai</a>, joint winner with Phillip Pullman of the 2005 Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award, has released his new illustrated book, &lsquo;<a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=509&Itemid=37">Knock Knock Door</a>&rsquo;. </p>\r\n                  <p>This time round, Arai has set his illustrations alongside the lyrics of Japanese pop band &lsquo;Kukikodan&rsquo;, with whom he has collaborated before with on cover design, promotional videos and similar. </p>\r\n                  <p>One night, while fast asleep, people from dreamland come knocking on the door to take us on a night''s journey, which ends with the words &ldquo;goodnight everyone!&rdquo; The book comes with a special edition 2-track CD, containing the song Knock Knock Door. </p>\r\n                  <p>The &lsquo;Kukikodan x Ryoji Arai Talkshow&rsquo; held to celebrate the release of the book was a huge success, and an autograph session was also held.</p>\r\n                </td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle"> &quot;The Knock-Knock Door&quot;</span><br />\r\n                  by Yukari Yamazaki <br />\r\n                  illus. by Ryoji Arai <br />\r\n                  26 x 20 cm, 32 pages <br />\r\n                  Full-colour illustrations</td>\r\n                <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>\r\n              </tr>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td style="padding: 0 15px 0 0;"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007knockknock.jpg" alt="The Knock-Knock Door" width="250" height="153" border="0" class="KeyLine" style="margin: 1px;" /></td>\r\n                  <td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007knockknock2.jpg" alt="An autographe session" width="300" height="153" border="0" class="KeyLine" style="margin: 1px;" /></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h2 name="news02">&lsquo;The Old Fisherman Who Smelt of Water&rsquo; Wins the Shogakukan Cultural Prize in Publishing for Children''s Books</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">November 2007</p>\r\n            <p>Shogakukan Cultural Prize in Publishing for Children''s Books, sponsored by the Japanese publisher Shogakukan and awarded to the year''s outstanding literary contribution to children''s literature, was won by <a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=103&Itemid=37">&lsquo;The Old Fisherman Who Smelt of Water&rsquo;</a>. </p>\r\n            <p>With documentary style photographs, the charming book is about the only old man to continue fishing in the traditional style on Japan''s biggest lake, Lake Biwa. </p>\r\n            <p>The author is <a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=creator&cid=mitsuhiko_imamori&Itemid=11">Mitsuhiko Imamori</a>, who lives by Lake Biwako himself and photographs the small villages and mountains of the surrounding area. </p>\r\n            <p>He has a deep understanding of the traditional Japanese life-style, and can see the natural beauty in his surroundings.</p>\r\n            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="430">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=103&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/theoldfishermanwsow_b.jpg" alt="The Old Fisherman Who Smelt of Water" width="199" height="245" border="0" style="margin: 1px;" /></a> </td>\r\n                  <td class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=103&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007oldman_n.jpg" alt="The Old Fisherman Who Smelt of Water" width="320" height="245" border="0" style="margin: 1px;" /></a> </span></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td colspan="2" valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 15px 0;"><span class="NewsBookTitle">&quot;The Old Fisherman Who Smelt of Water&quot;</span><br />\r\n                    by Mitsuhiko Imamori <br />\r\n                    27 x 23 cm, 64 pages, Full-colour photographs</td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h2 name="news03">Two New Books in the Bird Nest Series</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">November 2007</p>\r\n            <p>Two fresh volumes by artist and bird nest expert <a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=creator&cid=mamoru_suzuki&Itemid=11">Mamoru Suzuki</a> are being published simultaneously. </p>\r\n            <p>Praised for providing an accurate, succinct description of bird nests, his book &lsquo;<a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=406&Itemid=37">My Bird Nest Picture Diary</a>&rsquo; won the 2006 Kodansha Award for Literature. The author is an energetic participant in a range of events, opening exhibitions over Japan and even in New York.</p>\r\n            <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="430">\r\n              <tbody>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 7px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=408&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007ms_birdneststories_n.jpg" alt="Bird Nest Stories" width="136" height="145" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a> </td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 7px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=409&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007ms_unusualbird_n.jpg" alt="Unusual Birds Nests" width="136" height="164" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a> </span></td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 7px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=407&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007allaboutbirdnests_n.jpg" alt="All About Bird Nests" width="136" height="128" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a></td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 0 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=406&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/112007mybirdnest_n.jpg" alt="My Bird Nest Picture Diary" width="136" height="165" border="0" class="KeyLine" /></a></td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 15px 0;"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">&quot;Bird Nest Stories&quot;</span><br />\r\n                    by Mamoru Suzuki <br />\r\n                    28 x 26 cm, 32 pages <br />\r\n                    Full-colour illustrations</td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 15px 0;"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle"> &quot;Unusual Birds Nests&quot;</span><br />\r\n                    by Mamoru Suzuki <br />\r\n                    27 x 23 cm, 40 pages <br />\r\n                    Full-colour illustrations</td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 15px 0;"><span class="NewsBookTitle">&quot;All About Bird Nests&quot;</span><br />\r\n                    by Mamoru Suzuki <br />\r\n                    25 x 27 cm, 32 pages <br />\r\n                    Full-colour illustrations</td>\r\n                  <td valign="top" class="NewsBookDescription" style="padding:0 15px 15px 0;"><span class="NewsBookTitle">&quot;My Bird Nest Picture Diary&quot;</span><br />\r\n                    by Mamoru Suzuki <br />\r\n                    29 x 25 cm, 36 pages <br />\r\n                    Full-colour illustrations</td>\r\n                </tr>\r\n                <tr valign="top"> </tr>\r\n                <tr valign="top"> </tr>\r\n              </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h2 name="news04">Paris Exhibition of Hideko Ise''s Original Drawings</h2>\r\n            <p class="Date">November 2007</p>\r\n            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n              <tr>\r\n                <td valign="top" style="padding:0 15px 5px 0;"><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=522&Itemid=37"><img src="images/news/november2007/1000winds1000cellos_b.jpg" alt="A Thousand Winds, A Thousand Cellos" width="199" height="144" border="0" /></a></td>\r\n                <td valign="top">\r\n                  <p><a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=creator&cid=hideko_ise&Itemid=11">Hideko Ise</a>, the popular Japanese illustrator with a distinctive soft touch, author of &lsquo;<a href="index.php?option=com_publications&view=title&tid=522&Itemid=37">A Thousand Winds, A Thousand Cellos</a>&rsquo;, had the original drawings from her book &lsquo;Sophie et le Relieur&rsquo; (Seuil Jeunesse, published in Japan by Rironsha) exhibited i