(18, 'May 2010', 'may-2010', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>Bologna Children’s Book Fair 2010</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2010</p>\r\n<p>Kaisei-Sha was again exhibiting at the Bologna Children’s Book Fair, held in Italy between 23rd and 26th March. The atmosphere at the fair was really buzzing, with publishers and illustrators from all over the world in attendance. We were delighted to welcome everyone who made it to our stall ? where a few books really captured the imagination of guests. Amongst the picture books, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/629.html" target="_self">''Little Book''</a> was a real standout, thanks to its interesting concept - the book is about being a book - and charming illustrations. Amongst the children’s books,<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/110.html" target="_self"> ''I’m an African Giraffe''</a> was the main head turner. This lovely book is packed with gentle humour, and tells the story of two pen pals who have yet to meet. Thank you to everyone who came to see us. We look forward to seeing old and new friends alike next year in Bologna.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/may2010/bologna.jpg" width="249" height="202" style="margin-right:10px; "></td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/629.html"><img src="images/news/may2010/331680-hon-chan.jpg" width="150" height="202" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n  <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/110.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/books/iamafricangiraffe_b.jpg" alt="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/110.html" width="150" height="215" border="0"></a></td>\r\n  \r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n  <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Little Book</span><br />\r\nby Kanayo Sugiyama<br />\r\n26 x 19 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">I''m an African Giraffe</span><br />\r\n by Megumi Iwasa<br />\r\n illus. by Jun Takabatake<br />\r\n\r\n22 x 16 cm, 102 pages<br />Black-and-white illustrations\r\n</span></td>\r\n  \r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/619.html">The Wolf King</a> wins the Japan Picture Book Award!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2010 </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are delighted to announce that <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/619.html" target="_self">''The Wolf King''</a>, a Kaisei-Sha publication, has won the prestigious 15th All-Japan Picture Book Award run by the Japan School Library Association. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/619.html" target="_self">''The Wolf King''</a> is the fourth book in a series following the adventures of a silly, shy little wolf - this time around, he accidentally manages to become King of a thousand wolves. The illustrations are strikingly unique - the double page spread of a thousand wolf subjects is particularly well composed. Congratulations to the author, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yuichi_kimura.html" target="_self">Yuichi Kimura</a> and the illustrator, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/seizo_tashima.html" target="_self">Seizo Tashima</a>!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/619.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/king_of_wolf.jpg" width="250" height="218" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><p><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wolf King</span><br />\r\nby Yuichi Kimura<br />\r\nillus. by Seizo Tashima<br />\r\n24 x 28 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></p></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/695.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/feast_of_wolf.jpg" width="155" height="136" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/696.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/friends_of_wolf.jpg" width="155" height="135" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/697.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/seacret_of_wolf.jpg" width="155" height="135" border="0" ></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wolf''s Feast</span><br />\r\n by Yuichi Kimura<br />\r\nillus. by Seizo Tashima\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n24×28 cm, 32 pages\r\n<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wolf''s Friend</span><br />\r\n by Yuichi Kimura<br />\r\nillus. by Seizo Tashima\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n24×28 cm, 32 pages\r\n<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wolf''s Secret</span><br />\r\n by Yuichi Kimura<br />\r\nillus. by Seizo Tashima\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n24×28 cm, 32 pages\r\n<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news01" id="news03"></a>A New Series by Bestselling Picture Book Author!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2010 </p>\r\n<p>The “Open up! Open up” series of baby picture books by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/hiroyuki_arai.html" target="_self">Hiroyuki Arai</a> - now the favourites of a whole generation of young children - is now to be joined by an exciting new series by the author/illustration: the Find it! Find it! picture books.\r\nIn <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/689.html" target="_self">''Where are You Hiding?''</a>, children are hidden in trees and behind rock, and the reader has to find them. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/688.html" target="_self">''Which Hand is It In?''</a> takes the game of hiding something in one or other hand and making the other player guess, and expresses it in book form. These are wonderful books to read to young children, as each page offers a new chance to Find it! Find it! together.\r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/689.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/where_are_you_hiding.jpg" alt="Where are you hiding?" width="220" height="152" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/688.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/which_hand.jpg" alt="Which Hand is It In?" width="220" height="153" border="0" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Where are You Hiding?</span><br />\r\n by Hiroyuki Arai<br />\r\n\r\n18 x 13 cm, 19 pages\r\n<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Which Hand is It In?</span><br />\r\nby Hiroyuki Arai<br />\r\n\r\n18 x 13 cm, 19 pages\r\n<br />\r\nFull-colour illustration\r\n</span>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news01" id="news04"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/691.html" target="_self">The Mole Bus</a>: Well on its Way to Great Sales!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2010 </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/691.html" target="_self">''The Mole Bus''</a> is a wonderful new picture book from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/masahiko_sato.html" target="_self">Masahiko Sato</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/masumi_uchino.html" target="_self">Masumi Uchino</a>, the team behind “Pythagora Switch”, a popular TV programme for children shown on national broadcaster NHK. The Mole Bus trundles along the Mole Bus route, in Underground Town, regular as clockwork. But then, all of a sudden, something shoots up from the ground….The cute-as-pie illustrations from Sato and Uchino fit in perfectly with the warmth-filled story - and its sales are certainly testament to its popularity with all children. With a reprint ordered just five days after the book’s first print, this is certainly one to watch!\r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/691.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2010/mole_bus.jpg" width="250" height="182" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Mole Bus</span><br />\r\n      by Masahiko Sato and Masumi Uchino <br />\r\n      19 x 26 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><img style="margin-top:10px; " src="images/news/may2010/mole_bus_2.jpg" alt="Mole bus" width="500" height="175"></p>\r\n<p class="Clear">\r\n</p>\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2010-05-27 05:05:32', 62, '', '2010-05-27 13:06:28', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-05-27 05:05:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 3, 0, 22, '', '', 0, 665, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(19, 'August 2010', 'august2010', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/702.html" target="_parent">Brand New Book from Taro Miura Attracts Global Attention</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2010</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_miura.html" target="_parent">Taro Miura</a> is internationally active as an illustrator, publishing books with Edizioni Corraini in Italy, Chronicle Books in the U.S., and Media Vaca in Spain. His latest work, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/702.html" target="_parent">The Tiny King</a>, tells the story of a tiny monarch who lives in an enormous castle, all alone, every day feasting on enormous banquets. Yet at night, in his gigantic bed, the Tiny King feels terribly lonely. But one day, his solitude is swept away and his life changed completely; his feasts no longer seem so big, nor his castle so empty. But what has brought about this change in the Tiny King’s life? The answer is revealed in this beautifully composed picture book, which combines collage, colour and bold graphical design.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/702.html" target="_parent"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_1_1.jpg" width="162" height="211" border="0"></a></td>\r\n<td style="vertical-align:bottom; padding-left:10px;"><a href="file:///Macintosh%20HD/Users/masayo/Desktop/&#20181;&#20107;/&#20565;&#25104;&#31038;/Feb2010/html/images/news/feb2010/2010_Catalogue.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_1_2.jpg" alt="catalogue" width="325" height="211" border="0"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td style="margin-top:5px; "><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tiny King</span><br />\r\n by Taro Miura<br />\r\n27 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td></td>\r\n  <td style="vertical-align:bottom; padding-bottom:5px;">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/700.html">Latest Instalment in the Hit “Shinoda!” Fantasy Series</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2010 </p>\r\n\r\n<p>They seem like a normal family. Dad is just a normal guy. But mum is…a fox. And each of their three children has a special power, too. This not-so-normal family stars in the Shinoda! Series by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yoko_tomiyasu.html">Yoko Tomiyasu</a>, and the latest instalment has now been published. This time around, the Shinoda family receive an invitation to come and stay in a hotel on a remote island in the south. What mysteries will await them there? Find out in the fifth book in this popular series.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/700.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_2_1.jpg" width="198" height="283" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Mermaid Island, Lost in Time</span><br />\r\n by Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nillus. by Kenya Ohba <br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 272 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td height="10px">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="25%">\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/614.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_2_2.jpg" width="110" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom" width="25%"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/country/title/466.html?country=13" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_2_3.jpg" width="110" height="159" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom" width="25%"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/464.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_2_4.jpg" width="110" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom" width="25%"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/467.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2010/article_2_5.jpg" width="110" height="162" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td height="10px">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Mermaid Island, Lost in Time</span><br />\r\n by Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nillus. by Kenya Ohba <br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 272 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">A Strange Night in the Enchanted Forest</span><br />\r\n by Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nillus. by Kenya Ohba <br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 254 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Secret Lake in the Looking Glass</span><br />\r\n by Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nillus. by Kenya Ohba <br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 238-366 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n   <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Mermaid Island, Lost in Time</span><br />\r\n by Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nillus. by Kenya Ohba <br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 238-368 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear">Visit Kaisei-sha at the Beijing Book Fair</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2010 </p>\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha will be exhibiting at the Beijing Book Fair 2010, which will be held in Beijing, China, from 30 August to 3 September 2010. Our stand will be a must-see, showcasing our extensive range of picture books, fiction and educational picture books, mostly in the science field, with a strong focus on new publications. We’re looking forward to meeting and greeting new and old friends at the fair. \r\n</p>\r\n<img src="images/news/aug2010/article_3.jpg" alt="100 house" width="384" height="238" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;">\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2010-08-23 10:40:39', 62, '', '2010-11-22 19:11:44', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-08-23 10:40:39', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 22, 0, 21, '', '', 0, 682, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(20, 'November 2010', 'november-2010', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/720.html" target="_parent">Second Picture Book from Promising Young Illustrator</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2010</p>\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha is delighted to announce the publication of a second picture book from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/akiko_miyakoshi.html" target="_self">Akiko Miyakoshi</a>, a young illustrator whose work is also regularly seen in advertising and magazines. Since the release of her first picture book, Typhoon Comes (BL Shuppan), <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/akiko_miyakoshi.html" target="_self">Akiko</a>''s work has been characterised by the selective use of colour in her primarily black-and-white illustrations. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Her new book, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a>, is based on memories of her own childhood. One wintry morning, Kikko heads into the woods with a cake for her granny, hoping to catch up with her father who left a few minutes earlier. As she goes deeper into the woods, she comes across a house filled with animals, all having a tea party together. Will Kikko make it all the way to Granny''s house? </p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a> was the most popular picture book at the Frankfurt Book Fair 2010, and now it''s the perfect season to enjoy this magical tale and its snow-filled illustrations. </p>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/720.html" target="_parent"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_1.jpg" width="176" height="211" border="0"></a></td>\r\n<td style="vertical-align:bottom; padding-left:10px;"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_1_2.jpg" alt="catalogue" width="351" height="211" border="0"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td style="margin-top:5px; "><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tea Party in the Woods</span><br />\r\n by Akiko Miyakoshi<br />\r\n26 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td></td>\r\n  \r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>Latest Addition to the Popular “100” Activity Book Series</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2010 </p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/masayuki_sebe.html" target="_parent">Masayuki Sebe</a> has won great acclaim with his “100” series of activity books, and now there’s even more fun to be had with the publication of his latest book, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/719.html" target="_parent">100 Animals on Parade</a>. \r\nAs five troupes of birds, beetles and animals parade through the pages, the reader can count, search, and play. The final pages are an explosion of shape and colour as all 500 animals appear again. It’s a beautifully detailed, content-rich book that can be enjoyed over and over, differently each time. </p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/masayuki_sebe.html" target="_parent">Sebe</a>’s activity book series has been a global hit, and is currently published in France, Canada, Portugal, Belgium, Italy, New Zealand, Thailand, Taiwan and China.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="bottom">\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/719.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_2_1.jpg" width="175" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_2_2.jpg" width="344" height="211"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td height="10px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">100 Animals on Parade</span><br />\r\n by Masayuki Sebe<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/616.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_2_3.jpg" width="133" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/519.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_2_4.jpg" width="132" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></a></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/624.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_2_5.jpg" alt="100 Play Hide and Seek" width="130" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Dinosaur Puzzles</span><br />\r\n by Masayuki Sebe<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">100 in Total</span><br />\r\n by Masayuki Sebe<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">100 Play Hide and Seek</span><br />\r\n by Masayuki Sebe<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>The Friends of Vegetable Village: All Seasons Available</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2010 </p>\r\n<p>The Friends of Vegetable Village series will finally be completed with the publication of the <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/722.html" target="_parent">Winter</a> instalment. With a book for each season, the series introduces the vegetables of spring, summer, autumn and now winter with information on the origins of each vegetables, and how to store and cook them. There’s also a charming vignette for each vegetable, giving us a glimpse into their daily lives in the Vegetable Village.  \r\nThis is the perfect series to encourage a fussy eater to start eating his or her vegetables, and can also be used as educational material in schools. \r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/722.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_3.jpg" width="158" height="221" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n\r\n<td valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Friends of Vegetable Village: Winter</span><br />\r\n by Saeko Hirokawa<br />\r\n19 x14 cm, 39 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/693.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_3_1.jpg" width="115" height="161"  border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/699.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_3_2.jpg" width="115" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/710.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_3_3.jpg" alt="100 Play Hide and Seek" width="115" height="161" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Friends of Vegetable Village: Spring</span><br />\r\n by Saeko Hirokawa<br />\r\n19 x 14 cm, 39 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Friends of Vegetable Village: Summer</span><br />\r\n by Saeko Hirokawa<br />\r\n19 x 14 cm, 39 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Friends of Vegetable Village: Autumn</span><br />\r\n by Saeko Hirokawa<br />\r\n19 x 14 cm, 39 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>Nahoko Uehashi nominated for the ALMA Award</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2010 </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_parent">Nahoko Uehashi</a>, an author of children''s fantasy fiction with an unrivalled reputation in the genre, has been nominated for the <a href="http://www.alma.se/" target="_blank">Astrid Lindgen Memrorial Award (ALMA) 2011</a> . She is the only nominee from Japan.</p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.alma.se/" target="_blank">ALMA</a> is administered by the Swedish government via the Swedish Arts Council, and is awarded in recognition of outstanding contribution to children''s literature. It had been awarded to authors, illustrators, oral storytellers and other recipients since its inception in 2003. </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_parent">Nahoko</a> is best known for her Guardian series, which has won multiple awards within Japan, and has been published in translation throughout the world, including in the US, France, Italy, Spain, Taiwan and China. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_parent">MORIBITO: Guardian of the Spirit</a>, the first book in the series, was selected by the American Library Association to receive The Mildred. L. Batchelder Award in 2009. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/480.html" target="_parent">MORIBITO II: Guardian of the Dark</a> was selected for the Mildred L. Batchelder Honor in 2010, clear testament to the high regard in which the series is held worldwide. </p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.alma.se/" target="_blank">ALMA</a> is an extremely prestigious award that attracts global attention. Will <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_parent">Nahoko</a> triumph? The results will be announced at the Bologna Children''s Book Fair in March 2011. </p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_4_1.jpg" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2010/news_4_2.jpg" alt="Nahoko Uehashi" border="0"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Guardian of the Spirit</span><br />\r\nby Nahoko Uehashi<br />\r\nillus. by Makiko Futaki<br />\r\n22 x 16 cm, 284-358 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2010-12-08 22:26:07', 62, '', '2010-12-10 22:21:01', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-12-08 22:26:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 5, 0, 20, '', '', 0, 659, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(21, 'February 2011', 'feb2011', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>We’re off to Bologna Children’s Book Fair again!</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2011 </p>\r\n<table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/feb2011/bologna.jpg" alt="Bologna Book Fair" width="276" height="211"></td>\r\n    <td width="10px">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	<td valign="top"><p>Kaisei-sha is delighted to be visiting Bologna, Italy, once more to take part in the wonderful Bologna Children’s Book Fair. This year the fair will run for four days from 28th to 31st March. We will be showcasing the very best of our new title range, so please come along and take a look – you can find us at Hall 29 A18. We’re looking forward to greeting old friends and making new ones! </p></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/691.html" target="_parent">''The Mole Bus''</a> takes Second Place at the 3rd MOE Awards</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2011</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/691.html" target="_self">‘The Mole Bus’</a> has been awarded second place in the Book Seller’s Grand Prize at the third annual MOE Awards. The awards are run by MOE, a monthly Japanese language magazine dedicated to picture books.</p>\r\nMore than 1,000 specialist book sellers and buyers, representing children’s book stores and children’s sections in larger book stores from all over the country, were surveyed in the run up to the Award. The ranking books and Grand Prize winner were determined from the results of this survey. It is wonderful to have a Kaisei-sha title appear among this select list of books recommended by the experts. </p>\r\n<p>Comments from surveyed book buyers and sellers were full of praise for the book, including “it’s bursting with humour, and develops at a wonderfully leisurely pace”, and “I’m looking forward to the next instalment”. \r\nIf you haven’t had a chance to read it yet, take a look! </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/691.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2011/mole_bus.jpg" alt="The Mole Bus" width="290" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n\r\n<td>\r\n<img src="images/news/feb2011/MOE.jpg" alt="MOE" width="161" height="211" border="0">\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Mole Bus</span><br />\r\n by Masahiko Sato and Masumi Uchino<br />\r\n19x26 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><em>Inside The House of 100 Stories</em>: Exhibition on now!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2011 </p>\r\n<p><img src="images/news/feb2011/exhibition1.jpg" width="316" height="211" style="float:left; margin-right:10px; margin-bottom:10px;/">With over 800,000 copies sold in between them, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self">‘A House of 100 Stories’</a> (published 2008) and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/672.html" target="_self">‘An Underground House of 100 Stories’</a> (published 2009) have charmed a whole generation of children. Now, children in Japan have a chance to get to know a little bit more about these magical houses at an exhibition, Inside The House of 100 Stories, being run at Kichijoji Art Museum in Musashino City. </p> \r\n<p>The exhibition features original artwork from the books, as well as interpretations of the House and its inhabitants drawn by many of its young fans. It also includes translations of the books, from Taiwan, Korea and other countries. </p> \r\n<p>Many fans, young and old alike, have packed the Museum day in, day out, and have enjoyed the workshops run as part of the exhibition. The nearby Inokashira Park Zoo has also been running an exhibition featuring the books, where children can watch and learn about the ‘real life versions’ of the animals featured in the book. This exhibition has also proved extremely popular.</p> \r\n<p>The Kichijoji Art Museum exhibition runs until 20th February. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<img src="images/news/feb2011/exhibition2.jpg" width="316" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;">\r\n</td>\r\n\r\n<td>\r\n<img src="images/news/feb2011/exhibition3.jpg" width="236" height="211" border="0">\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2011-02-23 20:49:35', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-02-23 20:49:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 19, '', '', 0, 723, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(22, 'May 2011', 'may2011', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>Two Kaisei-sha publications chosen for honours at the Sankei Children''s Publishing Culture Awards</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2011 </p>\r\n<p>The results of the Sankei Children’s Publishing Culture Awards 2011, run by Japanese broadsheet The Sankei Shimbun, have been announced and Kaisei-sha is delighted to have won two major awards. ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/721.html" target="_self">The Closing-Down Sale of Specter''s Pharmacy</a>’ was selected for the JR Best Award, and ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/702.html" target="_self">The Tiny King</a>’ won the Achievement in Art Direction Award.</p> \r\n<p>\r\nThe Sankei Children''s Publishing Culture Awards were established in 1954 and represent one of the most important benchmarks of achievement in children''s literature in Japan. The list of previous award-winning books is packed with Japan''s most outstanding works by children''s authors.  We hope that the awards will spark renewed interest in these two wonderful publications.\r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/721.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_1_1.jpg" alt="The Closing-Down Sale of Specter''s Pharmacy" width="148" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Closing-Down Sale of Specter''s <br />Pharmacy</span><br />\r\n by Michiko Ito<br />\r\n22x16 cm, 153 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr height="20px">\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/702.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_1_2.jpg" alt="The Tiny King" width="162" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n  <td><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_1_3.jpg" width="321" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tiny King</span><br />\r\nby Taro Miura<br />\r\n27x21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>New <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> book out soon! </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2011</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_2.jpg" alt="The World is Full of Curious Things" width="180" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top"><p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> is one of the most popular author-illustrators of children''s picture books today, which means there is a great deal of excitement in the air about his forthcoming publication, The World is Full of Curious Things. It follows a little boy as he moves through the world noticing all the curious and wonderful things that other people just don''t seem to see. It is as charming and rhythmical as we have come to expect from this master storyteller. In addition to creating this wonderful new book, Taro Gomi has been keeping himself busy holding workshops overseas and seeing his books being published in many different languages all around the world. Here''s hoping there is much more of the same to come in the future. </p></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The World is Full of Curious Things</span><br />\r\n by Taro Gomi </span></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a> chosen as Japan’s Nomination for Hans Christian Andersen Award </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2011 </p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n  <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/120.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_3.jpg" alt="Mr. Crow''s Bakery" width="180" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign="top"><p>The Hans Christian Andersen Awards were established by the International Board on Books for Young People (IBBY) in 1953. Renowned author-illustrator of children’s picture books, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html">Satoshi Kako</a>, has been chosen by the Japanese National Section of the IBBY to be put forward for the award.  Satoshi Kako’s work is characterised by his wonderfully imaginative illustrations, but is also remarkable for his accessible and fun-packed approach to science, made possible by Satoshi’s background in engineering. To date, he has produced more than 500 books, including the Little Daruma series and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/120.html" target="_self">Mr. Crow’s Bakery</a>, of which many have gone on to become best sellers. We’re looking forward to the results and keeping our fingers crossed for Satoshi! </p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Mr. Crow’s Bakery</span><br />\r\nby Satoshi Kako<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>Kaisei-sha at the Bologna Children''s Book Fair</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2011 </p>\r\n<p>We headed to Bologna, Italy, to take part in the Bologna Children''s Book Fair from 26th − 31st March this year. We were delighted to meet with so many of you over the four days of the fair, and are already looking forward to meeting up with familiar faces and making new friends and contacts at the Fair next year. The Bologna Children’s Book Fair 2012 is scheduled for 19th-22nd March 2012. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_4_2.jpg" width="268" height="190"></td>\r\n    <td width="10ox">&nbsp;</td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2011/topic_4_1.jpg" width="268" height="190"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 4//-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2011-05-15 09:21:16', 62, '', '2011-05-24 12:57:55', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-05-15 09:21:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 10, 0, 18, '', '', 0, 688, 'robots=\nauthor=');
