(24, 'November 2011', 'november2011', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a> <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hoge</a> Wins the Libro Picture Book Grand Prize, Chosen By Booksellers</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2011</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hoge</a>, by Tamiko Yagi, has won the second annual Libro Picture Book Grand Prize, a new award established in 2010. Libro is a Japanese bookstore chain, and the winner is voted for by Libro staff out of a shortlist of ten picture books. Picture books first published between August 2010 and July 2011 were eligible to be shortlisted. Three of the final ten shortlisted books were Kaisei-sha publications. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>First place: <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hoge by Tamiko Yagi</a><br />\r\nSixth place: <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/725.html" target="_self">Hairy Henry by Genichi Yamanishi</a><br />\r\nNinth place: <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods by Akiko Miyakoshi</a></p>\r\n\r\n<P>The shortlist will now be sold in all Libro stores. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Libro Prize does not limit itself to high profile works by established authors, but also looks towards younger and upcoming authors and artists as a way to encourage and reward new talent in the picture book field. We’re already looking forward to seeing which titles are shortlisted next year. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom">\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/little_hoge.jpg" alt="Little Hoge" width="165" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></a></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/725.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/henry.jpg" alt="Hairy Henry" width="170" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></a></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/tea_party.jpg" alt="The Tea Party in the Woods" width="173" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Little Hoge</span><br />\r\n by Tamiko Yagi<br />\r\n25 x 19 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">Hairy Henry</span><br />\r\n by Genichi Yamanishi<br />\r\n27 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tea Party in the Woods </span><br />\r\n by Akiko Miyakoshi<br />\r\n26 x 21 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>New Book from Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award Winner <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2011</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a> is an internationally renowned picture book author who received the acclaimed Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award in 2005. His new book, “It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window”, will be published by Kaisei-sha this December. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>“It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window” starts with the same line, and shows people waking up to the homes and surroundings that they love. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>“There lies the sea, just where I always see it.  <br />\r\nThere is the sky, just where it is meant to be. <br />\r\nAnd that is why I am happy to be me, now, here”.  </p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe book depicts the happiness of knowing that all the things that are important to you – the sea, the mountains, the town – are right where they should be. Almost as if Ryoji is asking each reader, what is it you love about your home?  </p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="bottom">\r\n<td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/nov2011/ryoji_arai.jpg" alt="It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window" width="155" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></p></td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/nov2011/ryoji_arai2.jpg" alt="It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window" width="307" height="211"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td height="10px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span>\r\n  <br />\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window</span><br />\r\n by Ryoji Arai <br />\r\n</span></td>\r\n  <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self">A House of 100 Stories</a> Wins ‘Academy Award’ Chosen by Children </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2011</p>\r\n<p>The ‘Minoh City World Academy Awards for Children''s Books'', organised by Minoh City in Osaka, has selected ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self">A House of 100 Stories</a>’ by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/toshio_iwai.html" target="_self">Toshio Iwai</a>. The award was developed to be a literary prize run by children, for children, to celebrate children’s literature. Children are invited to nominate their favourite books, and shortlists are drawn up for each category in June. Children are then invited to read the shortlisted books over the summer holidays, and a vote is held in September, at the beginning of the new term, to determine the winning books. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>Children aged between 6 and 12 (first to sixth year elementary school children) are eligible to vote in the picture book category. ‘A House of 100 Stories’ was the outright winner, claiming around a third of all votes. An awards ceremony will be held in November, along with visits from the authors of winning books. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Awards celebrating books for children run by children, for children. It’s a lovely idea and we certainly hope it will spread to other parts of the country. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom">\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/100_stories.jpg" alt="A House of 100 Stories" width="151" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></p></td>\r\n\r\n<td valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">A House of 100 Stories</span><br />\r\n by Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n22 x 31 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a> ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/765.html" target="_self">The Wonders of Shops</a>’ Flying Off the Shelves</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2011</p>\r\n<p>‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/pictaure/title/765.html" target="_self">The Wonders of Shops</a>’ by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/chihiro_ishizu.html" target="_self">Chihiro Ishizu</a>, illustrated by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/kumiko_nakazawa.html" target="_self">Kumiko Nakazawa</a>, features a selection of everyday shops: the patisserie, the stationers, the grocers. Each shop is beautifully illustrated over a double page spread, and is accompanied with five ‘mysteries’, text clues for something hidden in the picture. The pictures are rich in detail, and have a sense of nostalgia about them that will charm adults reading with children. In the two months since its release, in September, the book has proved extremely popular, selling 20,000 copies in three print runs, not least because of strong support from booksellers. </p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/pictaure/title/765.html" target="_parent"><img src="images/news/nov2011/nazonazo.jpg" alt="The Wonders of Shops" width="168" height="211" border="0"></a></td>\r\n<td style="vertical-align:bottom; padding-left:10px;"><img src="images/news/nov2011/nazonazo2.jpg" alt="catalogue" width="335" height="211" border="0"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td style="margin-top:5px; "><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wonders of Shops</span><br />\r\n by Chihiro Ishizu<br />\r\nillus. by Kumiko Nakazawa<br />\r\n27 × 21 cm, 23 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td></td>\r\n  \r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2011-11-18 18:56:26', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-11-18 18:56:26', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 16, '', '', 0, 687, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(23, 'August 2011', 'august2011', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>Brand New Nontan Title Released!</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2011 </p>\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n<p>The Nontan series of books has sold an incredible 28.5 million units since the first issue of the first book was released 35 years ago. This new title, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/751.html" target="_self">Nontan''s Magic Spoon</a>, is a posthumous release based on a script written by the author, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/sachiko_kiyono.html" target="_self">Sachiko Kiyono</a>, for Japan''s traditional <em>kamishibai </em>‘paper theatre''. The story was developed in order to encourage fussy eaters to eat more, along with Nontan, and has been edited into the book now released. </p> \r\n<p>The title was unfinished at the time of Kiyono''s death, and to finish the book illustrations have been borrowed from other titles, altered, and amended. This magical title is the product of much effort and involvement from a team of people. </p>\r\n<p>Hopefully the book will encourage many children to eat up, just as the author wanted. </p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/751.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic1_1.jpg" alt="Nontan" width="177" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n  <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic1_2.jpg" alt="Nontan" width="340" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Nontan’s Magic Spoon</span><br />\r\nby Sachiko Kiyono<br />\r\n19 x 16 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>New <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> Title Out Now!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2011 </p>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n<p> Internationally acclaimed picture book author, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a>, has released a brand new title: <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/758.html" target="_self">The World is Full of Curious Things</a>. Each double page spread reveals all the curious things that a little boy notices about his surroundings – but nobody else seems to! Readers can search through the illustrations to find the wonders that he has seen. The book is filled with Gomi''s characteristic charm and wit, and will bring a smile to the faces of young and older readers alike. It is also a vibrantly illustrated book, created with crisp, bright acrylics, resulting in distinctive “Gomi colours”. </p>\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/758.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic2_1.jpg" alt="The World is Full of Curious Things" width="180" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic2_2.jpg" alt="The World is Full of Curious Things" width="340" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">The World is Full of Curious Things</span><br />\r\n      by Taro Gomi<br />\r\n     26 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class="Date">\r\n  <!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n  \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>Kaisei-sha Exhibition in Fukuoka Now Open! </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2011 </p>\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha is holding an exhibition in the Fukuoka Asian Art Museum, in the southern Japanese city of Fukuoka, from 29 July through 21 August 2011. The exhibition will feature original artwork from some of Kaisei-sha’s best loved picture books, and workshops with authors <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/toshio_iwai.html" target="_self">Toshio Iwai</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a>. The opening on 29 July attracted a large crowd, and the display of a thousand picture books proved particularly popular, with many parents reading aloud to their captivated children. There was also a long queue to get photographs in front of the life-size <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/691.html" target="_self">Mole Bus</a> and the <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self">House of 100 Stories</a>. The exhibition is sure to feature on many a summer holiday to do list this year.</p>\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic3_1.jpg" alt="Kaisei-sha Exhibition in Fukuoka Now Open!" width="281" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic4_2.jpg" alt="Kaisei-sha Exhibition in Fukuoka Now Open!" width="281" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="10px">\r\n     <td colspan="2"></td>\r\n </tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic3_3.jpg" alt="Kaisei-sha Exhibition in Fukuoka Now Open!" width="281" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic3_4.jpg" alt="Kaisei-sha Exhibition in Fukuoka Now Open!" width="281" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  \r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news03"></a>Kaisei-sha will be Back at the Beijing International Book Fair</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2011 </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2011/topic4_1.jpg" alt="Beijing International Book Fair" width="281" height="211"></td>\r\n    <td width="10ox">&nbsp;</td>\r\n    <td valign="top"><p>Kaisei-sha will be exhibiting again at the Beijing International Book Fair, which this year celebrates its 18 th anniversary. The Book Fair will be held over five days, from 31 August to 4 September. China is an exciting market for Kaisei-sha; many of our books are read and enjoyed by Chinese children, and the children''s book market is growing year on year. We will be exhibiting with plenty of long sellers and some great new titles too, so please drop by if you are planning to visit. </p></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 4//-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2011-08-17 19:21:42', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-08-17 19:21:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 17, '', '', 0, 572, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(28, 'November 2012', 'november2012', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>Long-Awaited New Title from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/komako_sakai.html">Komako Sakai</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2012 </p>\r\n<p>Books by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/komako_sakai.html">Komako Sakai</a> are read and loved all over the world, and now we are delighted to release her very latest title "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/808.html">Little Hanna</a>". <br />\r\nHanna, a little girl, wakes up in the middle of the night, only to discover she’s the only one in the house awake. She plays with Chiro the cat, eats the cherries in the fridge, and plays with her sisters toys. It’s a warm and wonderful story of Hanna’s night-time adventure in her very own home. Komako’s distinct illustrative style accompanies this story, which is filled with the fun of the night and Hanna’s boundless curiosity. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/808.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/hanna_A.jpg" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/hanna_B.jpg"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">Little Hanna</span><br />\r\nby Komako Sakai<br />\r\n26 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>Nominations for the 2013 Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award Released</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2012 </p>\r\n<p>The Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award is run by the Swedish government in memory of one of Sweden’s most important authors of children’s literature. The Award is presented to authors, illustrators, oral storytellers and those active in reading promotion work, and the nominations of the 2013 Award were released at the Frankfurt Book Fair on 11 October 2012. The Award will be presented at the Bologna Children’s Book Fair on 26 March 2013. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The list of nominees can be accessed at the official site of the Astrid Lindgren Memorial Award: <a href="http://www.alma.se/en/Nominations/Candidates/2013/" target="_blank">http://www.alma.se/en/Nominations/Candidates/2013/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>Two Kaisei-sha Titles Chosen for Bookstore Awards\r\n\r\n</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2012 </p>\r\n<p>"<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/765.html">The Wonders of Shops</a>", written by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/chihiro_ishizu.html">Chihiro Ishizu</a> with illustrations by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/kumiko_nakazawa.html">Kumiko Nakazawa</a>, and "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/783.html">It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window</a>", by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/ryoji_arai.html">Ryoji Arai</a>, have taken second and third places at the third annual Libro Picture Book Grand Prize, a new award established in 2010. <br />\r\n\r\nLibro is a Japanese bookstore chain, and the winner is voted for by Libro staff out of a shortlist of ten picture books. Picture books first published between August 2011 and July 2012 were eligible to be shortlisted. Two of the final ten shortlisted books were Kaisei-sha publications. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><p><strong>Second place:</strong></p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/765.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/wonders.jpg" border="0" style="margin-right:25px;"></a></td>\r\n<td><p><strong>Third place:</strong></p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/783.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/morning.jpg" border="0"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Wonders of Shops</span><br />\r\nby Chihiro Ishizu<br />\r\nillus. by Kumiko Nakazawa<br />\r\n27 × 21 cm, 23 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window</span><br />\r\nby Ryoji Arai<br />\r\n30 x 22 cm, 32pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>The Libro Prize does not limit itself to high profile works by established authors, but also looks towards younger and upcoming authors and artists as a way to encourage and reward new talent in the picture book field. We’re already looking forward to seeing which titles are shortlisted next year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>\r\n\r\nMore New Titles from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/jun_okada.html">Jun Okada</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2012 </p>\r\n<p>New titles from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/jun_okada.html">Jun Okada</a> have been released in October and November consecutively. Jun was an art teacher at elementary schools for 38 years, while at the same time writing many books widely loved by children all over Japan. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>"<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/818.html">Night Time at the Elementary School</a>" and "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/820.html">From the Art Prep Room Window</a>" are both titles written from Jun’s perspective as an art teacher. Night Time at the Elementary School contains 18 stories on the strange and mystical happenings at a certain school. "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/820.html">From the Art Prep Room Window</a>" is Jun’s first collection of essays, previously published on the Kaisei-sha website. Jun’s published works include many captivating stories full of magic and wonder, and are really worth a read. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/818.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/night_school.jpg" border="0" style="margin-right:35px;"></a></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/820.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/nov2012/art_prep.jpg" border="0"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">Night Time at the Elementary School</span><br />\r\nby Jun Okada<br />\r\n20 × 14 cm, 140 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">From the Art Prep Room Window</span><br />\r\nby Jun Okada<br />\r\n20 x 14 cm, 240 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour photographs and black-and-white illust</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2012-11-16 23:17:00', 62, '', '2012-11-19 15:03:41', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-11-16 23:17:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 12, '', '', 0, 839, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(25, 'February 2012', 'february2012', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/katsumi_komagata.html" target="_self">Katsumi Komagata</a> invited to <a href="http://www.salondulivreparis.com/GB.htm" target="_blank">Salon du Livre</a> in Paris</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2012 </p>\r\n<p>Japan has been selected as Guest of Honor at the forthcoming <a href="http://www.salondulivreparis.com/GB.htm" target="_blank">Salon du Livre</a>, to be held in Paris from March 16-19 2012. A total of 22 authors have been invited from Japan, including <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/katsumi_komagata.html" target="_self">Katsumi Komagata</a> as representatives of children''s literature. These two well-loved authors are both published in France; Taro Gomi''s Scribbles: A Really Giant Drawing and Coloring Book is even available at the Louvre Museum. Katsumi Komagata has held many workshops in France over the years. <a href="http://www.salondulivreparis.com/GB.htm" target="_blank">Salon du Livre</a> will feature a variety of events, including workshops and autograph sessions. Do make the trip to the event if you can so that you can meet the authors in person. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="bottom">\r\n<td>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2012/news1_1.jpg" alt="Gomi Taro" width="170" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px ;/ " ></a></td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/katsumi_komagata.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2012/news1_2.jpg" alt="Katsumi Komagata" width="170" height="211" border="0" ></a></td>\r\n\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n\r\n <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a></span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/author/katsumi_komagata.html" target="_self">Katsumi Komagata</a></span></td>\r\n \r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a>’s New Title Published</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2012 </p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a>''s latest book, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/785.html" target="_self">''Where Has the Elephant Gone?''</a>, has been published. An elephant is placed in a box and taken away from his home in the highlands. He arrives at a port and travels across the ocean. Then the box arrives at an even bigger port; but when it''s opened, the elephant is nowhere to be seen. “What do we have here? The elephant''s disappeared!” </p>\r\n\r\n<p>But where can the elephant have gone? Maybe we should ask the elephant himself….This joyful book is full of the characteristic wit and humour of a Taro Gomi book. </p>\r\n</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/785.html" target="_self"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/785.html"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/feb2012/zo_1.jpg" alt="Where Has The Elephant Gone?" width="194" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; / "></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/feb2012/zo_2.jpg" width="387" height="211"></td>\r\n   \r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td colspan="2"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span> <br />\r\n        <span class="NewsBookTitle">Where Has the Elephant Gone? </span><br />\r\nby Taro Gomi<br />\r\n25 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a>’s <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/783.html" target="_self">''It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window''</a> an Immediate Best-Seller </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">Februrary 2012 </p>\r\n<p>The new book by award-winning author and illustrator <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a>, ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/783.html" target="_self">It’s Morning So I’ll Open the Window</a>’, has proved a big hit, with 23,000 copies in 3 print runs already sold since the first edition was released in December 2011. Ryoji illustrated the book after the East Japan Great Earthquake of March 2011, and the book reflects the experiences and emotions he encountered at workshops conducted with people living in disaster-struck areas. The book depicts the joy of being alive; the simple happiness of being able to always open the window to greet the new day in the same place.\r\n</p>\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr valign="bottom">\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/783.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/ryoji_arai.jpg" alt="It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window" width="155" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>    </td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/feb2012/asa_mado.jpg" alt="It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window" width="311" height="211"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW!</span> <br />\r\n          <span class="NewsBookTitle">It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window</span><br />\r\n      by Ryoji Arai <br />\r\n	  30 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br /> Full-colour illustrations\r\n    </span></td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom">&nbsp;</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>Exhibiting at <a href="http://www.bolognachildrensbookfair.com/%20" target="_blank">Bologna Children’s Book Fair 2012</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2012</p>\r\n<p>We will again be taking part in <a href="http://www.bolognachildrensbookfair.com/%20" target="_blank">Bologna Children’s Book Fair</a>, which is taking place from March 19 to 22 2012. We have a lot of new books to showcase this year, so we hope to welcome many of you at our stall, Hall 29 A-18.  </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.bolognachildrensbookfair.com/%20" target="_blank"><img src="images/news/feb2012/exhibition.jpg" width="234" height="211" border="0"></a></p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2012-02-23 01:25:55', 62, '', '2012-02-23 09:20:58', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-02-23 01:25:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 15, '', '', 0, 517, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(26, 'May 2012', 'may2012', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>“<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a>” wins the Grand Prix, 2012 Nippon Prize for Picture Books</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2012 </p>\r\n<p>“<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a>”, by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/akiko_miyakoshi.html" target="_self">Akiko Miyakoshi</a>, has won the Grand Prix at the Nippon Prize for Picture Books, a major publishing award announced at the end of March every year. The prize was established in 1995, intended to promote and publicise picture book art, to encourage people to read picture books, and to contribute to the development of the picture book publishing industry. It has since become one of the most significant awards in the children’s literature publishing industry in Japan, and this year’s winners were selected from children’s books published between October 2010 and September 2011, including the winner of the prestigious Grand Prix, “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a>”. <br />\r\nThis exceptional title has already been published in many countries overseas, including France, Korea, China, Taiwan and Mexico, and promises to win the hearts of many more readers all over the world in the future, too.</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/nov2011/tea_party.jpg" alt="The Tea Party in the Woods" width="170" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></a> </td>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><img src="images/news/may2012/topic_1.jpg" alt="The Tea Party in the Woods" width="350" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:20px;"></td>\r\n\r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tea Party in the Woods</span><br />\r\nby Akiko Miyakoshi<br />\r\n26 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n</span></td>\r\n \r\n\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n \r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>Double Win at the Sankei Award for Children’s Books and Publications　</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2012 </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha titles have won two awards at the 2012 The Sankei Award for Children''s Books and Publications: <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/author/ryoji_arai.html" target="_self">Ryoji Arai</a>''s “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/783.html" target="_self">\r\nIt''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window</a>” took the Grand Prix, while “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/791.html" target="_self">Invitation to the Summer Festival of Bon</a>”, written by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yoko_tomiyasu.html" target="_self">Yoko Tomiyasu</a> and illustrated by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/kazue_takahashi.html" target="_self">Kazue Takahashi</a>, won the Fuji Television Award. The award has been held every year since 1954, and the winners are selected from all children''s titles published between 1 January and 31 December in the previous year. The award seeks to celebrate children''s literature that will stand the test of time, ensuring that outstanding work is preserved for future generations. Since its publication in December 2012,“<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/783.html" target="_self">\r\nIt''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window</a>” has received extensive media coverage, and remains in the news in 2012. This is the second major award for “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/791.html" target="_self">Invitation to the Summer Festival of Bon</a>”, after it won the 2011 Noma Award for Juvenile Literature. </p>\r\n\r\n<table width="387" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td width="204"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/783.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2011/ryoji_arai.jpg" alt="It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window" width="155" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n    <td width="183" valign="bottom"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/791.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2012/bon.jpg" alt="Invitation to the Summer Festival of Bon" width="153" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"></a>\r\n    </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  \r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">It''s Morning So I''ll Open the Window</span><br />\r\nby Ryoji Arai <br />\r\n30 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Invitation to the Summer Festival of Bon</span><br />\r\nby Yoko Tomiyasu<br />\r\nIllustrated by Kazue Takahashi<br />\r\n21 x 16 cm, 191 pages<br />\r\nBlack-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  \r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><a href="http://www.zrukydoruky.sk/" target="_blank">From Hand to Hand</a>: Exhibition in Bologna, Italy</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2012 </p>\r\n<p>A special exhibition, <a href="http://www.zrukydoruky.sk/" target="_blank">From Hand to Hand</a>, was held from 20-24 March 2012 in the Museo Civico Medievale in Bologna, Italy, to coincide with the Bologna Children’s Book Fair. <br />\r\nThe exhibition was the brainchild of Japanese picture book author <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/nana_furiya.html" target="_self">Nana Furiya</a>, as a charitable project dedicated to the children affected by the Great East Japan Earthquake of March 2011. All works at the exhibition were open to proposals for purchase, and all profits donated to post-earthquake recovery funds.  \r\nThe exhibition then moved to BIBIANA, International House of Art for Children, in Bratislava, Slovakia, from 29 March-25 April. Japanese artists contributing to the exhibition included <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/nana_furiya.html" target="_self">Nana Furiya</a>, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/iku_dekune.html" target="_self">Iku Dekune</a>, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/junko_hayakawa.html" target="_self">Junko Hayakawa</a>, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/mako_taruishi.html" target="_self">Mako Taruishi</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/illustrator/kiyo_tanaka.html" target="_self">Kiyo Tanaka</a>.  In total, 52 artists from all over the world took part. </p>\r\n<p>The exhibition will move to various locations in the future. </p>\r\n<p>[Next exhibition]<br/>\r\nThursday 24 May 2012 - Saturday 30 June 2012<br/>\r\nat Slovak Institute in Warsaw, Poland <br/>\r\nAdress: Krzywe Koło 12/14a , Warsaw </p>\r\n\r\n<p>From Hand to Hand website: <a href="http://www.zrukydoruky.sk/" target="_blank">http://www.zrukydoruky.sk/ </a></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr valign="bottom">\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2012/exhibition_1.jpg" alt="From Hand to Hand: Exhibition in Bologna, Italy" width="281" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;">    </td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2012/exhibition_2.jpg" alt="From Hand to Hand: Exhibition in Bologna, Italy" width="281" height="211" border="0"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>Kaisei-sha at the Bologna Children’s Book Fair</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2012</p>\r\n<p>This year’s Bologna Children’s Book Fair was held over three days (19-22 March 2012) in Bologna, Italy. We were delighted to meet so many of you at our stand at the book fair and at our stall. The Bologna Children’s Book Fair will be celebrating its fiftieth anniversary next year. We’re already looking forward to seeing many familiar and new faces there in 2013. \r\nIf you didn’t manage to catch us at the fair, you can still take a look at our fair catalogue <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/images/news/feb2012/Kaisei-sha_Catalogue2012.pdf" target="_blank">here (PDF)</a>. </p>\r\n<table>\r\n  <tr valign="bottom">\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2012/bologna_1.jpg" alt="Bologna Children’s Book Fair" width="154" height="211" border="0" style="margin-right:10px;"> </td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/may2012/bologna_2.jpg" alt="Bologna Children’s Book Fair" width="296" height="211" border="0"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2012-05-17 07:07:34', 62, '', '2012-05-17 08:11:43', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-05-17 07:07:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 9, 0, 14, '', '', 0, 644, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(27, 'August 2012', 'august2012', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>A “Delicious” New Book from Kaisei-sha!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2012 </p>\r\n<p>Take a good look at this sushi. Doesn’t it look delicious? But this isn’t a photograph. It’s a drawing.<br />\r\nIn fact, it’s a page from our forthcoming publication, ''Today’s Dinner'', by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yasumi_kato.html" target="_self">Yasumi Kato</a>.</p>\r\n<p>In the picture book, a kitten peeks inside all the houses it walks past at dinner time, to see what everyone is eating.\r\nOmelette stuffed with rice, croquettes, grilled fish…each dinner looks quite delicious, and almost like the real thing.\r\nThe author-illustrator, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yasumi_kato.html" target="_self">Yasumi Kato</a>, uses just crayon and cray-pas to create her stunning images.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yasumi_kato.html" target="_self">Yasumi</a>’s incredibly life-like pictures of food have won her regular columns in food magazines, as well as a reputation as the go-to illustrator for menus and food-related websites.</p>\r\n<p>We’ll be revealing all the details at our next update, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/aug2012/dinner.jpg" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/aug2012/dinner2.jpg"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 1 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>First Picture Book from Akutagawa Prize-winning Author</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2012</p>\r\n<p>Author <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/kiyoko_murata.html" target="_self">Kiyoko Murata</a> won Japan’s most prestigious literary prize for new authors, the Akutagawa Prize, in 1987 with her novel In the Cauldron. Since then, she has continued to publish and continued to be showered with awards. In 2007, she was presented with a purple ribbon Medal of Honor, awarded by the Emperor to individuals who have made contributions in academia and the arts.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>''<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/798.html" target="_parent">Creeping into the Forest</a>'' is the stunning new picture book from this author, the first she has written. The animals of the forest decide to take their ailing friends into the scariest part of the deep, dark forest. When they finally arrive, full of fear, they find a place rich with lush trees, clear water and wonderfully cooling breeze. By the time they leave, all of the animals are feeling well and full of life. The book is a celebration of the blessings of nature.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>Illustrations are by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/kumiko_kondo.html" target="_self">Kumiko Kondo</a>, who is renowned for her pictures of the natural world—plants, insects and animals. This wonderful tale of a mysterious and magical forest is bound to refresh and enchant readers young and old alike. </p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/798.html" target="_parent"><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/aug2012/creeping.jpg" style="margin-right:10px;"></a></td>\r\n<td><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/aug2012/creeping2.jpg"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">Creeping into the Forest</span><br />\r\nby Kiyoko Murata<br />\r\nllus. by Kumiko Kondo<br />\r\n27 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n</span></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 2 //-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class="Clear"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>Kaisei-sha back at the Beijing International Book Fair</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2012 </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha will be exhibiting again at the Beijing International Book Fair, which this year celebrates its 19th anniversary. \r\nThe Book Fair will be held over five days, from 29 August to 2 September, at the China International Exhibition Center. China is an exciting market for Kaisei-sha; many of our books are read and enjoyed by Chinese children, and the children''s book market is growing year on year. We will be exhibiting with plenty of long sellers and some great new titles too, so please drop by if you are planning to visit.</p>\r\n<p><img src="http://www.kaiseisha.net/staging/images/news/aug2012/bibf.jpg"  width="281" height="211" border="0"></p>\r\n\r\n<!--//end of 3 //-->', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2012-08-14 23:24:53', 62, '', '2012-08-15 15:21:54', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-08-14 23:24:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 13, '', '', 0, 779, 'robots=\nauthor=');
