ion"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">05: Mongolia</span><br />\r\n    by Tetsuro Shimizu</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/910.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/06_usa.jpg" alt="usa" width="120" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">06: United States of America</span><br />\r\n      by Tomoko Suzuki</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/911.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/07_nepal.jpg" alt="nepal" width="120" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">07: Nepal</span><br />\r\n      by Kentaro Kumon</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/912.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/08_kenya.jpg" alt="kenya" width="120" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">08: Kenya</span><br />\r\n      by Naoko Sakuragi</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/921.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/09_bangra.jpg" alt="bangladesh" width="120" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">09: Bangladesh</span><br />\r\n      by Naoki Ishikawa</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/922.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/10_france.jpg" alt="france" width="120" height="141" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">10: France</span><br />\r\n      by Mika Posa</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/923.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/11_vietnum.jpg" alt="vietnum" width="120" height="141" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">11: Vietnam</span><br />\r\n      by Kyuya Kamazawa</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/913.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/12_cambodia.jpg" alt="cambodia" width="120" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">12: Cambodia</span><br />\r\n      by Eriko Koga</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/feb2014/romania.jpg" alt="romania spread" width="240" height="141" class="KeyLine""></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/feb2014/Finland.jpg" alt="finland spread" width="240" height="141" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Series Two: 12 volumes</b> (to be published 2014-2015)<br />\r\n13: Republic of South Africa/ \r\n14: India/\r\n15: Thailand/ \r\n16: Bhutan/ \r\n17: Burma/ \r\n18: The Philippines/ \r\n19: Peru/\r\n20: Palestine/ \r\n21: Israel/ \r\n22: Mexico/\r\n23: United Kingdom/\r\n24: Turkey/\r\n</p>\r\n<p><b>Series Three: 12 volumes </b>(to be published 2015-2016)<br />\r\n25: Ethiopia/\r\n26: Senegal/\r\n27: Indonesia/\r\n28: Australia/\r\n29: China/\r\n30: Germany/\r\n31: Italy/\r\n32: The Netherlands/\r\n33: TBC/\r\n34: TBC/\r\n35: TBC/\r\n36: TBC/\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\n <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a> Sequels Project Completed with Final Four Publications</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a>''s "Satoshi Kako''s Stories" series, first published in 1972 and 1973, has sold a total of 5.5 million copies over the years. To celebrate this remarkable achievement, Kaisei-sha and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a> launched a project, running between 2013 and 2014, to produce sequels to the beloved books in the original series. Now, the final four sequels have hit the bookstore shelves. </p>\r\n<p>Four sequels to the much-loved "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/120.html" target="_self">Mr. Crow''s Bakery</a>" were published in April 2013, and have already sold 500,000 copies. Two sequels to the equally well-known "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/875.html" target="_self">School for Robber</a>" have now reached the 100,000 copies mark. </p>\r\n<p>Many of these copies have been sold to parents who enjoyed reading the original stories when they were young, and now, as grown-ups, which to read them to their own children. Both the original series and this series of sequels have enjoyed widespread acclaim from a diverse range of readers. </p>\r\n<p>Each of the following stories is a sequel to an original story from forty years ago. Of course, all the characters have grown a little older, but that hasn''t stopped them having the sort of crazy adventures that will make readers of all ages smile. </p>\r\n<p>Together, these twenty books form a wonderful set of stories that has a unique charm across many generations. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/919.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_new_papipupepo.jpg" width="120" height="148" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Piggies Playing Music</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/920.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_new_ant.jpg" width="120" height="148" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Red Ant Adventure</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/914.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_new_tadpols.jpg" width="120" height="148" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Tadpole Elementary School </span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/915.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_new_mary.jpg" width="120" height="148" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">A Shopping Trip with Mary Blue Eyes </span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="90" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/889.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_papipupepo.jpg" width="90" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Piggies Planting Carrots</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="90" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/890.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_ant.jpg" width="90" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Red Ants and Black Ants</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="90" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/119.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_tadpols.jpg" width="90" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Tadpole Number 101</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="90" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/891.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/kako_mary.jpg" width="90" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      <p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Blue Eyes, Black Eyes, Brown Eyes</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>\r\nDiscover a Captivating New Fantasy World!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three volumes of a new fantasy series, "Maya of the Golden Moon", have been published. This exciting new series is the work of the author and illustrator team behind <em>PoPoLoCrois Story</em>, the manga which inspired the popular Playstation role-playing game <em>PoPoLoCrois</em>. </p>\r\n<p>Ten-year old Maya is a fourth-year elementary school student. One morning, she encounters a mysterious black cat, who leads her to Shadowin, the world of shadows that exists in parallel to the human world. In Shadowin, all things are made from spirits, known as “elma”, and everything is controlled by magicians known as “elmanio”. Those in Shadowin believe Maya to be the Black Elmanio, told of in Shadowin folktales as a saviour who would appear from the human world. Only the Black Elmanio can appease the dark elma whose power threatens Shadowin, and save the world from peril! </p>\r\n<p>Author <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yosuke_tamori.html" target="_self">Yosuke Tamori</a> and illustrator <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/atsuko_fukushima.html" target="_self">Atsuko Fukushima</a> have created a vast world filled with unique characters. This is truly a fantasy series to get lost in. The feedback so far is that once you''ve entered the Shadowin world, you don''t want to leave! </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/906.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/maya1.jpg" alt="maya 1" width="120" height="177" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/907.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/maya2.jpg" alt="maya 2" width="120" height="177" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/908.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/feb2014/maya3.jpg" alt="maya 3" width="120" height="177" border="0" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n   <td valign="top" colspan="2"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Maya of the Golden Moon Series</span></span><br />\r\n     by Yosuke Tamori<br />\r\n     illus. by Atsuko Fukushima</span>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>\r\nKaisei-sha Back at the <a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/home/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna Children’s Book Fair</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This year''s <a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/home/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna Children''s Book Fair</a> is the 51st anniversary of the event, and Kaisei-sha will be attending once again. Our stall will be laden with new publications, long-sellers, and many more engaging and entertaining books. Please drop by and see us; we''ll be in our usual spot, A18 in Hall 29. We are looking forward to seeing many of you as possible at this year''s fair. </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/home/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna Children''s Book Fair</a>: 24-27 March, 2014 </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/feb2014/fair1.jpg" alt="bologna fair entrance" width="240" height="140" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/feb2014/fair2.jpg" alt="bologna venue" width="240" height="140" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2014-03-09 23:43:16', 62, '', '2014-03-10 13:20:54', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-03-09 23:43:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 10, 0, 7, '', '', 0, 594, 'robots=\nauthor=');
