(37, 'Februay 2015', 'feb2015', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><strong>Three Wins for Kaisei-sha Titles at the MOE Bookseller Awards</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">MOE, published by Hakusensha, is the world&rsquo;s only monthly magazine dedicated to picture books, and it also runs the annual MOE Awards. This year, at the 7th annual awards, three Kaisei-sha titles placed in the Book Seller&rsquo;s Grand Prize, a list of the top thirty picture books as voted for by 1,900 specialist book sellers and buyers around the country. </p>\r\n<p align="left">The three titles featured on the list are shown below. We&rsquo;d like to thank all of the book sellers and buyers who voted for us as well as everyone who has read and enjoyed the books! </p>\r\n<p align="left">4th place: <em>An Undersea House of 100 Stories</em> by Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n  22nd place:  <em>The Artist who Painted a Blue Horse</em> (Japanese Edition) by Eric Carle, translated by Arthur Binard)<br />\r\n  27th place: <em>The Tin Can of Secrets</em> by Kazumi Hanayama</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/935.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201502/topic_1.jpg" alt="white crow" width="131" height="180" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n      </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201502/topic_1_bluehorse.jpg" alt="white crow" width="137" height="180" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/937.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/topic_1_can.jpg" alt="white crow" width="200" height="180" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" style="padding-left:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">An Undersea House of 100 Stories</span><br />\r\nby Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n22 x 31 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" style="padding-left:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Artist who Painted a Blue Horse</span><br />\r\nby Eric Carle<br />\r\n30 x 22 cm, 25 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" style="padding-left:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription">\r\n <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Tin Can of Secrets</span><br />\r\nby Kazumi Hanayama<br />\r\n23 x 25 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\nFull-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\nFriends Around the World: Series Two Now Published in Full </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">Kaisei-sha will celebrate its eightieth year in 2016 and to mark the occasion in 2014 we decided to launch a unique 36-volume series, &ldquo;Friends Around the World&rdquo;. <br />\r\n  The second series of 12 books has now been completed. The series covered countries as diverse as the Thailand, Peru, and the United Kingdom. Each volume features photography and text focused on one child living with a family resident in the featured country. To create these unique books, the photographer spends time with the child and his or her family, gathering images of everyday life, such as going to school, traditional events, and leisure time. The text, written by the photographer, is carefully crafted in simple language to accompany the photography and paint its own vivid picture of the life of the child, wherever he or she may be. Each volume also gives a brief overview of the history, politics, and industry of the featured country. <br />\r\n  The internet has made even the furthermost corners of the world accessible, but in many cases we still know nothing about the lives of ordinary children in other countries. This series presents the everyday joy that is present in the lives of children all over the world, through the lenses of award-winning photojournalists and artists. </p>\r\n\r\n  <p><strong>Series One: 12 volumes </strong>(published in 2014)<br />\r\n  1: Romania / 2: Republic of Korea / 3: Brazil / 4: Finland / 5: Mongolia / 6: United States of America / 7: Nepal / 8: Kenya / 9: Bangladesh / 10: France / 11: Vietnam / 12: Cambodia <br /><br />\r\n  <strong>Series Two: 12 volumes</strong> (published 2014/15)<br />\r\n  13: Mexico/ 14: Republic of South Africa/ 15: Thailand/ 16: Peru/ 17: Israel/ 18: Palestine/ 19: India/ 20: The Philippines/ 21: Bhutan/ 22: China/ 23: United Kingdom/ 24: Turkey </p>\r\n\r\n  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/944.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_13.jpg" alt="mexico" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">13: Mexico</span><br />\r\n      by Hiromi Nagakura</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/946.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_14.jpg" alt="south africa" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">14: Republic of South Africa</span><br />\r\n      by Osamu Funao</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/950.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_15.jpg" alt="thailand" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">15: Thailand</span><br />\r\n      by Eric</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/951.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_16.jpg" alt="peru" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">16: Peru</span><br />\r\n      by Tomoko Suzuki</span> </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/952.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_17.jpg" alt="israel" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">17: Israel </span><br />\r\n      by Shinichi Murata</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/953.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_18.jpg" alt="palestine" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">18: Palestine</span><br />\r\n      by  Shinichi Murata</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/nonfiction/title/957.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_19.jpg" alt="india" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">19: India</span><br />\r\n      by Kazuma Momoi</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/979.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_20.jpg" alt="philippines" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/914.html" target="_self"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">20: The Philippines</span><br />\r\n      by Naoki Ishikawa</span> </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/980.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_21.jpg" alt="bhutan" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">21: Bhutan</span><br />\r\n      by Ryoichi Saito</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/981.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_22.jpg" alt="china" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n         <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">22: China </span><br />\r\n      by Hitoshi Katanoda</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/982.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_23.jpg" alt="uk" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n         <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">23: United Kingdom</span><br />\r\n      by Kentaro Kase</span> </td>\r\n\r\n      <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/983.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/201502/wf_24.jpg" alt="turkey" width="118" height="141" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n        <p> <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">24: Turkey</span><br />\r\n      by Noriko Hayashi</span> </td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </table>\r\n\r\n<p>  <strong>Series Three: 12 volumes </strong>(to be published 2015/16)<br />\r\n25: Ethiopia / 26: Italy / 27: Senegal / 28: The Netherlands / 29: Indonesia / 30: Russia / 31: Australia / 32: Cuba / 33: Myanmar / 34: Egypt / 35: Germnay / 36: Uzbekistan</p>\r\n  </p>\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a> <strong>Kaisei-sha Returns to Bologna Children&rsquo;s Book Fair</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">February 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">The annual Bologna Children&rsquo;s Book Fair will be held in Italy from 30 March to 2 April. As always, Kaisei-sha will there in our usual spot, A18 in Hall 29. Drop by to see a selection of new publications, long-sellers, and uniquely charming picture books. We look forward to seeing you there.</p>\r\n<table width="273" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" ><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201502/topic_3_logo.jpg" alt="romania" width="138" height="180"></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/201502/topic_3.jpg" alt="romania" width="135" height="180" ></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2015-03-23 09:25:18', 62, '', '2015-10-18 16:54:28', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-03-23 09:25:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 5, 0, 3, '', '', 0, 1092, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(31, 'August 2013', 'aug2013', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>\r\n\r\nNana and Mimi: Finding Adventure in the Everyday</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2013</p>\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha is delighted to have launched a brand new picture book series, chronicling the adventures of two fun-filled sisters, Nana and Mimi. <br />\r\n  The series is the work of <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/naho_ogawa.html" target="_self">Naho Ogawa</a>, an established illustrator who works primarily for magazines and advertising. This is her first foray into picture books. <br />\r\n  The inspiration for the books lies very close to home: herself and her little sister. Together, these two little girls experience the sort of everyday mini-adventures that are familiar to us all: having Mummy fix a skirt that’s got dirty, seeing the wonder in ordinary objects through the magic of a magnifying glass, or playing princess in Granny’s old clothes. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/naho_ogawa.html" target="_self">Naho</a> has transformed each episode into an adorable and lively picture book. <br />\r\nJoin these loveable sisters on their endless adventures! </p>\r\n<p>See Naho Ogawa’s website here: <a href="http://naho.com" target="_blank">http://naho.com</a>/　</p>\r\n<table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/863.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2013/nana_mahou.jpg" width="150" height="158" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/864.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2013/nana_skirt.jpg" width="150" height="158" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/862.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2013/nana_bukabuka.jpg" width="150" height="158" border="0"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Nana’s Magical Magnifying Glasse</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Naho Ogawa </span><br />\r\n      20 x 19 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\n    Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Mimi’s Polka Dot Skirt</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Naho Ogawa </span><br />\r\n      20 x 19 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Nana and Mimi: the Dress-up Princesses</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Naho Ogawa </span><br />\r\n      20 x 19 cm, 24 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\n\r\nLong-Awaited Sequels to ‘School for Robbers’</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2013</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a>’s ‘School for Robbers’ was first published in 1973 and has been a best seller ever since, to date selling over 600,000 copies. <br />\r\n  The book tells the tale of the head teacher at a School for Robbers, Mr. Kumasaka, as he struggles to turn a bunch of no-hope robbers into master criminals. One day, the entire class goes on a school outing—to a prison! The book ends with everyone being arrested. <br />\r\n  Now, 40 years after the original smash hit, two new titles in the series are to be published: ‘School for Robbers: The Class Escapes’ and ‘School for Robbers: Sports Day Spectacular’. As the titles suggest, the story of the daring criminals continues unabated, with the class managing to escape from prison and return to the School for Robbers, where they hold a sports day. <br />\r\nIt’s hard to hate these loveable rogues—so instead share in their audacious escapades!</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2013/dorobou.jpg" width="150" height="184" style="margin-right:10px; "></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2013/dorobou_1.jpg" width="150" height="182" style="margin-right:10px; "></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/aug2013/dorobou_2.jpg" width="150" height="181" style="margin-right:10px; "></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">School for Robbers</span><br />\r\nby Satoshi Kako <br />\r\n</span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">School for Robbers: <br />\r\nThe Class Escapes</span><br />\r\nby Satoshi Kako <br />\r\n</span></td>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">School for Robbers: <br />\r\nSports Day Spectacular</span><br />\r\nby Satoshi Kako <br />\r\n</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a></span>Luehdorfia Swallowtail Flutters into Readers’ Hearts </h2>\r\n<p class="TopItem"><span class="Date">August 2013</span></p>\r\n<p class="TopItem">It has been four years since the publication of ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/627.html" target="_self">Burying Beetle</a>’, by Hiroshi Tateno, a beautifully illustrated tale of the miniature world of the burying beetle, together with the creatures and nature that surround it. <br />\r\n  His new book, ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/861.html" target="_self">Luehdorfia Swallowtail</a>’, follows a swallowtail pupa as it passes through the four seasons in the forest. <br />\r\nIt is a perilous journey for the caterpillar to reach the pupal stage—the forest is filled with enemies—and few achieve it. It must then spend almost a year as a pupa, only transforming into a butterfly the following spring. Here, the death-defying lifecycle of the luehdorfia swallowtail is captured in painstakingly beautiful miniature. The book has been enjoying steadily accelerating attention from the media, patiently waiting, like the pupa, to emerge into the spotlight. </p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/627.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2013/shidemushi.jpg" width="150" height="179" border="0" style="margin-right:20px; "></a></td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/861.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/aug2013/gifuchou.jpg" width="150" height="176" border="0" style="margin-right:10px; "></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Burying Beetle</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Hiroshi Tateno</span><br />\r\n      29 x 25 cm, 36 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n    <td><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Luehdorfia Swallowtail</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Hiroshi Tateno</span><br />\r\n      29 x 25 cm, 40 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class="TopItem">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>Kaisei-sha Exhibiting at Books Fairs in Beijing and Frankfurt</h2>\r\n<p class="TopItem"><span class="Date">August 2013</span></p>\r\n<p class="TopItem">Kaisei-sha will be exhibiting again at the Beijing International Book Fair, which this year will be held from 28 August to 1 September, and will also be at the Frankfurt Book Fair, which runs from 9 October to 13 October. <br />\r\nWe will be exhibiting with our range of great new titles for 2013 together with plenty of best and long sellers. Please drop by if you are planning to visit.</p>\r\n<p>■ <a href="http://www.bibf.net/websiteen/home/default.aspx" target="_blank">Beijing International Book Fair</a> <br />\r\n■ <a href="http://www.buchmesse.de/en/fbf/" target="blank">Frankfurt Book Fair</a></p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2013-09-23 10:24:46', 62, '', '2013-09-23 20:09:08', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-09-23 10:24:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 9, '', '', 0, 489, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(32, 'November 2013', 'nov2013', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>\r\n\r\nNew Publication from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2013</p>\r\n\r\n<p>‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/876.html" target="_self">The Elephant is Going Nowhere</a>’, a delightful new picture book from renowned author-illustrator <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> is a companion publication to his recent publication, ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/785.html" target="_self">Where Has the Elephant Gone?</a>’. In this new tale, the elephant is stolen from his home in a helicopter, placed on a plane, and flown off to a far-away zoo. But he soon manages to get himself home, together with a little girl he has met on the way. But how? You’ll have to read Taro’s latest, lovely book, full of humour and with a philosophical touch, to find out. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/876.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/zo_nowhere.jpg" alt="The Elephant is Going Nowhere" width="120" height="127" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/nov2013/zo_spread.jpg" alt="The Elephant is Going Nowhere" width="240" height="127" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:40px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/785.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/zo.jpg" alt="Where Has the Elephant Gone?" width="120" height="127" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n   <td width="120" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">The Elephant is Going Nowhere</span></span><br />\r\n     by <span class="TopItem">Taro Gomi </span><br />\r\n     25 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n     Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n   <td width="240" valign="top">\r\n   <td width="120" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Where Has the Elephant Gone?</span></span><br />\r\n     by <span class="TopItem">Taro Gomi </span><br />\r\n     25 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n     Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\n\r\nLook, Find and Enjoy – Over and Over! </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2013</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha is pleased to announce the publication of a second book from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/yutaka_nakagaki.html" target="_self">Yutaka Nakagaki</a>, who made his picture book debut with ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/829.html">The Queue</a>’. This time, in ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/871.html" target="_self">How to Build a UFO</a>’, a spaceship crashes on Earth, prompting the people on the ground to work together to build a brand new craft for the aliens who have lost their only way of getting home. Just like ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/831.html">The Queue</a>’, this new picture book is crammed full of colourful characters in multiple scenarios on each page. This ensures that there will be discovery after discovery for young readers, no matter how many times the book is read. You can even prompt the search with the find-the-picture game at the back of the book. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/871.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/UFO.jpg" alt="How to Build a UFO" width="120" height="139" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/nov2013/UFO_spread.jpg" alt="How to Build a UFO" width="240" height="139" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:40px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/829.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/gyoretsu.jpg" alt="The Queue" width="120" height="139" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n   <td width="120" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">How to Build a UFO</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Yutaka Nakagaki</span><br />\r\n      27 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n   <td width="240" valign="top">\r\n   <td width="120" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">The Queue</span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Yutaka Nakagaki</span><br />\r\n      27 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>\r\n\r\n‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/702.html" target="_self">The Tiny King</a>’: Multiple Translations Published</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2013</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="TopItem">There once was a tiny king who lived in a very big castle, where he was ever so lonely indeed. Then, one day, he meets a big princess, and soon his big, lonely castle is filled with children and laughter and joy. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_miura.html" target="_self">Taro Miura</a> has created a real hit with this combination of a classical fairytale with bold graphics and detailed illustration. The book has now been published in the following languages. <br />\r\n\r\nIn addition, a version in simplified Chinese is soon to be published in China. We have “high” hopes that the prequel to ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/704.html">The Tiny King</a>’, ‘<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/865.html" target="_self">The Big Princess</a>’, will also be translated into many languages for children all over the world to enjoy. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n        <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/country/title/702.html?country=7" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/tinyking_UK.jpg" width="100" height="130" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/country/title/702.html?country=25" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/tinyking_MX.jpg" width="100" height="130" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/country/title/702.html?country=2" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/tinyking_FR.jpg" width="100" height="130" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/country/title/702.html?country=10" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/tinyking_KR.jpg" width="100" height="130" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/country/title/702.html?country=11" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/tinyking_TW.jpg" width="100" height="130" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n   <td width="100" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">English: </span></span><br />Walker Books/<br /> Candlewick Press</td>\r\n   <td width="100" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem"> Spanish: </span></span><br />Fondo de Cultura Economica</td>\r\n   <td width="100" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem"> French: </span></span><br />Editions Milan</td>\r\n   <td width="100" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem"> Korean: </span></span><br />Gimm-Young Publishers</td>\r\n   <td width="100" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Taiwanese <br />(traditional Chinese): </span></span><br />Hsiao Lu</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>\r\n\r\n''<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a>'' Comes to Life!</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2013</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, almost. ''<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a>''  is the charmingly quirky soft toy who is the star of smash-hit picture book of the same name, which has sold more than 60,000 copies since its release in 2011. Given as a gift to Yu by her uncle, ''<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a>''  puts up with all the trials and tribulations soft toys must go through…until one day he is left at home and decides to show how he really feels! This grumpy but impossible-to-hate character is now available as a soft toy, in three different delightful designs. Who will be the next little boy or girl to receive a ''<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a>''  from a favourite relative?  </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2013/LittleHogge.jpg" alt="Little Hogge" width="120" height="153" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n    <td><img src="images/news/nov2013/LittleHogge_toys.jpg" alt="Hogge soft toys" width="203" height="153" class="KeyLine" style="margin-right:10px"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td width="120" valign="top"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle"><span class="TopItem">Little Hogge </span></span><br />\r\n      by <span class="TopItem">Tamiko Yagi </span><br />\r\n      25 x 19 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2013-12-04 10:20:19', 62, '', '2013-12-04 10:35:06', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-12-04 10:20:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 8, '', '', 0, 1054, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(36, 'November 2014', 'nov2014', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>\r\nThe Hans Christian Andersen Awards Ceremony held in Mexico City </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Naoko Uehashi</a>, winner of the 2014 Hans Christian Andersen Author Award, received her award at a ceremony held in Mexico City in September 2014.\r\nThe ceremony was held, as always, during the International Board on Books for Young People (IBBY) Congress. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Uehashi</a> was given her award alongside the Brazilian illustrator Roger Mello, who won the 2014 Hans Christian Andersen Illustrator Award. In her speech,  <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Uehashi</a> said “Stories give us the ability to be someone else. By making our way through the book together with that someone else, we find ourselves in a slightly different position after we finish the book than where we were before we started to read it. I hope to continue to write this sort of story”.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHer Guardian of the Spirit series, which began with <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self">Moribito: Guardian of the Spirit</a>, now numbers ten volumes. The epic series allows the reader to experience the story by understanding the perspective and the motives of its characters, such as Balsa, the female bodyguard, and Chagum, the Imperial prince.  <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Uehashi</a>’s books depict the llives of the characters who populate them with a richness that goes well beyond a simple battle of good versus evil. Her well deserved award will hopefully help to introduce her body of work to more readers around the world.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/nov2014/andersen1.jpg" alt="andersen award1" width="240" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/nov2014/andersen2.jpg" alt="andersen award2" width="240" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\nCuddly Critter  <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a> is Back! </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuddly critter <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a> stole the hearts of readers young and old alike in his smash-hit first outing, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/753.html" target="_self">Little Hogge</a>, published in 2011. Now he is back in a highly anticipated new tale, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/949.html" target="_self">Little Hogge Gets Lost</a>. This time, Little Hogge is taken to the zoo by his owner Yuu and her family. But Little Hogge soon manages to get himself separated, which means he has to search through the whole zoo to find his family—who aren’t anywhere to be seen!  Join Little Hogge as he navigates his way through the animals at the zoo on his quest to get back home.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/949.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2014/hoge1.jpg" alt="hogge1" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Little Hogge Gets Lost</span></br>by Tamiko Yagi\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/nov2014/hoge2.jpg" alt="hogge2" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>\r\nBrand New Fantasy Series set in a Japanese Shinto Shrine </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">November 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/takako_sato.html" target="_self">Takako Sato</a> is an award-winning writer—her accolades include the prestigious Naoki Prize for Literature—who is known her meticulous research process, which imparts an impressive sense of realism to her work. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/takako_sato.html" target="_self">Sato</a> has now developed a new fantasy series, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/966.html" target="_self">White Crow</a>, which centres around Chisato, a supremely stubborn fifth-year elementary school student and martial arts virtuoso who lives in a Shinto shrine (Shinto is an animistic religion indigenous to Japan). Together with a handful of schoolmates, Chisato has been chosen to be part of the children’s performance group for the shrine. But their adventures go way beyond rehearsal, as they discover a world that’s almost normal, but not quite. The first three instalments, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/966.html" target="_self">Power Stone</a>, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/967.html" target="_self">Wake Up!</a> and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/968.html" target="_self">In Rehearsal</a> are all on sale now. The forth and fifth instalments are scheduled for publication in 2015.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/966.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/nov2014/shirogarasu1.jpg" alt="white crow" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">White Crow 1: Power Stone</span></br>by Takako Sato</p>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2015-01-27 00:21:06', 62, '', '2015-01-27 00:35:41', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-01-27 00:21:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 4, '', '', 0, 669, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(34, 'May 2014', 'may2014', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>\r\n<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Nahoko Uehashi</a> Wins Author’s Award at 2014 Hans Christian Andersen Awards </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Renowned children’s author <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Nahoko Uehashi</a> has been chosen as the recipient of the Author’s Award at the 2014 Hans Christian Andersen Awards. She is best known as the author of the “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self">Moribito: Guardian of the Spirit</a>” books, a stunning fantasy series that has already been translated into many languages and published in the US, France, Spain, China, Taiwan and many more countries worldwide. </p>\r\n<p>The Hans Christian Andersen Awards, established in 1956, are presented every other year to one living author and one living illustrator whose complete works have made a lasting contribution to children''s literature. Previous recipients of the Author’s Award include such leading figures as Tove Jansson, Astrid Lindgren, Erich Kästner, and David Almond. </p>\r\n<p>The 2014 recipients were announced at a press conference at the <a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/en/the-best-venue-for-childrens-publishers-to-meet/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna Children’s Book Fair</a>; <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Uehashi</a>’s name was met with a cheer from the audience. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Uehashi</a> herself was reportedly overcome with joy on hearing that she had been chosen for the honour, and has been busy with press interviews ever since. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/uehashi.jpg" alt="naoko uehashi" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>Author Nohoko Uehashi\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/seirei.jpg" alt="guardian of the spirit" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">Guardian of the Spirit</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\nNew Young Adult Fiction, Classmates, Released</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Classmates, a new two-part collection of short stories, tells the stories of 24 children, all of whom are in the same junior high school class. Parts One and Two have been released simultaneously. </p>\r\n<p>Author <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/eto_mori.html" target="_self">Eto Mori</a> is perhaps best known today as a recipient of the prestigious Naoki Prize for literature, but her background is in children’s literature; she made her debut with a children’s novel and has continued to write for children and young adults. </p>\r\n<p>In this new collection, she tackles the many issues that children face as they transition into young adulthood: life at home, friendships, first love, problems with teachers. As she tells each classmate’s story in turn, the class, initially a rag-tag bundle of strangers, gradually begins to come together as a unified whole. </p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/eto_mori.html" target="_self">Mori</a> takes a very realistic approach in her depiction of these contemporary school children, but the stories are peppered with gentle humour, and build to an ending designed to encourage and empower the reader. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/928.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/classmates1.jpg" alt="classmates1" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Classmates Part 1</span></br>by Eto Mori\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/nonfiction/title/929.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/classmates2.jpg" alt="classmates2" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Classmates Part 2</span>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>\r\nLatest Instalment in The Rent-A-Ghost Store Series Now On Sale</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Rent-A-Ghost Store series tells the story of Tamotsu, an elementary school kid with a difference—he runs the local Rent-A-Ghost store with his team of ghosts. Tamotsu commissions his ghosts to perform tasks for clients, and in return he gives the ghosts what they love the best—renditions of their favourite lullabies. </p>\r\n<p>Enter the magical world of Tamotsu, Pomposo Mysterion (the giant rabbit who looks after Tamotsu), and all the ghosts who work for him. The mixture of text and illustrations makes this a perfect choice for young readers to gain confidence. The series has proved a big hit with young readers, thanks to its depiction of the hard-working elementary school-age protagonist, and the adorable team of ghosts. This fourth book is testament to the popularity of the series. </p>\r\n<p>The latest task facing Tamotsu and his ghosts is babysitting. They find themselves struggling to control Temari, the naughty little girl they are taking care of. An evening of searching for Temari, an expert escape artists, and coaxing her to behave awaits!  </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/934.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/ghost4.jpg" alt="ghost4" width="120" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle"> 4: The Baby-Sitter</span></br> by Rika Okabe</p>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width=“90” style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/759.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/ghost1.jpg" alt="ghost1" width=“90” class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">1: What Ghosts Do</br> for a Living</span></p>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width=“90” style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/796.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/ghost2.jpg" alt="ghost2" width=“90” class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">2: Trust Us with</br> Your Secret Tasks</span></p>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width=“90” style="padding-left:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/850.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/may2014/ghost3.jpg" alt="ghost3" width=“90” class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">3: It’s Hard Work</br> Being Floaty</span></p>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>\r\nAnother great year at <a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/en/the-best-venue-for-childrens-publishers-to-meet/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna</a></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kaisei-sha was once again part of the <a href="http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/en/the-best-venue-for-childrens-publishers-to-meet/878.html" target="_blank">Bologna Children’s Book Fair</a>. We would like to thank everyone who dropped by our stall to see us and our selection of Kaisei-sha publications. We’re already looking forward to being back in Bologna in 2015. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="240" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/may2014/bologna.jpg" alt="bologna fair" width="240" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2014-06-06 11:37:57', 62, '', '2014-06-18 20:28:47', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-06-06 11:37:57', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 6, '', '', 0, 1132, 'robots=\nauthor=');
