(35, 'August 2014', 'aug2014', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a>\r\nAn Undersea House of 100 Stories Hits the Shelves </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After a five year wait, the next book in the House of 100 Stories has finally hit the shelves. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/935.html" target="_self">An Undersea House of 100 Stories</a> follows on from the publication of <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/558.html" target="_self">A House of 100 Stories</a> (2008) and <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/672.html" target="_self">An Underground House of 100 Stories</a> (2009). Sales of the two previous books have totalled more than 1.35 copies, and the latest book looks set to continue that success, selling 170,000 copies in its first month alone. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>After the overground and underground versions of the two previous books, this time we explore a house under the sea. A little girl accidentally drops her favourite doll, Ten, over the side of the ship she has boarded. As Ten tumbles down through the water, all of her lovely clothes and accessories fall off, and eventually she lands on the first floor of a very strange undersea house. She begins to make her way down through the stories of the house, searching for her clothes and her accessories. But the octopuses and dolphins and all the other sea creatures living in the house already seem to have found good uses for Ten’s things….whatever will she do? \r\n</p>\r\n<p>As with the other books, each story is illustrated in enchanting detail, meaning that there is much to capture the attention of little readers every time they open the book. \r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/935.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/august2014/100stories1.jpg" alt="undersea house cover" width="128" class="KeyLine"></a><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">An Undersea House of 100 Stories</span></br>by Toshio Iwai\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/august2014/100stories2.jpg" alt="undersea house text1" width="195" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:10px"><img src="images/news/august2014/100stories3.jpg" alt="undersea house text2" width="195" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a>\r\nNew Taro Gomi Book Published </h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest work from <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a>, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/936.html" target="_self">The Shadow Plane</a>, is now available to buy. <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> is much loved for his playful picture books, charming word play, and his ability to engage young and old minds alike with his games and guides. This publication, however, is a little different; it has a beautiful poetic style, together with all the distinct characteristics of a Gomi book. A little boy boards the shadow plane, which flies underneath the plane flying peacefully through the sky. He is soon joined by all the different people and animals over which the shadow plane flies. Both planes glide over the ocean to their final destination. And when they land and the plane doors open, there’s a very Gomi-esque ending to the book, filled with humour. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="176" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/936.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/august2014/kage1.jpg" alt="classmates1" height="176" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">The Shadow Plane</span></br>by Taro Gomi\r\n    </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="176" style="padding-left:0px"><img src="images/news/august2014/kage2.jpg" alt="classmates2" height="176" class="KeyLine"></a><p>\r\n<span class="NewsBookDescription"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a>\r\nMoribito: Guardian of the Spirit</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fresh from winning the Author’s Award at the 2014 Hans Christian Andersen Awards, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/nahoko_uehashi.html" target="_self">Nahoko Uehashi</a> will now see her popular fantasy series, <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self">Moribito: Guardian of the Spirit</a>, adapted into a live-action drama. NHK, Japan’s national broadcaster, will be airing the first of the ten books in the series in 2016. The adaptation is set to run over 22 episodes over a three year period. The broadcast still a little way off, but seeing Uehashi’s fantasy world come to life on our screens is certainly something to look forward to. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/479.html" target="_self"><img src="images/news/august2014/guardian1.jpg" alt="guardian of the spirit" width="123" class="KeyLine">\r\n  <span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="TopItem">Moribito: Guardian of the Spirit</span></p>\r\n    </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news04" id="news04"></a>\r\nLike Us on Facebook</h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/偕成社/552925014817568" target="_blank"><img src="images/news/august2014/fb_logo.png" style="float:left; margin-right:10px; /"></a>We launched a <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/偕成社/552925014817568" target="_blank">Kaisei-sha Facebook</a> page on 1 July this year. It’s only in Japanese at the moment, but features cover artwork and photographs of our publications, so please like and share! \r\nFind us <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/偕成社/552925014817568" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2014-09-21 14:39:40', 62, '', '2014-09-21 14:43:57', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-09-21 14:39:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 3, 0, 5, '', '', 0, 1069, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(38, 'May 2015', 'may2015', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><strong>A Beguiling New Book from The Cabin Company</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">The Cabin Company, comprised of two young creative talents, has already attracted plenty of buzz for their work—and this new publication is sure to raise their profile even further. "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/991.html" target="_self">Professor Ponderous and his Curious Creatures</a>" reveals some strange secrets to us: did you know that many of the weird and wonderful things in the world are, in fact, the work of some even weirder and more wonderful creatures? <br />\r\nProfessor Ponderous is on hand to guide us through his compendium of these curious creatures. Have you ever asked yourself, for example, why pedestrian crossings are marked with stripes? It’s all down to the Street Stitcher, a mysterious creature determined to sew up the gaps in the pavement—but always and only in secret, when the streets are empty of people. The pages of "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/991.html" target="_self">Professor Ponderous and his Curious Creatures</a>" reveal the nonsensical yet somehow quite believable beings responsible for many of the things we take for granted around us. <br />\r\n The Cabin Company is currently working with a number of publishers, including Kaisei-sha, to bring their uniquely imaginative work to as many readers as possible; this is one creative team to keep a keen eye on. \r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/991.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/hatena.jpg" alt="curious creatures" width="150" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n     </td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="300" style="padding-right:10px"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/itonui.jpg" alt="curious creatures spread" width="300" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span><span class="NewsBookTitle">Professor Ponderous and his Curious Creatures</span><br />\r\n      by The Cabin Campany<br />\r\n      24 x 24 cm, 60 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span>\r\n   </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table><br />\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/1001.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/yorudesu.jpg" alt="night time" width="100" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n    \r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">Night Time</span><br />\r\n      by The Cabin Company<br />\r\n      24 x 29 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><strong>New Night-time Inspired Picture Book from Promising Young Author-Illustrator</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">Author-illustrator Akiko Miyakoshi came to prominence with the award-winning "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/720.html" target="_self">The Tea Party in the Woods</a>". Now, she is back with a beautiful new book, inspired by the night: "<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/992.html" target="_self">Walking Home through the Night</a>". <br />\r\nNight-time. A young rabbit boy is being carried home by his mother. As they pass through the streets, the boy peers through the windows of the houses lining the streets, and lets his imagination reveal what is happening in each home. What is everyone doing? Are they having a party? Or getting ready to have a bath and go to bed? Are they reading the next chapter of the story they were reading the night before? <br />\r\nSome people are only just being welcomed back home. Others are getting on the train to make the long journey back to their family. And a little rabbit is turning off the bedroom light so he can turn in for the night. Full of warmth and charm, this picture book capture those night-time moments shared by us all.  </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/992.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/yorunokaerimichi.jpg" alt="walking home" width="150" class="KeyLine"></a>\r\n    </td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="300" style="padding-right:0px"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/yorunokaerimichi_2.jpg" alt="walking home spread" width="300"  class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">Walking Home through the Night</span><br />\r\n      by Akiko Miyakoshi<br />\r\n      27 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n   </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n   \r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><strong>Spooky New Stories from the Rent-A-Ghost Store</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">May 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">School boy and Rent-A-Ghost shop owner Tamotsu is back, along with his supernatural staff, in this latest instalment of the popular Rent-A-Ghost series. It’s a busy time in Tamotsu’s town, as his ghosts, ever-ready to lend a hand, are called to the local elementary school by the head teacher to help get a surprise graduation present ready for the students about to finish their final year.<br />\r\nThe fanbase for the Rent-A-Ghost series continues to grow with every new publication, which means that plenty of young readers will be dying to know what Tamotsu and his ghosts get up to in this latest collection of stories. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/fiction/title/994.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/yorunogakko.jpg" alt="night school" width="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="300" style="padding-right:0px"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/yorunogakko_2.jpg" alt="night school spread" width="300" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="150" style="padding-right:10px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Rent-A-Ghost Store - 5: Night School Mission</span><br />\r\n      by Rika Okabe<br />\r\n      21 x 16 cm, 87 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour and black-and-white illustrations</span></td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/759.html"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/obake1.jpg" width="100" alt="ghost1" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/796.html"><img style="margin-right:0px;"  src="images/news/may2015/obake2.jpg" width="100" alt="ghost2" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/850.html"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/obake3.jpg" width="100" alt="ghost4" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/fiction/title/934.html"><img style="margin-right:0px;" src="images/news/may2015/obake4.jpg" width="100" alt="ghost4" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr align="left">\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">1:What Ghosts Do For a Living</span><br />\r\n    </span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">2:Trust Us with Your Secret Tasks</span><br />\r\n    </span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">3: It’s Hard Work Being Floaty</span><br />\r\n    </span></td>\r\n    <td valign="top" width="100" style="padding-right:5px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"><span class="NewsBookTitle">4: The Baby-Sitter</span><br />\r\n    </span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  \r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2015-07-09 23:01:07', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-07-09 23:01:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 2, '', '', 0, 404, 'robots=\nauthor='),
(39, 'August 2015', 'aug2015', '', '<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news01" id="news01"></a><strong>Taro Gomi Wins the 50th TonenGeneral Children’s Culture Award </strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">Renowned children’s author-illustrator <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a>, who celebrates his seventieth birthday this year, has been announced as the recipient of the 50th TonenGeneral Children’s Culture Award. This long-standing and prestigious award, established in 1966, is bestowed upon individuals and foundations which have made a significant contribution to the development and enrichment of children’s culture in Japan. This is the second time in recent years that a Kaisei-sha published author has received the honour: in 2012, the winner was <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/satoshi_kako.html" target="_self">Satoshi Kako</a>, author-illustrator of such classics as “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/120.html" target="_self">Mr Crow’s Bakery</a>". The selection panel gave the following reasons for the selection: “<a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/taro_gomi.html" target="_self">Taro Gomi</a> is widely renowned internationally, having won numerous awards, including the Graphic Prize at the Bologna Children''s Book Fair, and been widely published in translation. His works are familiar to children all over the world, and through this body of literature he has made a substantial contribution to the cultural lives of children in Japan and beyond”. The author will be presented with the award at a ceremony in November 2015. </p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/gomi.jpg" alt=“taro gomi“ height="200" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/69.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/koushi.jpg" alt=“koushi” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/38.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/bus.jpg" alt=“bus” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/936.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/hikouki.jpg" alt=“hikouki” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n     <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle"></span><br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      </span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">A Calf in Spring</span><br />\r\n      by Taro Gomi<br />\r\n      26 x 21 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Bus Has Come</span><br />\r\n      by Taro Gomi<br />\r\n      25 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">The Shadow Plane</span><br />\r\n      by Taro Gomi<br />\r\n      25 x 23 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news02" id="news02"></a><strong>Komako Sakai Special Edition Stamps Released!</strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/komako_sakai.html" target="_self">Komako Sakai</a> is a children’s author-illustrator whose distinctive style has won her praise both throughout Japan and internationally. Her work has now been celebrated in the release, on 18 September 2015, of a limited edition set of Japan Post stamps. The set of ten stamps is the first part of a series entitled “Nostalgia for Pictures of Children”,  and features images from her award-winning book “Emily’s Balloon”, as well as her cover illustrations used for “Haha no Tomo”, a popular monthly magazine on parenting and children’s literature. Anyone making the trip to Japan should pop into their local Japan Post office and pick up a set – to keep, since they are clearly too lovely to actually use! And don’t forget to stock up on Kaisei-sha books while you’re here, too! </br>\r\nSee details on <a href="https://www.post.japanpost.jp/kitte_hagaki/stamp/tokusyu/2015/h270918_t.html" target=“_blank”>Japan Post homepage</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/stamps.jpg" alt=“stamps“ height="200" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/385.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/sucre.jpg" alt=“sucre” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/backlist/picture/title/808.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/hanna.jpg" alt=“hanna” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n     <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle"></span><br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      </span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">Friday''s Sugar</span><br />\r\n      by Komako Sakai<br />\r\n      19 x 14 cm, 61 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle">Little Hanna</span><br />\r\n      by Komako Sakai<br />\r\n      26 x 22 cm, 32 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="TopItem"><a name="news03" id="news03"></a><strong>A House of 100 Stories: Series Now Available in Handy Miniature Sizes! </strong></h2>\r\n<p class="Date">August 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="left">”The House of 100 Stories” series, by <a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/author/toshio_iwai.html" target="_self">Toshio Iwai</a>, continues to enchant young readers, selling more than two million copies in total. Now, the series is available as miniature book boards, perfect for popping into a bag to take along with you on a day out for entertainment on the go. A gift set is also available, which includes miniature versions of all three books, and makes an ideal present for little readers with little hands.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/100stories_box.jpg" alt=“box“ height="200" class="KeyLine"></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/1004.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/100stories_mini.jpg" alt=“100stories mini” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/1005.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/100underground_mini.jpg" alt=“100underground mini” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="bottom" width="120" style="padding-left:0px"><a href="http://www.kaiseisha.net/newpublications/newpicture/title/1006.html" target="_self"><img style="margin-right:10px;" src="images/news/201508/100undersea_mini.jpg" alt=“100undersea mini” height="150" class="KeyLine"></a></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n\r\n  <tr>\r\n     <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="NewsBookTitle"></span><br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      <br />\r\n      </span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">A House of 100 Stories: Mini Edition</span><br />\r\n      by Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n      18 x 13 cm, 34 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">An Underground House of 100 Stories: Mini Edition</span><br />\r\n      by Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n      18 x 13 cm, 34 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n\r\n    <td valign="top" width="120" style="padding-right:0px"><span class="NewsBookDescription"> <span class="New">NEW! </span> <span class="NewsBookTitle">An Undersea House of 100 Stories: Mini Edition</span><br />\r\n      by Toshio Iwai<br />\r\n      18 x 13 cm, 34 pages<br />\r\n      Full-colour illustrations</span></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, '2015-07-09 23:01:07', 62, '', '2015-10-29 19:08:21', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-07-09 23:01:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=