(101, '1,2', 1, 'Seizo', 'Tashima', '', 'Born in Osaka in 1940. He moved to contryside in Tokyo in 1969 and while recreating scenes and words from his very rural life, he also painted nature, animals and children.\r\nWith his strong painting style, he worked prolifically producing pieces such as ‘Drop a Stone and Forget’ and ‘Ball in the Grass’.\r\nHe has won many awards including the BIB Golden Apple Award for ‘Chikara Taro’ in 1969, and the Bologna International Book Fair Graphic Prize for ‘Fly, Grasshopper!’ in 1989.\r\nHe has recently been putting his writing ability to good use and is actively involved in environmental issues.', '', '', '', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-10-13 18:44:22', 62, 1),
(102, '1,2', 1, 'Shigeru', 'Tamura', '', 'Born in 1949 in Tokyo. Illustrator and animator.\r\nTamura expresses poetic and fantastic worlds through his picture books, animated cartoons, motion pictures and CDs. His pictures, which use a variety of different mediums such as watercolours, coloured pencils, graphics and photographs are loved by many, he is the recipient of many children’s book awards and animation prizes in Japan.\r\nHis illustrations have recently been used for the covers of monthly magazines and he works in an increasing number of fields. ', 'shigeru_tamura_big.jpg', 'http://www.tamurashigeru.com/', 'Japanese only', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-10-13 18:44:56', 62, 1),
(103, '1', 1, 'Yoko', 'Tomiyasu', '', 'Born in Tokyo in 1959.\r\nIn addition to being chosen for the IBBY Honour List 2002, Tomiyasu has also won many prizes for children’s literature in Japan.\r\nHer fantasy stories, which are imaginatively inspired by Japanese folk tales and flavoured with modern day humour, are loved by many children. ', 'yoko_tomiyasu_b.jpg', '', '', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-10-13 18:45:13', 62, 1),
