(202, '1,2', 1, 'Tsutomu', 'Murakami', '', 'Born in Hyogo in 1943.\r\nHis picture book and fairy story illustrations show a lively creative spirit and his fine, delicate lines and fresh young colours are highly respected all over the world.\r\nIn 1972 and 1989 he won bronze medals for ‘The Most Beautiful Picture Book’ at the International Book Design Exhibition in Leipzig, for ‘I wish I had a big, big tree’ and ‘Sankichi the Fox’.\r\nHis illustrations have wide support and in Japan he is involved in fields such as stamp design.', '', '', '', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2012-08-15 11:19:50', 62, 1),
(203, '2', 1, 'Yasunari', 'Murakami', '', 'Born 1955 in Gifu. Murakami’s ‘Pink and Old Man Snow’ (Tokuma Shoten) was given a Special Mention in the Graphic Prize for Children at the 1986 Bologna Children’s Book Fair. In 1988, his ‘Present’ (Book Loan Publishing) and the following year his ‘Welcome to the Forest’ (Tokuma Shoten) were also given Special Mentions. His ‘Pink! Pearl!’ won a Gold Plaque at the 1991 Biennial of illustrations in Bratislava. Murakami displays his original illustrations at his private gallery in Ito, Shizuoka. His hobby is fishing, for which he makes many worldwide trips. ', '', 'http://www.murakami-museum.co.jp/', 'Japanese only', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-10-13 19:00:33', 62, 1),
