(321, '1', 1, 'Masahiko', 'Sato', '', 'Born in Shizuoka. Currently a Professor at the Graduate School of Film and New Media at Tokyo University of the Arts. Creates works focused on ideas generated with his students in his research laboratory. Created and oversaw “Pythagora Switch”, an educational television programme first broadcast on NHK in 2002. Now, it has become a perennial children’s favourite, will new episodes still being made and broadcasted. He is active in the development of new games, and in the research of on neuroscience and the nature of expression. He has also written novels and picture books.', '', '', '', '2010-05-11 08:23:00', 62, '2010-05-11 08:23:08', 62, 1),
(322, '1', 1, 'Masumi', 'Uchino', '', 'Born in Kanagawa. Created and oversaw “Pythagora Switch”, an educational television programme first broadcast on NHK in 2002, where she was responsible for the design of the penguins and the mouse and all the other creatures that appeared on the show. Her songs for children’s programmes – for which she writes both the lyrics and the compositions – are also the beloved theme tunes of countless childhoods.', '', '', '', '2010-05-11 08:23:50', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
