(72, 14, 'Solve all the Puzzles!', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|8|2|10|11|14|', '', 'Another title in the popular series features a spot-the-differences quiz, a maze, a sentence-making game, a puzzle using different shapes and various other challenges.', '', '', '', '', '1999-05-01 00:00:00', '28 x 19', '24', 1, 'tggb_solveallthepuzzles_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:12:03', 62, 1),
(73, 14, 'Getting it Right!', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|8|2|10|11|14|', '', 'Count the different coloured flowers, take a walk with your fingers, match the flower shapes, compare the cakes and find seats for the pixies. These and other picture games are included.', '', '', '', '', '1999-07-01 00:00:00', '29 x 19', '24', 1, 'tggb_gettingitright_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:12:30', 62, 1),
(74, 43, 'Beware of Miss Tomato', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', '"Aren''t I cute?" If you don''t praise Miss Tomato she will cry. No need to worry. She soon stops. Miss Tomato always wants to talk about herself, or to tell others what to do. "I can sing. You sing too! Sing louder." So, beware of Miss Tomato. ', '', '', '', '', '2000-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_bewaremisstomato_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(75, 43, 'Beware of Master Frog', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Master Frog boasts that he is famous and strong. He makes fun of his friends by saying that "6" is "9". Then he sticks his tongue out and goes away. So, beware of Master Frog, and beware that you don''t become like him!', '', '', '', '', '2000-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_bewaremasterfrog_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(76, 43, 'Beware of Master Television', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', '"Yellow crayons are made from eggs, and red crayons from tomatoes. That''s the truth." Taro Gomi''s imaginative approach continues with a warning not to be like the malicious Master Television with his tall stories and bad jokes.', '', '', '', '', '2000-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_bewaremastertv_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(77, 0, 'Someone''s There', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|2|10|', '', 'What is that white eye in the green tree? It''s a bird. What is that white eye in the black barn? It''s a horse. What is that white eye in the brown tree? It''s a squirrel. A small dog reacts with wonder to the various discoveries that it makes.', '', '', '', '', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_someonesthere_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-03-11 17:07:59', 62, 1),
(78, 0, 'Let''s Play', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|10|', '', 'A little pink bird lands on a giraffe''s head. "Let''s play," it says. But the giraffe won''t. When the bird pursues it, the giraffe hides first behind some trees, then behind an elephant, and then in the water. Finally, the bird gives up, and flies off, saying "Let''s play tomorrow." ', '', '', '', '', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_letsplay_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-03-11 17:07:08', 62, 1),
(79, 0, 'Who Lives Here?', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Who lives in the big blue house in the red field? First a rabbit comes out, then a crocodile, then a hen. A family of humans returns to the house, followed by the rabbit. But then an alien-looking creature flies out of a hole in the roof. It seems to be full of music and laughing voices. Let''s visit it.', '', '', '', '', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '32', 1, 'tg_wholiveshere_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(80, 0, 'Are You All Right, Little Mouse?', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|10|', '', 'Life is dangerous for the mouse. He gets knocked over by a swinging gorilla, then crushed under a snake. He also has a collision with a horse, is stepped on by a bird and knocks his head against the wall. Father comes along to save the day.', '', '', '', '', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_areyouallrightlmouse_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-03-11 17:07:32', 62, 1),
(81, 0, 'Sing, Little Bird', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|2|10|', '', 'The little bird''s song makes everyone feel good - the flowers burst into bloom, the sleepy brothers perk up, the fighting piglets suddenly become friends and the rabbits begin to dance. Perhaps the little bird will come to your window too.', '', '', '', '', '2001-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_singlittlebird_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(82, 0, 'Get out of the Way, Snake!', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|2|10|', '', 'He doesn''t mean to, but the blue snake is always getting in the way. He disturbs the little girl. He lies along the bench, down the slide and across the swings. What a nuisance he is! But then it rains. The snake makes an umbrella for the girl and is finally helpful.', '', '', '', '', '2003-03-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_getoutofwaysnake_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(83, 0, 'I Told You So', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|2|11|', '', 'A horse and his foal are trotting along the road. Whenever the father sees something dangerous, he shouts out to his child to be careful! But the little horse doesn''t always listenÉA very funny picture book about a parent/child relationship.', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '20 x 19', '24', 1, 'tg_itoldyouso_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-03-11 17:07:45', 62, 1),
(84, 0, 'Welcome to the Great Wondership', 15, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|18|2|11|', '', 'A great ship appears in the distance. Lets go! So we jump into a helicopter and fly to the Great Wondership, where all sorts of treats await. A library, a botanic garden, a zoo, a children''s room, a town and even a mountain we see on our grand tour, until finally we come to the sea. *Big book edition also available. (Size: 52_42 cm)', '', '', '', '', '2007-10-01 00:00:00', '17 x 14', '34', 1, '212110great_wondership.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-09-05 05:03:31', 62, 1),
(85, 0, 'The Bremen Town Musicians', 16, 1, 58, 5, '', 206, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'A long awaited, reprinted edition of the Grimm brothers'' folk tale. A group of old and unwanted animals - a donkey, dog, cat and rooster - head to Bremen to become musicians. They find a house of thieves, scare them, and take over the house, before deciding to stay there and live together happily as musicians.', '', '', '', '', '1967-11-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, 'brementownmusicians_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(86, 0, 'Mah-Kun in the Wilderness: The Trial', 18, 1, 0, 0, '', 247, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'In the second exciting volume detailing his adventures, Mah-Kun is besotted with the fallen angel Takizawa, who has transformed him into a child of power. Further, more dangerous trials lie ahead for Mah-Kun, however, and he cannot relax for a moment. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-02-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '194', 2, 'mitwthetrial_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(87, 0, 'Mah-Kun in the Wilderness: The Ordeal', 18, 1, 0, 0, '', 247, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'The visitor who appears unexpectedly at Mah-Kun''s house has the demure appearance of an angel, but she drops a bombshell that signals the end of Mah-Kun''s carefree elementary schools student days, and the start of his ordeal, in the first of two exciting adventure books for teens. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-03-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '226', 2, 'mitwtheordeal_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(88, 22, 'Claw of the Sun', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 241, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'A tale of the rise and fall of a magnificent ancient kingdom in Central Asia. Many vigorously individual young characters appear in the story, which describes the war waged by a powerful hungry king against the tribe of the Red Mountain.', 'Award', '1985 THE SANKEI AWARD FOR CHILDREN''S BOOKS & PUBLICATIONS', '', '', '1984-12-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '340', 2, 'yt_clawofthesun_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(89, 22, 'Birth of the Fire King', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 241, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'After the young Kaguuto becomes king, his dominating mother Dagirin holds political power. In contrast, the old chief priest Igisu and his attendant Horoshi, the future king, though unrelated, are like wise father and son.', '', '', '', '', '1986-03-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '340', 2, 'yt_birthofthefireking_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(90, 22, 'Legend of the Far Water', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 241, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'This novel depicts the continuing fortunes of the kingdom of Yurun in a period when the capital city is threatened by drought and the heir to the throne kidnapped by a religious sect of transvestite warriors.', '', '', '', '', '1987-03-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '340', 2, 'yt_legendofthefarwater_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(91, 22, 'Wind over the Plains', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 241, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'Tagutai, son of the tribe''s chief, falls in love with Hinguri. But in the battle which the Yurun wage against their oppressors, the Chirugido, fate leads the two lovers adrift.', 'Award', '1989 AKAITORI AWARD', '', '', '1988-11-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '340', 2, 'yt_windovertheplains_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(92, 22, 'Priestess of the Moon', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 241, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'This book covers the earliest period yet in the history of the Yurun tribe of Central Asia. A number of stories are interwoven in a complex pattern, among them the tale of how the tribe gained iron. Ingredients in this heroic adventure include wars, the death of a king and human sacrifice.', '', '', '', '', '1991-05-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '340', 2, 'yt_priestessofthemoon_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(93, 0, 'Kias The Priestess', 19, 1, 0, 0, '', 226, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '', '', 'Unaware of the secret of her own birth, Kias, a trainee priestess, sets out to discover the origin of the empire''s troubles and to break the curse.', 'Award', '1998 THE SANKEI AWARD FOR CHILDREN''S BOOKS & PUBLICATIONS', '', '', '1997-01-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '680', 2, 'kiasthepriestess_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(94, 0, 'The Tears of the Dragon', 20, 1, 0, 0, '', 178, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|13|7|', '', 'A story inspired by a Chinese legend. The bravery and friendship of a strange boy soften the heart of a violent and much-feared dragon. Hirosuke Hamada''s tale of trust is sensitively illustrated by Chirhiro Iwasaki.', '', '', '', '', '1965-11-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '33', 1, 'jpb_tearsofthedragon_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(95, 0, 'The Red Ogre Wept', 20, 1, 0, 0, '', 176, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'A lonesome red ogre lived in a mountain. He wanted very much to associate with the villagers. Seeing a blue ogre, one of his friends thought of an idea: the blue ogre would pretend to be wicked and threaten the villagers, then the red one would come to chase the blue one away.', '', '', '', '', '1965-12-01 00:00:00', '29 x 21', '32', 1, 'jpb_redogrewept_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(96, 29, 'The Kingfisher''s Babies', 21, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 266, 0, 4, 5, '|10|', '', 'Small animals living in nature are the stars of these photographic field guids which contain colour photographs.', '', '', '', '', '1992-02-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '23-27', 5, 'thekingfishersbabies_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(601, 39, 'Vol.2 - Rhododendron Butterflies Flying in the Woods', 135, 12, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Rhododendrons, the beautiful butterflies often found in woods, used to be a familiar sight to Japanese people, but now numbers are decreasing year on year. What has happened to them?', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '40', 5, 'insectsnenvironment2_b.jpg', '2008-12-24 14:37:22', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(98, 0, 'Little Bear''s Forest', 22, 1, 0, 0, '', 172, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'A little bear that runs away from the danger posed by human beings, is adopted by a mother bear and her baby. This book vividly illustrates the importance of sustaining the integrity of natural habitats, through the life of a small bear.', '', '', '', '', '2005-07-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, 'littlebearsforest_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(99, 0, 'The Desperate Vitality of Animals', 23, 1, 0, 0, '', 229, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '', '', 'Animals are living desparate lives. We have much to learn from them. A picture book containing fantastic illustrations depicting the charm and mystery of animals.', '', '', '', '', '1995-03-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '32', 1, 'hs_desperatevitalityofani_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(100, 0, 'Tetsubin Story', 24, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 272, 0, 3, 9, '', '', 'On 17 January 1995, a massive earthquake struck Kobe. An old woman who owns ''Tetsubin'', a small restaurant, tells of the city''s reconstruction during the last 10 years. An insightful photo picture book.', 'Award', '2005 THE SANKEI AWARD FOR CHILDREN''S BOOKS & PUBLICATIONS', '', '', '2004-12-01 00:00:00', '27 x 23', '56', 5, 'tetsubinstory_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1);
INSERT INTO `jos_publications_titles_2011-08-26` (`id`, `series_id`, `title`, `author_id`, `author_type`, `author2_id`, `author2_type`, `author_ext`, `illustrator_id`, `illustrator2_id`, `photographer_id`, `photographer2_id`, `cat_id`, `age_group_id`, `country_id`, `country_ext`, `synopsis`, `sub1_title`, `sub1_text`, `sub2_title`, `sub2_text`, `publication_year`, `book_size`, `pages`, `book_colour`, `imageurl`, `created`, `created_by`, `modified`, `modified_by`, `published`) VALUES
(101, 0, 'Eugene Smith The Walk to Paradise Garden', 24, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 275, 0, 3, 11, '', '', '"My life is devoted to recording human existence as it really is", says photojournalist Eugene Smith. He has produced many memorable works, including ''Footsteps to Paradise'', depicting young people looking towards the future, and ''Minamata'', which sent shockwaves around the world with its portrayal of people fighting Minamata disease. The photographs assembled in this volume showcase his love of Japan and Minamata.', '', '', '', '', '2006-02-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '160', 7, 'eugenesmithtwtpg_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(102, 0, 'Whale Fishing', 25, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 9, '|0|', '', 'The Japanese people have been eating whales for more than 5,000 years. A photographer ventured out on the Antarctic Ocean with a fleet of whalers from December 1982 until the following February. His dynamic photographs show the process of finding, pursuing, shooting, and dismembering gigantic whales. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-07-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '64', 5, 'whalefishing_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-02 07:23:21', 62, 1),
(103, 0, 'The Old Fisherman who Smelt of Water', 26, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 9, '', '', 'Photographer Imamori meets Sangoro, an old fisherman who smells of water, on the west shore of Lake Biwa in Japan. He fishes with traditional tools for his wife and himself, sharing his catch with herons and kites. At the end of this beautiful journey, Imamori discovers what Sangoro''s smell reminds him of.', 'Award', '2007 Shogakukan Cultural Prize in Publishing For Children''s Books', '', '', '2006-04-01 00:00:00', '27 x 23', '64', 5, 'theoldfishermanwsow_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(104, 41, 'Insects of the World -  A Journey to Encounter Wonderful Lives', 26, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 12, '', '', 'Imamori, a photographer, has liked insects since childhood, and always longed for tropical jungles. He has travelled all over the world and taken photographs of insects for 30 years. This photo gallery is a precious record of his passion -  including very rare scenes that have not been seen in several decades, and his secret stories behind the photo shooting session. ', '', '', '', '', '2007-10-01 00:00:00', '25 x 20', '40', 5, '082008Insects_of_the_world_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(105, 29, 'Konkon the Little Fox', 27, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 5, '|10|', '', 'Small animals living in nature are the stars of these photographic field guids which contain colour photographs.', '', '', '', '', '1990-11-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '23-27', 5, 'konkonthelittlefox_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(106, 0, 'I''ve Run Away From Home!', 28, 1, 0, 0, '', 242, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|10|', '', 'A boy gets angry when his younger brother knocks down the castle which he was building, and runs away from home. Actually, he gets no further than the front garden. But there he sits down under a tree, determined never to return. The rest of the story shows how his brother, mother and father gently persuade him to change his mind.', '', '', '', '', '1996-08-01 00:00:00', '22 x 28', '32', 1, 'iverunawayfromhome_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-09-14 15:35:49', 62, 1),
(107, 36, 'Red Foxes', 96, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '2006-02-01 00:00:00', '28 x 23', '40', 5, 'redfox_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-09-14 15:36:38', 62, 1),
(108, 0, 'Little Violet', 29, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '|8|', '', 'Little Violet likes her name - but would prefer Florence. When her little sister is born, what name will Daddy give her, and why? Will Mummy still hug her? She continues to ponder life''s mysteries and discovers that being an elder sister is not all that bad.', '', '', '', '', '2005-12-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '138', 1, 'littleviolet_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-23 20:39:26', 62, 1),
(109, 0, 'The Tengu''s Noodle Bar', 30, 1, 0, 0, '', 253, 0, 0, 0, 2, 10, '', '', 'The Tengu, a long-nosed goblin, loves noodles so much that he has opened an authentic, handmade-noodle shop. However, nobody turns up, even at lunch time. Then, this rather unusual shop gets a number of odd helpers to attract more customersÉ', '', '', '', '', '2005-05-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '120', 2, 'tengusnoodlebar_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(110, 0, 'I''m an African Giraffe', 31, 1, 0, 0, '', 235, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '|22|8|10|25|11|', '', 'A lonely giraffe in Africa writes a letter, which it asks a pelican to take to someone living "on the other side of the horizon". Presently the pelican brings a reply from a penguin. In the correspondence that follows the giraffe and the penguin discuss their differences and try to imagine what it would feel like to be the other.', '', '', '', '', '2001-06-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '102', 2, 'iamafricangiraffe_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-23 20:35:02', 62, 1),
(111, 0, 'The Whale that Lived at Cape Whale', 31, 1, 0, 0, '', 235, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '|8|11|', '', 'A retired whale teacher living alone writes lots of letters. One day the pelican postman brings a reply from a penguin that was once his pupil. One thing leads to another, and the whale and his friends decide to revive the Olympic Games of Cape Whale! ', '', '', '', '', '2003-04-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '102', 2, 'twtlivedatcapewhale_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-23 20:35:24', 62, 1),
(112, 0, 'How are You, Fur Seal?', 31, 1, 0, 0, '', 235, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '|8|10|', '', 'This is a tale of adventure and perseverance as Little Seal becomes a fully-fledged sea messenger, delivering letters between Fur Seal and little Whale. Fur seal has important news to be delivered, but on his first task alone, Little Seal gets lost! Will he and the letters find their way safely home? ', '', '', '', '', '2005-12-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '104', 2, 'howareyoufurseal_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-23 20:35:47', 62, 1),
(113, 0, 'Golden Elephant', 32, 1, 0, 0, '', 186, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '|10|', '', 'Six short stories that depict life as seen through the eyes of an adolescent girl, who is unsure of her self, her family and friends, but gradually comes to gain confidence. Episodes deal with a visit to her grandmother in hospital, a student friend from a difficult home background and an aborted runaway.', '', '', '', '', '2001-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '182', 2, 'goldenelephant_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(114, 0, 'That Warmth Never Fades', 32, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 12, '|10|', '', 'Nami obeys her mother''s wishes and goes to a cram school and softball practice after school. However, her everyday life changes when she agrees to take a lonely old lady''s dog out for a walk. Nami meets a boy upstairs from the lady''s house, and their bond beyond time and space helps them understand their emotional autonomyÉ', '', '', '', '', '2007-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '286', 4, '112007thatwarmthnever_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:12:15', 62, 1),
(115, 0, 'Dumpling Soup', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 174, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|8|10|11|13|', '', 'An old man who feels lost and lonely after the death of his wife rediscovers the joy of living by trying to remember how she made a favourite soup. As his cooking skills improve, animal and human friends appear and the joy returns his home.', '', '', '', '', '1997-11-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '32', 1, '052008_dumpling_soup_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:48:31', 62, 1),
(116, 0, 'Captain Ship and Itto, the Dolphin', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 219, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Captain Ship knows everything about the sea. No matter what he is asked to do, he will do it, so he tends to take on too much. I wonder what he''ll be asked to do nextÉ', '', '', '', '', '2004-08-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '72', 1, 'scaithedolphin_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(117, 0, 'Captain Ship and Yuki, the Snowman', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 219, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Busy Ship Captain faces his hardest task yet: to take a smart snowman Yuki, from the northernmost country to the southernmost country as a gift to a little girl. On his way, the sun gets hotter and the snowman melts. Ship Captain will need all his resourcefulness to fulfil his task and not disappoint the little girl.', '', '', '', '', '2005-11-01 00:00:00', '20 x 16', '72', 1, 'scaythesnowman_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-11-24 13:20:05', 62, 1),
(118, 0, 'Captain Ship and the Sea Monster', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 219, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Captain Ship never says no when he is given work on the sea. One day, while his ship Cha-cha is grumpy, a gigantic sea monster appears, asking to be taken to the sky. He is too big for the ship but the Captain is never supposed to say noÉ This is the third volume of ''Captain Ship'' series.', '', '', '', '', '2007-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 16', '72', 1, '112007scndaseamonster_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(119, 0, 'Tadpole NO.101', 34, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|21|8|10|', '', 'A tadpole No.101 went astray. Her mother sought, sought and sought for her child. Just as she found her, a crawfish saw her too and began to chase after her. Then another enemy joined in the pursuit, which resulted in a fight between the two hunters. The mother fainted while the two were fighting. Tadpole No.101, confronted with this situation... One of the author''s favorite ways of telling a warm-hearted tale to children.', '', '', '', '', '1973-07-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '32', 1, 'tadpoleno101_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-24 15:34:19', 62, 1),
(120, 0, 'Mr. Crow''s Bakery', 34, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|21|8|10|11|', '', 'There was once a bakery shop by a crow at a corner of the Black -Letter Crossroads in Izumigamori. One day the baker, asked by children for bread, baked trays of wonderful and amusing bread to delight them. The children were so pleased with this, that they gathered in front of the shop before down. Adults also rushed to the shop, resulting in a tumult in front of the bakery. ', '', '', '', '', '1973-09-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '32', 1, 'mrcrowsbakery_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 23:37:57', 62, 1),
(121, 0, 'The Red Shoes', 36, 2, 0, 0, 'based on an original story by H.C.Andersen', 178, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|7|13|', '', 'The strange, sad fate of a girl who wore a pair of red dancing shoes to church. A beautiful picture book. Chihiro Iwasaki''s light and lyrical illustrations are at one with the dreamlike world of Andersen''s Story.', '', '', '', '', '1968-08-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '35', 1, 'ci_redshoes_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 12:48:40', 62, 1),
(122, 0, 'I Can Put on My Pants by Myself', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 211, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|11|10|8|', '', 'A little boy could not put on his underpants by himself. When he lifted one leg he lost his balance and fell down. So he went out without any clothes on. But how the animals laughed at this strange creature! It made him run home and finally learn how.', '', '', '', '', '1970-12-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '32', 1, 'icanputonmypantsbymyself_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(123, 0, 'Barba the Duck Goes to Town', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 252, 0, 0, 0, 2, 6, '', '', 'Long-selling series first published in 1974 and now in its 85th printing. The author creates a character whose virtues will be immediately recognisable to all young children.', 'Award', '1975 THE SANKEI AWARD FOR CHILDREN''S BOOKS & PUBLICATIONS', '', '', '1974-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'btheduckgoestotown_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(124, 0, 'Barba''s Balloons', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 252, 0, 0, 0, 2, 6, '', '', 'When Barba hears that her friend Usako the rabbit is in hospital, she begins thinking of ways to cheer her up. First she makes a delicious cherry pie, then she picks some flowers, and, lastly, she buys a bunch of colourful balloons.', '', '', '', '', '1975-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'bsballoons_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(125, 0, 'Barba and the Missing Hat', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 252, 0, 0, 0, 2, 6, '', '', 'Barba the duck offers to look after the hen''s chicks and the mouse''s children while their mothers go shopping. Together they have a splendid time, planting seeds, playing hide ''n'' seek and sailing on the pond.', '', '', '', '', '1978-05-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'bandmissinghat_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(126, 0, 'Barba''s Guest', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 252, 0, 0, 0, 2, 6, '', '', 'One day Barba gets a call. ''I''ve got something good. Can I come and show you?'' Wondering who it can be, Barba decides to do some quick shopping. Little does she know that she will encounter her guest on the way.', '', '', '', '', '1980-01-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'bsguest_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(127, 0, 'The Rat''s Sumo', 36, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'The contestants in this match of sumo--traditional Japanese wrestling--are two rats. When the lone spectator, a poor old man, sees how one-sided a contest it is, he decides with the help of his wife to try and even things up.', '', '', '', '', '1983-07-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '31', 1, 'jpb_ratssumo_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(128, 38, 'Vol.1 -  Solar Energy / Finds Solution to Solar Energy and Fuel Problems', 37, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'An informative look at our world''s natural resources. From practical tips for conducting simple experiments using solar power, to diagrams illustrating the benefits of sustainable energy, this book suits the inquisitive child.', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '48', 5, 'lult_vol1solarenergy_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(129, 38, 'Vol.2 -  Bio-technology / Saving Mankind from Starvations', 37, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'From familiar methods such as fermentation and food improvement to cell fusion and genetic recombination, both of which have wide-reaching effects on technology and industry. A simple introduction.', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '48', 5, 'lult_vol2biotechnology_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(130, 38, 'Vol.3 -  Ubiquitous / The Evolvement of a Network Society', 37, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'We are now living in an age where network terminals are part of everyday life. They have now become ubiquitous. This is an introduction to the information society of the near future.', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '48', 5, 'lult_vol3ubiquitous_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(131, 38, 'Vol.4 -  Nano-technology / One billionth of a Metre is Changing the Future', 37, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'There is little difference between highly advanced technology and magic'' ealing with matter on a molecular level. Simple explanation of nano-technology, the ''magic of the future''.', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '48', 5, 'lult_vol4nanotechnology_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(132, 38, 'Vol.5 -  Humanoid / Making the Movie World Real', 37, 3, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'An insight into artificial intelligence and robots. Using colourful graphics, photographs and cartons, this book shows the history of mankind''s desire to create humanoids and raises the question "how long before our dream robot appears?"', '', '', '', '', '2004-03-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '48', 5, 'lult_vol5humanoid_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(133, 0, 'Tobimaru the Flying Dragon', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 191, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'One day in late summer Satoko, who is alone at home, discovers a strange animal in the kitchen. Tobimaru the dragon has come to the humans'' world to search for the ''Autumn Sun.'' With Satoko acting as a guide, they embark on a fantasy journey through time and space.', '', '', '', '', '1988-06-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '143', 2, 'nk_tobimaruflyingdragon_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(134, 0, 'Great Aunt''s Mysterious Recipes', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 191, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'Mina has little skill for cookery and sewing. But then she discovers a book of her great aunt''s containing cooking recipes and instructions for making things. When she puts the information to practical use, Mina finds herself transported to a strange and fantastic world.', '', '', '', '', '1993-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '188', 2, 'nk_greatauntsmr_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(135, 0, 'The Dodo''s Little Helper', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 191, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'A dodo escapes from a collector and appears in the home of a boy called Taka. What does the bird want? And why is it so proud and haughty? It turns out that the dodo is searching for his bride-to-be, and needs someone to help him find her. ', '', '', '', '', '1997-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '206', 2, 'nk_dodoslittlehelper_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(136, 15, 'Vol.1- Greedy Mrs. Bear', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 134, 0, 0, 0, 2, 5, '', '', 'Today''s babysitter is called Mrs. Bear. She loves sweets, and hates piano practice. She proves to be lots of fun and plays many games with Kako, as they make an eventful trip to the supermarket.', '', '', '', '', '2005-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '31', 1, 'pcagreedymrsbear_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(137, 15, 'Vol.2- Cry-Baby Mrs. Goat', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 134, 0, 0, 0, 2, 5, '', '', 'Today''s babysitter is Mrs. Goat, who can''t help crying when others do. She bursts into tears when unable to find Kako during a game of hide and seek. When they go to a restaurant, she is again affected by other people''s emotions.', '', '', '', '', '2005-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '31', 1, 'pcacrybabymrsgoat_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(138, 15, 'Vol.3- Slowcoach Mrs. Tortoise', 38, 1, 0, 0, '', 134, 0, 0, 0, 2, 5, '', '', 'Mrs. Tortoise and Kako go to the barber''s shop, leaving in plenty of time because Mrs. Tortoise cannot walk very quickly. They try to take a shortcut and end up in the sea. They have discovered the prawn and crab barber''s shop!', '', '', '', '', '2005-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '31', 1, 'pcaslowcoachmrstortoise_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(139, 0, 'The Red Balloon', 39, 2, 0, 0, 'based on an original story by Ramolis', 178, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'A pictorial representation of the much loved superb French film, ''The Red Balloon''. A beautiful portrayal of a deep friendship between a young boy and a red balloon which is able to understand human words.', '', '', '', '', '1968-12-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '35', 1, 'ci_redballoon_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(140, 7, 'Let Us Have a Swing, Too, Nontan', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|2|10|11|', '', 'Nontan monopolizes a swing and refuses to let his friends have a turn. Angry, his friends decide to go home and leave him behind. Then Nontan tells them they can have a ride, after he counts to ten.', '', '', '', '', '1976-08-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpletushaveswing_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:38:06', 62, 1),
(141, 7, 'Good Night, Nontan', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|2|10|11|', '', 'Nontan has trouble sleeping at night. He wants to play with his friends but they are all sound asleep - except for the little owl. So Nontan and the owl play all night long. ', '', '', '', '', '1976-08-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpgoodnight_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:07:36', 62, 1),
(142, 7, 'Nontan the Naughty Cat', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|2|10|11|', '', 'Nontan scares his friends by walking around and making faces. He also makes a face at the sun, but the sun in turn makes a face at him. Still, Nontan enjoys making faces so much that he cannot stop!', '', '', '', '', '1976-10-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpnaughtycat_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 12:53:45', 62, 1),
(143, 7, 'Nontan Loves to Swim', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'While swimming at the beach, Nontan and his friends, meet a lost baby turtle. They all try to find its mother. ''Have you seen Baby Turtle''s mother?'' they ask. But everyone they meet says no.', '', '', '', '', '1977-08-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlplovestoswim_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:27:08', 62, 1),
(144, 7, 'Nontan Blows Bubble Gum', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Nontan decides to blow the biggest bubble of all and puts a large piece of gum in his mouth. But he mistakenly swallows the gum. His stomach starts to blow up like a balloon and he gets so fat he floats up into the sky.', '', '', '', '', '1977-12-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpblowsbubblegum_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:42:46', 62, 1),
(145, 7, 'Nontan Wets the Bed', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|11|', '', 'When Nontan wakes up in the morning, his bed is soaking wet. Nontan and his friends, the rabbit, the bear, the raccoon and the pig, have all wet their beds. And when they put their mattresses out to dry, it begins to rainÉ', '', '', '', '', '1978-04-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpwetsthebed_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:06:40', 62, 1),
(146, 7, 'Nontan, Santa Claus!', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'The sky is full of many different flying Santa Clauses. Nontan wants to ask Santa the cat for a present but can''t find him.', '', '', '', '', '1978-11-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpsantaclaus_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:43:10', 62, 1),
(147, 7, 'Nontan and the Frothy Soapsuds', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Nontan got dirty playing outside. But he refuses to take a bath, saying that he doesn''t like to get wet. His friends jump in and start playing hide-and-seek with soap bubbles. Nontan watches them for a while, and thenÉ', '', '', '', '', '1980-01-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpfrothyprothysoap_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:05:48', 62, 1),
(148, 7, 'Nontan''s Birthday', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Nontan''s friends will not play with him. They shut the door and will not let him come in. What can they be up to? Nontan is very upset but there''s a nice surprise in store for him - a birthday party!', '', '', '', '', '1980-12-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpbirthday_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:44:16', 62, 1),
(149, 7, 'Nontan the Bouncing Ball', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'When Nontan''s red ball bounces off, nobody can catch it. It seems to gather speed as it bounces on the rabbit''s bottoms, into the balloon tree, down the mousehole and finally into Mr.Owl''s nest.', '', '', '', '', '1982-09-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpthebouncingball_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:41:20', 62, 1),
(150, 7, 'Nontan''s Paper Pranks', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Nontan has great fun scattering wastepaper and rubbish all over the place until his friends come and tell him off. A simple tale with a mild little message for infants growing up and having to get used to being neat.', '', '', '', '', '1986-08-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlppaperpranks_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:12:34', 62, 1),
(151, 3, 'Nontan Smiling', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|', '', 'Nontan smiles, grins, wonders, screeches, boohoos, sniffles, fumes, snarls, tee-hees, beams, yawns and, finally, goes to sleep. Delightful first picture book for very small children.', '', '', '', '', '1987-08-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbsmiling_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(152, 3, 'Nontan Munching', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|11|', '', 'Nontan is munching something. What is it? It''s a delicious banana. Rabbit is munching something. What is it? A carrot! Meanwhile, Piglet is eating an apple and Master Bear an orange.', '', '', '', '', '1987-08-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbmunching_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(153, 3, 'Nontan Tinkling', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|11|', '', 'Tinkle, tinkle... It''s Piglet doing a wee-wee. Tinkle, Tinkle... This time it''s Raccoon. The Rabbits are doing wee-wees too. Here''s Nontan. Oh dear! He''s weeing on the floor! Quickly, the potty! That''s better. Well done, Tinkle, tinkle... It''s Piglet doing a wee-wee. Tinkle, Tinkle... This time it''s Raccoon. The Rabbits are doing wee-wees too. Here''s Nontan. Oh dear! He''s weeing on the floor! Quickly, the potty! That''s better. Well done, Nontan!', '', '', '', '', '1987-08-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbtinkling_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(154, 7, 'Nontan''s Tickly Time', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|2|10|', '', 'When Nontan, asleep in the field, is woken up by the tickle of the grass, it gives him an idea for some mischief. So off he goes to tickle the pig. Then off they go to tickle all their friends!', '', '', '', '', '1987-11-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpticklytime_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:32:38', 62, 1),
(155, 7, 'Nontan''s Birthday Book', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'This little book, built around the story of a runaway egg, will make a nice birthday present for any small child. There are blanks to fill in with personal details, pictures, handprint, ets., and also tiny adhesive pictures to stick on.', '', '', '', '', '1987-12-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpbirthdaybook_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:11:19', 62, 1),
(156, 3, 'Nontan, Peekaboo!', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|11|', '', 'Nontan puts his hands over his face. Then suddenly, ''Peekaboo!'' Master Bear hides under his hat. ''Peekaboo!'' Now the Rabbit Brothers. ''Peekaboo!'' And Raccoon and Piglet. Now everyone altogether. ''Peekaboo!''', '', '', '', '', '1988-04-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbpeekaboo_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(157, 3, 'Nontan Brum-brum', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|', '', 'Nontan''s red car goes brum-brum through Master Bear''s legs, around the Rabbits, bounces over Piglet, zigzags, wobbles, careers all over the shop, hits Raccoon... Lots of fun and new words for baby readers.', '', '', '', '', '1988-06-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbbrum-brum_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(158, 3, 'What Shall We Play, Nontan?', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|11|', '', 'Even though his usual friends don''t appear in this book, Nontan still finds plenty to do - reading, digging in the sand, sitting in a cardboard box boat, playing ball, swinging on the swing, and banging the pots and pans.', '', '', '', '', '1988-09-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbwhatshallweplay_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(159, 3, 'Nontan Cleans His Teeth', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|11|', '', 'Here Nontan and his friends - the Rabbits, Raccoon, Piglet and Bear - show what fun you can have brushing your teeth.', '', '', '', '', '1989-10-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbcleanshisteeth_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(160, 3, 'Good Morning Nontan', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|', '', 'Nontan wakes up and says, ''Good morning.'' So do all his friends. Then they eat breakfast. ''Delicious!'' While playing, Nontan and Piglet bump into each other. ''Sorry.'' Simple manners for very young children.', '', '', '', '', '1989-11-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbgoodmorning_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(161, 3, 'Nontan, Atchoo!', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|10|', '', 'When he begins coughing and sneezing, Nontan consults Dr. Bear. Poor Nontan hates being ill. But kind Dr. Bear soon has him chuckling, and, after taking his medicine, Nontan is well again in no time.', '', '', '', '', '1989-12-01 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, 'nontanfbatchoo_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(162, 0, 'In Santa''s Land...', 35, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|8|2|10|11|', '', 'Everyone knows what Santa Claus does on Christmas Eve. But what about the rest of the year? In Santa''s land there is a whole population of Santa Clauses busily making presents, searching out the world for good children, training their reindeers and maintaining their sleighs.', '', '', '', '', '1990-11-01 00:00:00', '21 x 27', '31', 1, 'kk_insantasland_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-28 14:04:24', 62, 1),
(163, 7, 'Nontan and The Ghost Town Maze', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'If you follow the ghost of the bamboo and paper umbrella through the maze, the ghost will become friends with everyone and you''ll no longer be afraid of getting up in the night or sleeping in a dark room!', '', '', '', '', '1991-02-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpmazeofghosttown_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:14:14', 62, 1),
(164, 7, 'Nontan''s Hiccups', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Nontan and his friends get the hiccups and try all the ways they know to get rid of them - pinching their noses, holding their breath, drinking water, doing a handstand... Everything fails until a little frog comes along.', '', '', '', '', '1996-07-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlphiccups_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:13:58', 62, 1),
(165, 13, 'Nontan''s Guitar', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|', '', 'Nontan plays the guitar in a band with Piglet, Bear, Raccoon and the Rabbits. When his fellow members complain of his raucous rhythms, Nontan gets upset. His subsequent adventure takes him into a tunnel and an encounter with a horde of creepy-crawlies.', '', '', '', '', '1997-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'nontanilyguitar_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(166, 13, 'Be Brave, Nontan!', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|', '', 'Nontan has to go to the hospital after falling off a swing and cutting his ear. At first he is scared when the doctor says that he has to have an injection. But, with the encouragement of his friends, he overcomes his fears and soon gets better.', '', '', '', '', '1998-06-01 00:00:00', '22 x 18', '32', 1, 'nontanilybebrave_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(167, 7, 'Nontan''s Little Sister', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Nontan and his younger sister Tartan come to play with Piglet. But Nontan gets angry when Tartan begins throwing bricks around and tells her to go away. Later, he really regrets what he said. How happy he is when she finally reappears!', '', '', '', '', '2001-06-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlplittlesister_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-24 15:25:38', 62, 1),
(168, 0, 'Nontan & Tartan''s Picture Playbook', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|', '', 'Aimed at pre-schoolers, some sections of this book offer early learning experiences in subjects like writing and arithmetic, while other pages are devoted to puzzles and games. With three printings in its first six months, this volume is another winner.', '', '', '', '', '2003-04-01 00:00:00', '28 x 23', '64', 1, 'nontanotpictureplaybook_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(169, 7, 'Nontan Says Go Away Pain', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Tartan, the cat, Nontan''s younger sister, falls over and cries a lot. However, Nontan tells the pain to go away! I wonder where it''s gone!', '', '', '', '', '2004-02-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpgoawaypain_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:13:22', 62, 1),
(170, 0, 'Nontan A.B.C', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|', '', 'A fun ABC picture book packed with lively illustrations. An introduction to English pronunciation and opposites. A small, hardback ''Nontan'' board book.', '', '', '', '', '2004-09-01 00:00:00', '13 x 14', '16', 1, 'nontanotabc_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(171, 0, 'Nontan 1.2.3', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|', '', 'There''s one cake with a strawberry on top, two happy rainbows and three Santa Clauses eating sandwichesÉ This is a small, hardback book full of lively illustrations to help children learn to count with the much beloved Nontan and his friends.It comes with some fun addition sums to try. ', '', '', '', '', '2004-09-01 00:00:00', '13 x 14', '16', 1, 'nontanot123_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:43:46', 62, 1),
(172, 16, 'At the Dentist', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Maa does not like going to the dentist, but one day, the Pain Monster, who can eat up people''s pain, emerges from a picture book. He soon becomes close friends with Maa, and shows him that a trip to the dentist is nothing to be afraid of.', '', '', '', '', '2005-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '78', 1, 'tpmatthedentist_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(173, 16, 'Let''s Save the Egg!', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Another exciting tale featuring Maa and his faithful friend, the Pain Monster. Adventure ensues when they attempt to retrieve a stolen Pain Monster egg from a colony of turtles in a far away island. Once again the Pain Monster saves the day. ', '', '', '', '', '2005-07-01 00:00:00', '23 x 16', '78', 1, 'tpmletssavetheeggs_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(175, 16, 'Beating the Nebababa', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Maa''s friend Koro is a pain monster who can gobble up pain. One day, Koro appears with a little water sprite, whose father and friends have been kidnapped by the Nebababa, who eats the ''crybaby sticky stuff'' that appears when water sprite kids cry. Can Maa and Koro save them?', '', '', '', '', '2006-03-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '78', 1, 'tpmbeatingthenebaneba_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(176, 7, 'Nontan''s Massive Thank You', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Nontan and friends are drawing on the ground, but his little sister Tartan ruins his masterpiece, and Nontan angrily goes to the top of the hill to finish his artwork on his own. Tartan follows him and steps on his drawings again, but she has actually come to tell him something surprising...', '', '', '', '', '2006-06-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '32', 1, 'nontanlpmassivethankyou_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:13:08', 62, 1),
(177, 7, 'Nontan Fun Book', 40, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'This long awaited latest title of Nontan Let''s Play series contains counting, finding, colouring, drawing, singing, tongue twisters, maze and lots of other fun games! Introduced by the popular Nontan and his friends, children can play in this imaginative world on their own or together with friends.', '', '', '', '', '2008-07-01 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '72', 1, '082008nontan_fun_book_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:12:51', 62, 1),
(178, 0, 'Can a Whale Drown?', 41, 1, 0, 0, '', 46, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '|8|11|14|', '', 'Answers to 41 interesting animal questions. In addition to the title, here are some of the other riddles: Why is a rhinoceros''s horn on its nose? Do animals have belly buttons? Do giraffes really sleep standing up? Don''t animals sweat? A zoologist who worked at Tokyo two biggest zoos provides the answers with the aid of cartoon illustrations.', '', '', '', '', '2003-07-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '174', 2, 'canawhaledrown_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2011-02-23 20:19:22', 62, 1),
(179, 1, 'Therefore I am a Little Piggy by Yoko Kitayama', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'This is the first in the series of the Little Piggy stories. Little Piggy introduces himself and his parents; in the bath or playing with a friend, naked or wearing pyjamas, behind a mask or under a hat, until he grows up, he will always be Little Piglet! ', '', '', '', '', '1987-10-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_thereforeiamlp_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(180, 1, 'What are Your Favourite Things, Little Piggy?', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Little Piglet shows us his favourite things. They are apples and mandarins, bananas, melons and grapes... and he has outfits to match their colours: pants, wellies, t-shirt, hat and apron; but his favourite thing is a peach - can you guess why? It''s the colour of his own skin!', '', '', '', '', '1987-10-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_whatryourfavouritethings_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(181, 1, 'Little Piggy Images', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Little Piglet is a very proud little pig. He has images of little pigs everywhere: on his clock, his towel, his spoon, his mug, his toothbrush and toothpaste, his comb and shampoo, his chair, his favourite toys and his pillow - even on his house so it''s easy to recognise. Teaches babies about their surroundings.', '', '', '', '', '1987-10-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_littlepiggyimages_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(182, 1, 'Little Piggy and His Friends', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Little Piglet has many good friends: he goes for walks with Puppy, sings with Baby Bird, has afternoon tea and cake with Baby Bear, brushes his teeth with baby Rabbit and plays with Kitty. When it''s time for their afternoon nap, they all snuggle up together.', '', '', '', '', '1987-10-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_littlepiggynhisfriends_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(183, 1, 'Little Piggy Has No Hair', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Little Piglet has a pretty ribbon but no hair! Where could it go? On his ear or nose? Over his eyes? Around his wrist, ankle or waist? No, so Little Piglet finds three hairs on his head and makes a bow. Teaches the names of the parts of the body.', '', '', '', '', '1988-06-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_littlepiggyhasnohair_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(184, 1, 'How Much Can You Eat Little Piggy!', 42, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Little Piglet has a healthy appetite: he loves sweet potatoes, green peppers, fried eggs, tomatoes and fish; and whatever he eats, his mum eats twice as much and his dad eats four times as much! That is why they are a fat, healthy and happy family.', '', '', '', '', '1988-06-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, 'lp_howmuchcanueat_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(185, 2, 'Hello!', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Pi the bird, Mike the cat, Koro the dog and Mr.Monster all come to Yu-chan''s house, knock on the door and say ''Hello!'' Big double-page illustrations, in which the animals really bow as they give their greetings.', '', '', '', '', '1988-12-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'hello_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(186, 2, 'Peekaboo!', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'The large striking pictures in the books of this series are ideal for the very young. Here the animals and Yu-chan play peekaboo. Also available in sturdy ''Board Book'' form', '', '', '', '', '1988-12-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'peekaboo_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(187, 2, 'Yum-yum', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Here the double-page illustrations are cleverly contrived to make the animals pick up the food from their plates and begin to eat it. Also available in sturdy ''Board Book'' form', '', '', '', '', '1988-12-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'yum-yum_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(188, 2, 'Poo-poo', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'When doing poo-poo on the potty, each of the animals has its own style. Pi does a little poo, while Mr.Monster does an enormous one. Also available in sturdy ''Board Book'' form', '', '', '', '', '1989-11-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'poo-poo_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(189, 2, 'Moving Dolls', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|11|', '', 'Characters introduced in the first four books of the series reappear as a push-out movable card figures simply assembled with sticking tape.', '', '', '', '', '1991-11-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'movingdolls_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:38:35', 62, 1),
(190, 2, 'Let Me Hear You', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Pi is reading a book, Koro is drawing a picture and Mike is playing with a toy car. But they all give a loud and clear reply when mother calls them to come for snacks! This book provides lots of potential for interaction and game play. Also available in sturdy ''Board Book'' form', '', '', '', '', '1992-04-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'letmehearyou_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(191, 2, 'Night-night', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'In this very simple story, Yu-chan and her friends say ''Night-night", and then, quite literally, close their eyes and pull up the bed covers.', '', '', '', '', '1993-11-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'night-night_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(192, 8, 'Playing with Daddy', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'The elephant and other animals are playing with their children. The elephant makes a swing with his trunk and the gorilla uses his strong arms to lift baby onto his shoulders.', '', '', '', '', '1995-04-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '32', 1, 'pb_playingwithdaddy_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:46:41', 62, 1),
(193, 8, 'What Are You Doing?', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'When the rabbit, bear, elephant and other animals are asked what they are doing they turn round and give their answers. The rabbit is making an origami paper model, the bear is crying and the elephant is talking with the mouse. Simple, but effective playbook for the very young.', '', '', '', '', '1995-04-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '32', 1, 'pb_whatrudoing_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 16:05:17', 62, 1),
(194, 2, 'Shampoo', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Cleverly designed book in which the animals and Mr. Monster all wash themselves Japanese-style sitting on a small bath stool. Yu-chan shampoos her hair, rubbing in the suds, rinsing and then drying her hair with a towel.', '', '', '', '', '1996-04-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'shampoo_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(195, 2, 'Cleaning Teeth', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|', '', 'After eating, Yu-chan cleans her teeth, so do Koro, Mike and Pi. What is Mr. Monster doing? He''s sucking a lollipop! Be sure to clean your teeth afterwards, Mr. Monster!', '', '', '', '', '1998-03-01 00:00:00', '15 x 17', '26', 1, 'cleaningteeth_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(196, 8, 'Let''s Go to the Park', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'A baby hippo goes to the park with his mother and watches the other animals play: the piglets are on the seesaw, baby bear is in the sand pit and the raccoons are going down the slide. When the little hippo plucks up enough courage to have a go on the swing he is soon enjoying himself.', '', '', '', '', '1999-06-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '32', 1, 'pb_letsgo5thepark_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:13:07', 62, 1),
(197, 2, 'Getting Dressed', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|', '', 'Koro, Mike and Mr. Monster are having problems putting on their clothes. So, Yu-chan demonstrates how to do it properly. These pages show how she takes off her coat, shirt and trousers, and smartly puts on her pajamas.', '', '', '', '', '2001-01-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '28', 1, 'gettingdressed_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(198, 8, 'Brush Your Teeth!', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 123, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '', '', 'The bear, rabbit and mouse enjoy a sandwich, noodles and rice, followed by desserts. Now it''s time for them to clean their teeth. Fun learning book for the very young with pop-up pictures.', '', '', '', '', '2003-08-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '29', 1, 'pb_brushurteeth_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(199, 8, 'Ok, Smile!', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 123, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '', '', 'The bear, rabbit and mouse enjoy a sandwich, noodles and rice, followed by desserts. Now it''s time for them to clean their teeth. Fun learning book for the very young with pop-up pictures.', '', '', '', '', '2004-11-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '29', 1, 'pb_oksmile_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 13:11:38', 62, 1),
(200, 8, 'A Trip Out', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 123, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|0|', '', 'On the way back from a trip to the department store neither the mouse''s mummy or daddy will carry him or give him a piggyback. What''s he going to do?', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '21 x 17', '29', 1, 'pb_tripout_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:49:09', 62, 1),
(201, 2, 'Tickling Games', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '|8|10|', '', 'Yu-chan has great fun in this book, as she tickles her friends Pi the bird, Mike the cat, Koro the dog and Mr. Monster. Then she gets a taste of her own medicine as they decide to tickle her! Lift-up flaps reveal how everyone reacts to being tickled.', '', '', '', '', '2006-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '26', 1, 'tickling_games_big.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(202, 0, 'The Christmas Song Book 1', 44, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '', '', 'Christmas songs in English and Japanese with accompanying music and colour illustrations. Includes favorites such as "Joy to the World", "O Little Town of Bethlehem", "Silent Night", "We Wish You a Merry Christmas", "Santa Claus is Comin'' to Town" and "Winter Wonderland".', '', '', '', '', '1999-10-01 00:00:00', '31 x 23', '40', 1, 'nk_christmassongbook1_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(203, 0, 'The Christmas Song Book 2', 44, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '', '', 'More carols and traditional songs with Christmas flavour. Contains "Good King Wenceslas", "God Rest You Merry Gentlemen", "We Three Kings Orient Are", "Rudolph the Red Nose Reindeer", "Little Drummer Boy", "Go Tell it on the Mountain", "White Christmas" and "Auld Lang Syne".', '', '', '', '', '1999-10-01 00:00:00', '31 x 23', '40', 1, 'nk_christmassongbook2_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(204, 0, 'The Story of Saint Madeleine Sophie Barat', 44, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '', '', 'A beautifully produced book with small colour illustrations and a simple story relating events in the life of French nun Madeleine Sophie Barat (1779-1865), who traveled around post Revolution France building convents and opening schools.', '', '', '', '', '2001-04-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '56', 1, 'nk_storyofstmsb_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(205, 0, 'The Alphabet Picture Book', 44, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 11, '', '', 'A graphic artist who was raised in the United States and went to college there products a highly diverse selection of 441 subjects in this attractive picture dictionary that young readers will surely read for enjoyment rather than study. To give you an idea of the imaginative diversity, the "P" section includes a pig, a potato, a pillow and a prayer.', '', '', '', '', '2003-10-01 00:00:00', '27 x 22', '61', 1, 'nk_alphabetpicturebook_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(206, 0, 'Singing Shijimi Clam', 44, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|13|', '', 'An old witch brings home some shijimi clams to make miso soup. Her hungry cat is waiting eagerly. She is about to toss the clams into the boiling broth, when wait! She realizes that the clams are fast asleep. A delicately illustrated tale of friendship, ingenuity, and kindness.', 'Award', 'Bank Street College of Education Best Children''s Books of the Year (in U.S) ', '', '', '2005-04-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 2, 'nk_singingshijimiclam_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1);
INSERT INTO `jos_publications_titles_2011-08-26` (`id`, `series_id`, `title`, `author_id`, `author_type`, `author2_id`, `author2_type`, `author_ext`, `illustrator_id`, `illustrator2_id`, `photographer_id`, `photographer2_id`, `cat_id`, `age_group_id`, `country_id`, `country_ext`, `synopsis`, `sub1_title`, `sub1_text`, `sub2_title`, `sub2_text`, `publication_year`, `book_size`, `pages`, `book_colour`, `imageurl`, `created`, `created_by`, `modified`, `modified_by`, `published`) VALUES
(207, 0, 'The Little Move', 45, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Four people and a dog live in a beautiful little house. They begin to feel that they are growing up rapidly, but in fact their house is shrinking! When the door becomes too small for father to get through, he decides to build a new house, and the little house becomes smaller than a doll''s house...', '', '', '', '', '2006-10-01 00:00:00', '21 x 26', '32', 1, 'littlemove_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(208, 0, 'Do Bears Say "Bear"?', 46, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'Are the stripes of a tiger horizontal or vertical? Why is an elephant''s neck so short? This is an educational and informative insight into nature as a whole, packed with interesting information from an expert animal fieldworker, accompanied by illustrations and graphs.', '', '', '', '', '2005-02-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '174', 2, 'dobearssaybear_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-12-10 22:34:08', 62, 1),
(209, 0, 'A Fun Book on Animals For Fieldworkers', 46, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'This indispensable reference book presents a wealth of fascinating facts about the animal kingdom, in a fun and exciting way. Discover the truth about seeds, scientific names and evolution, with interesting episodes such as why giraffes have long necks, why rabbits eat their own poo and more!', '', '', '', '', '2006-02-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '262', 2, 'afunbookonaff_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(210, 30, 'Wild Fruits and Friends', 48, 7, 134, 8, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '|8|', '', 'This picture book combines a cute story about animals searching for food with botanical notes and detailed instructions on how to make toys, decorations, jam, pancakes and jellies from the collected nuts and berries.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '1996-09-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '36', 1, 'wildfruitsandfriends_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:27:55', 62, 1),
(211, 30, 'Berries and Friends', 48, 7, 134, 8, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '|0|8|', '', 'Subtitled ''find them, eat them, grow them'', this second book uses a story about a girl and her animal friends to impart information about wild and cultivated strawberries, raspberries, etc. The book includes a variety of recipes for using the berries.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '1997-06-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '36', 1, 'berriesandfriends_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-12-10 22:48:57', 62, 1),
(212, 30, 'Seaside Friends', 48, 7, 134, 8, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '|8|10|', '', 'The first time that the little forest girl went to the seaside, she came into contact with many sea creatures. Simply looking at these beautiful pictures will make you feel as if you are really by the sea! A refreshing new picture book. ', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '1999-07-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '36', 1, 'seasidefroiends_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:39:24', 62, 1),
(213, 30, 'Making Friends with Mushrooms', 48, 7, 134, 8, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '|8|', '', 'The story is interspersed with pictures and details of the different types of mushrooms, arranged in sections: pine and beech forest, mixed woodland and grassland. There is also a section on poisonous fungi to beware of, and cooking hints.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2001-10-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '36', 1, 'makinfriendswithm_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:03:00', 62, 1),
(214, 30, 'Flowers and Friends', 48, 7, 134, 8, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '|8|10|', '', 'A pictorial introduction to flowers. It includes flowers'' names and distinguishing features, cooking, flower games and pressed flowers. Full of flower features.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2004-01-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '36', 1, 'flowersandfriends_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:05:38', 62, 1),
(215, 11, 'The Crane''s Reward', 49, 2, 0, 0, '', 178, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|13|', '', 'A brilliantly illustrated old Japanese tale of a crane whose life is saved by a man for whom she then weaves a beautiful cloth, using her own feathers.', '', '', '', '', '1966-10-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '33', 1, 'jpb_cranesreward_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 14:34:59', 62, 1),
(216, 11, 'The Fisherman Who Went to the Bottom of the Sea', 49, 2, 0, 0, '', 178, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'Miyoko Matsutani retells the famous traditional story of the fisherman who is taken to an undersea palace by a grateful turtle whose life he has saved. Chihiro Iwasaki''s illustrations make a fresh and charming setting for this folk tale.', '', '', '', '', '1967-07-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '33', 1, 'jpb_fishermanwent2dac_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(217, 0, 'Letters to Anne Frank', 49, 1, 0, 0, '', 154, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '|19|17|', '', 'One summer, Fumiko gives her teenage daughter a copy of Anne Frank''s Diary. For Fumiko, this diary is a painful remainder of the war. Each begins to keep a diary, addressed to Anne, recording disturbing signs of the present day.', 'Award', '1980 JAPANESE ASSOCIATION OF WRITERS FOR CHILDREN PRIZE', '', '', '1979-12-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '253', 2, 'letterstaf_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 17:03:24', 62, 1),
(218, 0, 'Secrets in the Attic', 49, 1, 0, 0, '', 154, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '|8|11|', '', 'After their Grandpa''s death, Eriko and Yuko come to his summer cottage to try and solve the riddle of his will. The secret they uncover appals them --- Grandpa was a member of the notorious 731 Unit which carried out medical experiments on prisoners of war. His unexpiated sins now pass to then.', '', '', '', '', '1988-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '208', 2, 'secretsita_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(219, 0, 'Chanting for Warmth', 51, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'On a bitterly cold day, Tomo-chan is making her way home with her shopping when she meets an owl who teaches her a chant to keep her warm, which goes ''pokka-poka-ha!'' She teaches the chant to the many other animals she meets, and soon everyone is nice and toasty in this heartwarming tale.', '', '', '', '', '2006-12-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '072007chantingforwarmth_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(220, 40, '7. Observing Familiar Trees <1>', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'Another volume in the popular series which combines botanical detail with a sense of poetry. The approach of the authors is summed up in a note on the cover sleeve: "Look closely and at any time of the year a tree will show you its beauty. Try it. You will find that trees make wonderful friends."', '', '', '', '', '1989-06-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_07observingfamiliar_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(221, 40, '8. Observing Familiar Trees <2>', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'From the bud to the flower and fruit to the seed; a year in the life of the fruit of our most popular trees. An encyclopaedic guide for nature lovers written from a fresh perspective.', '', '', '', '', '1989-06-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_08observingfamiliar_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(222, 40, '1. Trees that Flower in Spring', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'The trees and shrubs featured in this new series can be seen in most city streets and parks. Each entry includes between six and ten illusrations showing how a bud develops into a flower and how this then develops into a seed-bearing fruit. A detailed index gives added information.', '', '', '', '', '1990-04-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_01treesthatflower_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(223, 40, '2. Trees that Flower in Summer, Autumn & Winter', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'This second volume dealing with later flowering trees and shrubs contains 18 species ranging form gardenia to loquat. The fine illustrations aim both to give botanical detail and to show the beauty and wonder of the flowers'' formation.', '', '', '', '', '1990-04-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_02treesthatflower_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(224, 40, '3. Park and Garden Trees', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'Trees commonly found in parks and gardens are the focus of this third volume. Species include the oleaster, Kerria, winged spindle tree, deutzia and japanese privet.', '', '', '', '', '1992-05-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_03parkngardentrees_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(225, 40, '4. Roadside Trees', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'The trees and shrubs introduced in the fourth volume of this popular series, which combines artistic excellence with precise botanical facts, include spirea, dogwood, honeysuckle and horse-chestnut. At the back of the book there is an index to the whole series.', '', '', '', '', '1993-07-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_04roadsidetrees_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(226, 40, '5. Trees to See on a Walk', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'The fifth volume of the series covers more popular trees and shrubs. Among them are species like daphne and magnolia, which are loved for their beautiful or fragrant flowers, as well as fruit -- producing species like blueberry and prune.', '', '', '', '', '1994-03-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_05trees2conawalk_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(227, 40, '6. Familiar Trees through the Year', 52, 1, 0, 0, '', 222, 0, 0, 0, 4, 14, '', '', 'Platan, Japanese laurel, lilac, paper mulberry, staff tree, fig, ivy and cotton rose are among the 18 trees and shrubs included in the last volume of this best-selling series. ', '', '', '', '', '1997-05-01 00:00:00', '28 x 24', '40', 5, 'ifatf_06familiartreesthroughdayear_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(228, 34, 'Eating Death', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'Animals don''t waste death. Death is consumed by the stomach and transformed into the life of another living thing. Through observing death, you become aware of the importance of eating well and life itself.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2002-02-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '36', 5, 'eatingdeath_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(229, 34, 'Eating Garbage', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'In the natural world nothing is wasted - garbage becomes food for animals, birds and insects whose own dead bodies will eventually provide nourishment for other living things.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2002-03-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '36', 5, 'eatinggarbage_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(230, 34, 'Animals and the City', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'Animals that are making their nests and looking for roosting places in cities and residential areas are rapidly intruding on the lives of humans. We should consider the new relationship which exists between animals and people. ', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2002-03-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '36', 5, 'animalsandthecity_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(231, 34, 'Scent Map', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'Rats living in big cities, and animals converging on rubbish bins. Sensitive to the smell of peoples'' daily lives, the animal ''scent map'' makes us think about environmental problems.', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2002-03-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '36', 5, 'scentmap_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(232, 34, 'Light Nights', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'For human beings, the most useful lights are able to light up the living spaces of animals. Seeing their shapes in the bright evening light makes you think about problems of environmental pollution. ', 'Award', '2002 PUBLICATION AWARD FOR SCHOOL LIBRARY', '', '', '2002-03-01 00:00:00', '23 x 23', '36', 5, 'lightnights_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(233, 33, '1. Animal Tracks', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'Animals have their own routes through the forest, just as we have regular routes to school or work. Japanese antelope and monkeys walk on ridges, squirrels and raccoon dogs run over fallen trees, and rabbits and martens jump over the mountain streams. The animals'' tracks give clues to their communities and activities.', '', '', '', '', '2006-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 23', '40', 5, 'fapjanimaltracks_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 14:14:58', 62, 1),
(234, 33, '2. The Water Hole', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'The author, finding a small watering hole in the forest, guessed that it was an important place for forest animals to get water, and he was right. His robotic camera captures wild birds bathing, a monkey family in the summer, and squirrels drinking water after gathering nuts and seeds.', '', '', '', '', '2006-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 23', '40', 5, 'fapjthewaterhole_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 14:15:17', 62, 1),
(235, 45, 'The Moon Bear', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 12, '', '', 'Photographer Miyazaki was shocked to discover that moon bears, which used to be hardly ever seen, have begun appearing in human settlements without fear, and no longer fear the noise of huge lorries. Miyazaki decided to record the ecology of moon bears to alert humans to changes in nature caused by our behaviour. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-10-01 00:00:00', '20 x 15', '161', 5, 'moonbear_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-11-17 14:19:09', 62, 1),
(236, 45, 'The Persimmon Tree', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 12, '', '', 'There is an 80-year-old persimmon tree on the hill. As the seasons go by, it sees a fox in the snow, a meteor in the clear sky, and a stray cat chasing a field mouse. No one cares about its deliciously ripe fruit anymore. While other trees have been sold and made into golf clubs, and its owner has moved to the city, it alone still stands.', '', '', '', '', '2006-10-01 00:00:00', '20 x 15', '80', 5, 'persimmontree_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2008-11-17 14:18:59', 62, 1),
(237, 33, '3. The Nests of Eagles and Hawks', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'The author travels all over Japan seeking out the nests of raptorial birds; eagles, hawks and owls. He finds there are four types of location where they choose to build their nests depending on their activity style, dietary habits and how they raise their young: namely rocky outcrops, on trees, in tree holes and on moorland.', '', '', '', '', '2007-03-01 00:00:00', '29 x 23', '40', 5, '072007fapnestfalconine_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 14:15:33', 62, 1),
(238, 33, '4. Japan''s Sub-Tropical Forests', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'From the Southernmost point of Japan''s Kagoshima to the furthest Southwesterly of the Okinawa Islands lies an area of bounteous sub-tropical forest. A photographer specializing in wildlife, Miyazaki has gathered together here a spectacular collection of shots from this unexplored region. His subjects include eagles, bats, rare trees, crabs, snakes and spiders, many of which are unique to the area.', '', '', '', '', '2007-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 23', '40', 5, '112007subtropicalforests.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 14:15:55', 62, 1),
(239, 33, '5. The Mountains Where Bears Live', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Since 2000, there has been a dramatic increase in the number of black bears coming down from the mountains into Japanese villages. Realising that we know very little about them, Miyazaki set up a fixed observation camera in the mountains where these bears live. His discoveries, recorded in this book, will fascinate and delight.', '', '', '', '', '2008-05-01 00:00:00', '29 x 23', '40', 5, '052008the_mountains_where_bears_live_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-05-15 14:16:10', 62, 1),
(240, 0, 'The Restaurant of Many Orders', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 227, 0, 0, 0, 1, 11, '', '', 'After going into a restaurant in the depths of the mountains the two hungry hunters pass from one door to the next. When notices tell the customers to ''take off your shoes'' and ''cover your body with salt'' the men finally realize what a horrible situation they are in.', 'Award', '1989 INTERNATIONAL BOOK DESIGN EXHIBITION AT LEIPZIG (Silver Medal)', '', '', '1984-06-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '36', 1, 'km_restaurantofmanyorders_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(241, 0, 'Gorsh the Cellist', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 158, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'The story of how Gorsh, the worst player in the Venus Orchestra, becomes the best. Like many of Kenji''s heroes, Gorsh is an outsider, a lonely character, but with an appealing combination of stubornness and naivety.', '', '', '', '', '1989-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '48', 1, 'km_gorshdacellist_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(242, 0, 'The Cat''s Office', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 1, 8, '|8|', '', 'A cat working as an office clerk is persecuted because he has sooty fur. The petty attitudes and poses of the cat''s colleagues caricature human society, and make us feel the stupidity and illogicality of discrimination.', '', '', '', '', '1994-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '36', 1, 'kk_catsoffice_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2010-12-08 22:43:58', 62, 1),
(243, 0, 'Notebook', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 1, 14, '', '', 'This sister volume to Kuroi''s earlier work ''Sign of Clouds'' contains more landscape pictures of poet Kenji Miyazawa''s beloved Iwate countryside, as well as sketches from the artist''s notebook, letters written to friends and more of Miyazawa''s evocative poems.', '', '', '', '', '1997-10-01 00:00:00', '22 x 31', '40', 1, 'kk_notebook_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(244, 0, 'Night Train to the Stars', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 232, 0, 0, 0, 1, 12, '|10|', '', 'A lonely schoolboy makes a dream-like journey through the night sky on a magic train. Illustrator transforms the human characters into cats. This book contains both an earlier and late version of the story, neither of which were published until after the author''s death.', '', '', '', '', '2000-11-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '102', 1, 'km_nighttrain2dastars_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(245, 0, 'The Wild Goose Child', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 154, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'An old man tells the legend of a heavenly being, `The Wild Goose Child'' who in ancient times came down from the sky with a message. An Exceptionally beautiful tale with a spiritual message.', '', '', '', '', '2004-09-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '36', 1, 'km_wildgoosechild_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(246, 0, 'Matasaburo, the Wind Imp', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 232, 0, 0, 0, 1, 12, '', '', 'When the mysterious boy Saburo transfers to a rural school, pupils wonder if he is an wind imp, as whenever he appears, the wind always blows. Then, when they become good friends, he leaves on the windÉ This is a new edition of time favourite classic piece illustrated with elaborate oil-paintings. ', '', '', '', '', '2007-09-01 00:00:00', '26 x 29', '88', 1, '112007matasaburowindimp_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(247, 0, 'The Fur of the Glacial Mouse', 54, 1, 0, 0, '', 188, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'It happens in an express train to Bering. A passenger, who is proud of his luxurious fur coats, especially the one made of only the fur from the necks of glacial mice, is attacked by a group of strange bear-like men! A story that raises a question about the human ego in a surreal and poetic way. ', '', '', '', '', '2008-02-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '36', 1, 'hyoga-nezumi-no-kegawa_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(248, 0, 'Go on! Don''t Give up Slug!', 55, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'From all appearances, there is a shell; it''s a slug and a snail. However, how about if we trace the slug''s ancestors? A poem with a unique viewpoint of a slug. ', '', '', '', '', '2004-11-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, 'goondontgiveupslug_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(249, 0, 'The Warty Toad', 55, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', '"Toads are so disgusting! They are different from frogs." "Toads can''t jump as much as frogs can. They are useless animals." The warty toad is always being teased. This is a book that praises a toad who tries to live his life steadfastly despite being taunted. ', '', '', '', '', '2005-10-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, 'wartytoad_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(250, 0, 'It''s Fish, It''s Fish!', 55, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|', '', 'The children at the kindergarten are wondering what they will cook for lunch - when their teacher brings in an enormous fish. They carry it, bake it, eat it and dance with the bones. The words can be sung to a number of jaunty tunes, bringing the children''s lunch to life in a musical way. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, 'itsfishitsfish_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(251, 0, 'The Little Bear''s Walk', 56, 1, 0, 0, '', 183, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'The little bear who delivers a lunch to his father doesn''t have much experience. In the middle of the trees with tainted autumnal leaves a strange world is in existence. ', '', '', '', '', '2004-09-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, 'littlebearswalk_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(252, 0, 'Waiting', 56, 1, 0, 0, '', 246, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', '''I''ll be back soon,'' says the rabbit to the pig, and goes home. The bear and the fox visit the rabbit, and they start dancing and cooking. The pig waits for the rabbit, watching ants and listening to trees. The sun begins to set, but the rabbit does not appear.', '', '', '', '', '2006-08-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, 'waiting_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(253, 0, 'What Happened to the Crocodile?', 57, 1, 97, 4, '', 218, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Gapa the African crocodile is longing for his baby to arrive, but when his egg hatches, it turns out not to be a crocodile but a bird chick. For some reason, however, Gapa cannot help loving the chick. While everybody is making fun of him, Gapa brings up his ''son'' to become a mature bird.', '', '', '', '', '2007-02-01 00:00:00', '22 x 28', '32', 1, '072007whatHappenedtothecrocodile_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(254, 0, 'Dear Friend', 59, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 14, '', '', 'Collection of black-and-white photographs from all over the world showing children living with resilience in conditions of deprivation and hardship. Locations include a refugee camp in EI Salvador, war-torn Afghanistan, the slums of Guatemala, a Philippine garbage dump and the villages of South Africa.', '', '', '', '', '1998-08-01 00:00:00', '19 x 17', '119', 7, 'dearfriend_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(255, 0, 'Children of Kosovo', 59, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 14, '', '', 'Photo-journalist Hiromi Nagakura made two trips to Kosovo after the devastating war with Serbia. This collection of photographs focuses on one extended family and, in particular, a 7-year-old boy and his younger sister. It records the shock of returning to the family''s ruined home, and follows the slow rebirth of hope.', '', '', '', '', '2000-09-01 00:00:00', '19 x 20', '95', 8, 'childrenofkosovo_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(256, 0, 'My Homeland Afghanistan', 59, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 14, '', '', 'Nagakura has been visiting Afghanistan for 20 years. Most of the pictures come from the northern part of the country, where armed conflict, first against the Soviet Union and then against the Taliban, became a part of everyday life. Despite the difficulty, he gained hope and inspiration from the shining faces of the youngsters.', '', '', '', '', '2002-04-01 00:00:00', '19 x 20', '83', 5, 'myhomelandafganistan_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(257, 0, 'Xhavit and his Family Build a House', 59, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 14, '', '', 'Taken during the reconstruction of Kosovo, this collection of photographs features the real lives of 10 families living simple yet difficult lives. A lively collection of 58 black and white photographs, it follows the trials and tribulations of Xhavit and his wife as they watch their children growing up, and await the arrival of a new member of the family.', 'Award', '2005 KODANSHA CULTURE PRIZE FOR CHILDREN''S PICTURE BOOK PUBLICATION', '', '', '2004-04-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '64', 7, 'xhavitandhfbah_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(258, 0, 'Afghanistan: Children of a Mountain School', 59, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 9, '', '', 'Photojournalist Hiromi Nagakura visits a small school in a mountain valley in Afghanistan just after its post war reopening. Although the school is draughty and the children must share textbooks, their faces shine with eagerness in the classroom, and they smile in the playground. ', '', '', '', '', '2006-08-01 00:00:00', '27 x 23', '64', 5, 'afganistanchildrenoams_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(259, 0, 'A Day in the Life of a Ghost', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|11|', '', 'Shinta Cho had an enormous reputation in Japan as a picture-book artist. In this story a ghost on a hill goes shopping, entertains his friend, reads and practices baseball. Unpretentious, undemanding, totally appealing.', '', '', '', '', '1986-06-01 00:00:00', '29 x 21', '32', 1, 'sc_adayinthelifeofaghost_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-11-01 13:49:26', 62, 1),
(260, 0, 'Umi''s Window', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 162, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'A little girl named Umi looks out of her apartment window and see an airplane. ''Hey airplane!'' she calls out. ''What can I do for you?'' the airplane answers. Together the girl and the airplane set out to visit a variety of fantastic countries.', '', '', '', '', '1997-06-01 00:00:00', '22 x 28', '32', 1, 'sc_umiswindow_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(261, 0, 'Hat', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 3, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'A blue hat slinks along. Underneath it is a crocodile. A red hat hops along. Underneath it is a rabbit. A white hat slides along. Underneath it is a snake. A green hat floats on the pond. Underneath it is a duck. All the animals love their hats. An ideal first book for babies.', '', '', '', '', '2000-02-01 00:00:00', '17 x 17', '24', 1, 'ra_hat_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(262, 0, 'Ri-ng !', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 3, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Ri-ng! It''s the doorbell. Kitten answers the door. A cat delivers a neatly wrapped parasol. Ri-ng! Puppy answers the door. A delivery man gives him a football. This time, a bag for Miss Pelican. Ri-ng! Finally all the little animals go outside to show off and play with their new things.', '', '', '', '', '2000-02-01 00:00:00', '17 x 17', '24', 1, 'ra_ring_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(263, 0, 'Nursery Rhymes 2', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 197, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '', '', 'A pleasure to listen to, and a delight to look at, this volume contains 15 slightly longer songs. As it includes lots of soothing and rhythmic tones, it is sure to bring a smile to baby''s face and help them drift off to sleep.', '', '', '', '', '2005-01-01 00:00:00', '18 x 18', '32', 1, 'nurseryrhymes2_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(264, 0, 'Nursery Rhymes 1', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 249, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '', '', 'A song based book, ideal for introducing vocabulary and rhythm, this first volume contains 15 short songs for babies, which are great for reading out loud. Each song is accompanied by colourful and vibrant illustrations.', '', '', '', '', '2005-01-01 00:00:00', '18 x 18', '32', 1, 'nurseryrhymes1_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(265, 0, 'Tales of the Old Tree Stump', 62, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'The old tree stump was once a tall tree covered in beautiful green leaves that provided shade from the sun and shelter from the rain. That is, before it was cut down. What use is it now? The old stump feels very sad. But, then two rabbits, three squirrels, a hedgehog and a wedding party of mice make the stump happy again.', '', '', '', '', '2003-10-01 00:00:00', '18 x 18', '24', 1, 'oldtreestump_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(266, 0, 'The Old Tree Stump''s Friend', 62, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'Spring is a sad time for the old tree stump, which at this time of the year used to have birds and their babies nesting in its branches. Now its only companion is a dandelion that regards the old stump as an ugly eyesore. This story for the very young describes how the two become friends.', '', '', '', '', '2003-10-01 00:00:00', '18 x 18', '24', 1, 'oldtreestumpfriend_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(267, 0, 'The Old Tree Stump''s Birthday', 62, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|', '', 'It''s the old tree stump''s birthay, but it can''t remember its age. A succession of animals, beginning with an ant and ending up with a bear, come along and help to count the year rings on the top of the stump. It turns out that the stump is 93 years old. Happy birthday!', '', '', '', '', '2003-10-01 00:00:00', '18 x 18', '24', 1, 'oldtreestumpbirtsday_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
