(609, 0, 'When Murray and Mo Met', 285, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Murray, a rabbit who is always in a hurry, moves next door to Mo, a very slow mole. Murray rushes to join Mo at the river where Mo is waiting patiently to catch a fish. But Murray is too impatient to wait! How will the two friends work together to make a delicious dinner?  ', '', '', '', '', '2008-11-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '331620sassatomota.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:05:03', 62, '2009-02-26 14:17:40', 62, 1),
(602, 39, 'Vol.3 - Cicadas Settled in the City', 135, 12, 148, 12, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Cicadas, and in particular Kuma Cicadas from Fukuoka and Minmin Cicadas from Tokyo, are for some reason increasing in numbers. Two photographers try to discover why.', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '40', 1, 'insectsnenvironment3_b.jpg', '2008-12-24 14:39:46', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(558, 0, 'A House of 100 Stories', 151, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|10|11|', '', 'Tochi, a boy who likes watching stars, receives a letter from someone living at the top of a 100-storey house. While walking up the stairs, Tochi meets a variety of creatures living in the building. Turning the book sideways and reading up vertically, it is fun to follow the scenes happening in each storey. ', '', '', '', '', '2008-05-01 00:00:00', '22 x 31', '32', 1, '082008a_house_of_100_stories_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:17:14', 62, 1),
(604, 39, 'Vol.5 - Black Hornets Living in the Village', 149, 12, 135, 11, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Black Hornets have always been a tasty snack for people in the village. This volume shows many aspects of their lives, such as how the workers collect food, bring up their larvae and much more.', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '40', 5, 'insectsnenvironment5_b.jpg', '2008-12-24 14:42:10', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(608, 0, 'Lion and Me', 284, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|', '', 'Lion and I are best friends. We do everything together. One day, I invited Lion to my house. But Daddy was angry at his dirty paws and Mummy was angry at his messy mane. So Lion washed his paws, combed his mane and tried to be neat and polite. But I only like the Lion I know! ', '', '', '', '', '2008-11-01 00:00:00', '29 x 21', '32', 1, '331610riontoboku.jpg', '2009-01-30 16:59:43', 62, '2010-03-11 17:08:15', 62, 1),
(560, 0, 'Cham the Tadpole', 152, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Cham the tadpole is looking forward to growing up. When he sees a beautiful shiny fish, he yearns to become a fish. But when he grows legs, he yearns to become a fluffy waterfowl. Then when he grows arms, he yearns to become a great turtle with a big shell. But Cham is disappointed when he starts to lose his tailÉ', '', '', '', '', '2008-06-01 00:00:00', '25 x19', '32', 1, '082008cham_the_tadpole_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(561, 0, 'A Summer Holiday in the Beach House', 153, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'On the first day of a summer holiday, a girl visits her cousin at his family''s beach house. They pick beautiful shells, catch small fish and crabs, swim in the sea and play with a ball. But she soon realises she has lost her hat full of shellsÉ All sorts of fun in a nostalgic Japanese beach house is depicted in this lively book.', '', '', '', '', '2008-06-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '082008summer_holiday_in_the_beach_house_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(562, 0, ' The Tale of Grandma', 154, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Ine, a nine-year-old girl, has a grandma who is a great cook. One day, when a samurai visits and asks for a meal, Ine comes to know the secret of grandma''s delicious meals by chance. A story about the origin of grains, based on real writings from ancient Japanese documents.', '', '', '', '', '2008-06-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '082008the_tale_of_grandma_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(563, 42, 'Vol.1- A Study Room of the Age of Dinosaurs', 155, 1, 0, 0, '', 259, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Find dinosaurs in a toy corner in a department store, in an old film, in a laboratory, in a museum, and in your dream! While playing the ''Finding Dino'' games, you can solve questions with dinosaur expert Dr. Ren -  What is a dinosaur? When did they exist? What kinds of dinosaurs were there? And how can we find their fossils?', '', '', '', '', '2008-07-01 00:00:00', '24 x 31', '36', 5, '082008finding_dino_1_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(564, 42, 'Vol.2- A Study Room of the Company of Dinosaurs', 155, 1, 0, 0, '', 259, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'In this second title of the ''Finding Dino!'' series, we investigate the different species of dinosaurs. We look at their names, their appearance, how they lived, which dinosaurs related to which, where and when they lived, the differences between the Triceratops and the Stegosaurus and so onÉ Dr. Ren invites you to the fascinating world of many different kinds of dinosaurs!', '', '', '', '', '2008-07-01 00:00:00', '24 x 31', '36', 5, '082008finding_dino_2_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(565, 42, 'Vol.3- A Study Room of the Data of Dinosaurs', 155, 1, 0, 0, '', 259, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'In the third title of the series, we look deeper into the data of dinosaurs. What was the biggest/smallest dinosaur ever? How did they grow up? What did they eat? What did dinosaur eggs look like? Find the dinosaur footprint! After reading through this package of wonderful information, you too could be a dinosaur expert like Dr. Ren!', '', '', '', '', '2008-07-01 00:00:00', '24 x 31', '36', 5, '082008finding_dino_3_b.jpg', '2008-10-10 00:00:00', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(603, 39, 'Vol.4 - Insects Living in the Rice Fieldy', 135, 12, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'A variety of insects, such as grasshoppers and red dragonflies, can be found in rice fields, which are of course a man-made environment. Which species can still be found and which have disappeared?', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '40', 5, 'insectsnenvironment4_b.jpg', '2008-12-24 14:40:50', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(567, 0, 'Come on in, Tabby Cat!', 110, 1, 0, 0, '', 212, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'When Tabby Cat and Black Cat were playing skipping rope, Siamese Cat barged into them and made them tumble down. Tabby Cat got furious and decided to play alone. No matter what Black and Siamese said, Tabby stubbornly insisted that he wouldn’t stop until he tripped over the rope. He wouldn’t even stop even when a storm came…', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, 'toranekosan.jpg', '2008-11-13 14:21:44', 62, '2008-11-19 18:32:34', 62, 1),
(568, 10, 'A Friend He Likes', 104, 1, 0, 0, '', 165, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'The Fox was worried about his friend, Wolf. He had seemed strange since the Fox had introduced him to little furry Dormouse. As the Snake told him that the Wolf must like her a lot, the Fox decided to plan a moon viewing party in the oak woods where the Dormouse lived.  \r\nWhat will happen to the excited Wolf?', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, 'kininaru-tomodachi.jpg', '2008-11-13 14:26:13', 62, '2008-11-19 18:33:17', 62, 1),
(569, 0, 'My Big Brother', 65, 1, 0, 0, '', 60, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'My big brother is mean, cowardly, narrow-minded, and lazy. He doesn’t do his homework. He never visits his friends or invites them to come round. He goes to school with messy hair. He pushes me down when he sees me in school. He gets sick on a swing easily...but he is still my big brother!', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 28', '32', 1, 'a-channo-onichan.jpg', '2008-11-13 14:29:06', 62, '2008-11-17 16:24:00', 62, 1),
(570, 0, 'The Sun Organ', 3, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Along with the sound of the organ that the sun plays, an elephant bus makes his great journey! He runs along bumpy roads, through fields, over  bridges, through buildings, in the rain, on a ferry, and through tunnels...everyone is welcome to get on and off as they please! Playful colours come vividly alive as if dancing in the music.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 31', '32', 1, 'taiyo-organ.jpg', '2008-11-13 14:43:02', 62, '2008-11-17 18:36:54', 62, 1),
(571, 0, 'Achan’s Birthday', 279, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Achan got a huge ladder as a birthday present. What shall we do with this? While Achan invents stories with a crow, a monkey and a bear, another present arrives…it’s a massive birthday cake!  \r\nAfter Achan climbs the ladder to blow out the candles, they all share the cake and play until it’s time to go home.', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '22 x 26', '32', 0, 'a-channo-birthday.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:06:49', 62, '2008-11-17 18:37:17', 62, 1),
(572, 0, 'The Sons of Mrs. Maron', 122, 1, 0, 0, '', 254, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Mrs. Maron sent nice handmade hats, jumpers and trousers as birthday presents to her three careless sons. They were so happy when they read her letter saying she would treat them to delicious wine, chicken and cake if they came to visit her with their new clothes on properly. Will they get their birthday treats?', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, 'marlon-obasan.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:31:52', 62, '2008-11-19 18:44:41', 62, 1),
(573, 0, 'Morumo, A Wonderful Guinea Pig', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 280, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'One day, Morumo came down from the sky with the rain and jumped on the head of a first year schoolboy. He made the boy so happy and playful that they went off to explore the school together. In the science class, music class, library, playground and even in the nurse’s room, wonderful Morumo makes everyone happy and playful!', '', '', '', '', '2008-09-01 00:00:00', '16 x 21', '72', 2, 'fujigina-morumo.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:37:12', 62, '2008-11-19 18:34:08', 62, 1),
(574, 0, 'Captain Ship and the Whale', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 219, 0, 0, 0, 2, 8, '', '', 'Captain Ship challenged a boy to a fishing game. To impress the boy, Captain Ship said he could catch a whale by making himself the bait… and they did! His boat Cha-cha tugged the whale along to prove his ability. But everyone thought the whale had saved the boat and Captain Ship was just boasting…', '', '', '', '', '2008-10-01 00:00:00', '16 x 21', '72', 2, 'shipsencho-to-kujira.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:52:16', 62, '2008-11-13 15:53:32', 62, 1),
(575, 0, 'Funguri Konguri – Storytelling in the Art Class', 73, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 10, '', '', 'A primary school art teacher finds himself telling stories to unusual guests after school, like how first year pupils floated into the air while playing a finger game like ‘Incy Wincy Spider’, or the story of when the second years became invisible… this is a collection of six unbelievable stories that all happened at school!', '', '', '', '', '2008-10-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '164', 2, 'funguri-konguri.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:55:53', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(576, 33, '6. The Holes of the Trees', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Holes in trees have always made safe homes for forest animals. Titmice make nests for their chicks. After they leave, flying squirrels widen the holes to make them their homes. As the holes grow bigger they are occupied by owls, by sables, and eventually, after hundreds of years, by bears.… An amazing story of trees and animals! ', '', '', '', '', '2008-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 24', '40', 5, 'judo.jpg', '2008-11-13 15:57:44', 62, '2009-05-15 14:16:28', 62, 1),
