(587, 0, 'The Secret of Granny Violet', 281, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|11|', '', 'Granny Violet is a very good dressmaker. But the problem is, she has trouble with threading needles because of her aged eyes. One rainy day, she asks a frog family to do the threading for her, and in return, they ask her to fix their lotus leaf bed. In turn, other creatures come to Granny Violet for help as well…', '', '', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '32', 1, '082008secret_of_granny_violet_b.jpg', '2008-11-15 13:29:15', 62, '2010-03-11 17:10:03', 62, 1),
(628, 0, 'The Rice Cracker Taxi', 293, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '', '', 'A giant rice cracker falls from the sky, into the mouth of a little boy. Suddenly, his feet turn into tyres, and he is transformed into the Rice Cracker Taxi! Who will his next customer be? Where will they want to go? Delightfully nonsensical prose is accompanied by colourful and dynamic illustrations depicting magical rides.', '', '', '', '', '2009-05-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '331670the_rice_cracker_taxi.jpg', '2009-09-08 01:56:30', 62, '2009-09-08 02:07:15', 62, 1),
(610, 0, 'The Twelve Months', 163, 1, 289, 14, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Gentle-hearted Maruša lives with her step-mother and step-sister, who treat her like a slave. One day, in the dead of winter, they send her to search for violets. At the top of a snowy mountain, Maruša meets twelve mysterious men sitting around a fire. How will they help her fulfil her impossible task? ', '', '', '', '', '2008-12-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '40', 1, '96390012gatsunotsukitachi.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:08:38', 62, '2009-02-26 14:32:22', 62, 1),
(600, 39, 'Vol.1 -  Hatcho Dragonflies', 147, 12, 135, 11, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 10, '', '', 'Where does the smallest dragonfly in the world live? Why have its numbers been decreasing? This book explores the marsh environment during a year in the life of this dragonfly.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2005-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '40', 5, 'insectsnenvironment1_b.jpg', '2008-12-24 14:36:12', 62, '2009-01-05 14:37:43', 62, 1),
(607, 0, 'Mexico, Mole Country', 283, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 15, '', '', 'This unique book, packed with evocative photographs and original artwork, takes the reader on a fascinating tour of Mexico’s stunning remains. The author, an artist, introduces the country’s rich and varied artistic heritage in an accessible and engaging way, taking time to mention Mexico’s most distinctive cuisine, the spicy, chocolately, very moreish mole sauce. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-01-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '176', 14, '003350morenokuni.jpg', '2009-01-29 17:16:08', 62, '2009-02-26 14:13:32', 62, 1),
(606, 0, 'Wi’ la’ mola: My Travels with Wolfy the Wolf-dog Puppy', 282, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 13, '|11|', '', 'This charming true-life story tells of the fateful encounter between the author, travelling through Canada seeking out adventure and inspiration, and Wolfy, a curious Wolf-dog puppy. Their developing friendship, transcending transcends country, age, and species, is recalled together with stunning descriptions of the awesome Canadian countryside and their travels through it. \r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2009-01-00 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '259', 5, '003370wilamora.jpg', '2009-01-29 16:45:44', 62, '2009-11-01 13:37:36', 62, 1),
(611, 0, 'The Cockroach King', 286, 1, 97, 4, '', 287, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'A popular Russian classic, this book tells the tale of the fearsome cockroach king, scourge of the animal kingdom. The rhythmical prose makes it a delight to read for children of all ages, who will be equally captivated by the charming illustrations. Hated by all the animals, big and small, will anyone ever defeat the cockroach king?', '', '', '', '', '2008-11-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '28', 1, '348110gokiburidaijo.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:16:00', 62, '2009-02-26 14:37:29', 62, 1),
(612, 0, 'The Town Has Disappeared', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 174, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '|8|', '', 'Granny Chira lives with Mr. Cat in a grey house in a grey town. One day, making soup, her windows steam up, making it seem like everything outside has disappeared into a dark fog. She paints herself a wonderful new town on her windows, full of flowers, birds and trees. Will Granny’s dreams ever come true? \r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2009-01-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '331630osotogakieta.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:19:27', 62, '2011-08-17 19:43:33', 62, 1),
(613, 0, 'Mr. A. Plot and the Mystery of the Lickety-Lick', 94, 1, 0, 0, '', 288, 0, 0, 0, 2, 10, '', '', 'When The Daily Mole starts to be delivered without any letters on, Mr. A. Plot and his faithful dog visit Mole Town to see what has happened. They hear about the terrifying Lickety-Lick, a creature that slurps up freshly printed ink, leaving nothing but blank pages behind. Will Mr. A. Plot and his canine companion solve the mystery? ', '', '', '', '', '2008-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '184', 2, '528360toranpuojisan.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:23:57', 62, '2009-02-26 14:39:34', 62, 1),
(614, 20, 'A Strange Night in the Enchanted Forest', 103, 1, 0, 0, '', 214, 0, 0, 0, 2, 12, '|8|11|', '', 'The latest instalment in the popular Shinoda series tells the story of the first, magical encounter between the boy and the fox who were later to marry and have children. One mysterious night during summer camp, in a forest said to be haunted, Itchi and Saki find themselves trapped in time – what awaits them in the forest? ', '', '', '', '', '2008-12-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '254', 2, '644040mamononomori.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:28:55', 62, '2010-09-05 04:58:17', 62, 1),
(615, 52, 'Igel''s Logbook Volume 2  Head for East, Cross the Desert!', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 257, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'Karl happened to board the secret submarine Igel again and set off to investigate a cave, which led them to the desert. There, Karl and the crew met the cactus-men, who were dying due to extremely dry weather caused by something called ‘Keuka’. Their adventure began when they decided to find out what was happening in the desert…', '', '', '', '', '2008-12-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '270', 2, '744820-2e_gerugo.jpg', '2009-01-30 17:31:10', 62, '2011-02-14 09:45:03', 62, 1),
(616, 0, 'Dinosaur Puzzles', 123, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|8|2|15|26|14|', '', 'Brightly-coloured cartoon dinosaurs of every shape and size feature in this collection of puzzles and games for young children, who will enjoy searching for hidden animals, matching up species, reading coded messages, finding their way through mazes, and numerous other attention-grabbing games.', '', '', '', '', '1993-12-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '24', 1, '330650_dinosaur_puzzles.jpg', '2009-02-02 17:21:34', 62, '2010-12-08 22:47:49', 62, 1),
(618, 0, 'The Swallow’s Journey 5000 kilometers across the sea', 92, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'This dramatic picture book lets the young reader accompany the swallow on\r\nhis long, perilous journey to Japan. The rhythmical, lyrical text expresses\r\nthe instincts driving the swallow, whilst the anatomically accurate yet\r\nartistically sweeping pictures bring the bird to life on each page. This\r\nstunning book artfully communicates the preciousness of life.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2009-02-01 00:00:00', '25 x 27', '40', 1, '437390_the_swallows_journey.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:17:56', 62, '2009-05-26 10:00:20', 62, 1),
(619, 51, 'The Wolf King', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 101, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'One day, a fortuitous fall from a slippery cliff edge propels a lone wolf – a shy, klutzy wolf – to lupine royalty. He just wants to be alone – but more and more wolves keep following him, hanging off his every word! Humorous text and striking illustrations will capture the young reader’s attention. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-03-01 00:00:00', '24 x 28', '32', 1, '331640the_wolf_king.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:24:25', 62, '2011-02-23 20:34:01', 62, 1),
(620, 33, '7. Herbivores', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'In Japan’s wilderness, hares are disappearing but serows are increasing. Why is it that the number of wild animals is changing? This stunning book is filled with beautiful photographs that capture Japan’s native herbivorous wildlife in its natural habitat, and looks at how environmental changes are affecting wildlife and the relationship between creatures and plants throughout Japan. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-03-01 00:00:00', '29 x 24', '40', 5, '526870herbivores.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:27:16', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(621, 33, '8. Carnivores', 53, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '', '', 'Another book in this beautiful series of photo journals capturing Japan’s wildlife in its natural habitat. This edition introduces the carnivorous animals that populate the islands of Japan– such as the wily fox, the champion swimmer weasel, and the ferocious ermine. The roles of these animals are examined alongside spectacular photography. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-03-02 00:00:00', '29 x 24', '40', 5, '526880carnivores.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:29:48', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(622, 48, 'Fridge', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '|10|', '', 'This charming book is ideal for baby’s first picture book. Open up the cover, illustrated to look like a fridge door, to find all the delicious food inside! The brightly coloured, bold pictures are accompanied by well-balanced, rhythmical text that builds to a scene of baby’s breakfast. The size is also perfect for little hands. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '102710fridge.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:32:15', 62, '2011-02-24 15:19:04', 62, 1),
(623, 48, 'Closet', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '|10|', '', 'In this delightful board book, readers can open the door to the bedroom cupboard to discover all the bedding inside. Familiar household items appear in sequence on carefully balanced pages, with enjoyable onomatopoeia-filled text creating a strong sense of tempo and progression throughout the pages. Sure to be an instant favourite for the youngest of readers. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '102720cupboard.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:33:47', 62, '2011-02-24 15:18:22', 62, 1),
(624, 0, '100 Play Hide and Seek', 123, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|2|15|11|14|', '', 'Pirates, kings, Santa Clauses, marathon runners, children…each double page spread features 100 charming characters, asking questions and challenging young readers to find the answers! Filled with dynamic, humorous illustrations, this wonderful book can be read and enjoyed over and over again, helping children to count, learn, read and play. Part of a popular series. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '24', 1, '331710hide_and_seek_by_100.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:35:34', 62, '2011-08-03 13:37:58', 62, 1),
(625, 0, 'When I opened the door to that garden', 84, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'A curious little girl finds a beautiful garden which is looked after by a crotchety old lady. One day, she meets a mysterious girl in the garden, who begins to tell her story. At once both humorous and bittersweet, this is a creatively brilliant modern classic by the renowned children’s author. Also includes another tale, “The Golden Baby”. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '166', 2, '643050when_I_opened_the_door_to_that_garden.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:54:10', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(626, 41, 'The landscape of Satoyama', 26, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 11, '', '', 'Award-winning photographer Mitsuhiko Imamori has selected some of his favourite pictures for this book. His images capture the beauty of the satoyama landscape, those areas that straddle the border between land managed by humans and the wildness of nature. The accompanying text reveals Imamori’s thoughts on the significance of the many elements of satoyama. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '94', 5, '016530the_landscape_of_satoyama.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:56:50', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(627, 0, 'Burying Beetle', 292, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '|10|', '', 'This illustrated book depicts the life of the burying beetle, which uses the flesh of dead animals to carefully feed its young. The beetle’s birth, nurturing instinct and death are all beautifully depicted in highly realistic illustrations and straightforward prose. This book is excellent for teaching young children about nature’s cycle. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-04-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '36', 1, '437050_burying_beetle.jpg', '2009-05-26 09:59:13', 62, '2010-09-05 04:56:26', 62, 1),
(629, 0, 'Little Book', 294, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|22|10|11|', '', '“You must work hard if you’re going to grow up to be an impressive encyclopaedia!”, Little Book is always being told. But what kind of book will he eventually become? In this colourful, original story, Little Book thinks about what he wants to be in the future. A book where the book is about the book! ', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '32', 1, '331680little_book.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:08:47', 62, '2010-09-05 04:59:44', 62, 1),
(630, 0, 'What’s your most special thing?', 295, 1, 0, 0, '', 296, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'This charming book tells the story of Natsuka, who was adopted at an early age. The warmth and sensitivity of the story is testament to the fact that the writer has herself adopted. A gentle, affectionate book that shows there can be more than just one type of family.', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '232330whats_your_most_special_thing.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:11:06', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(631, 0, 'Piano Dreams', 297, 0, 0, 0, '', 156, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '', '', 'Lilting verse combines with bold, colourful illustrations to conjure up the dreams of a piano. Big, heavy and unable to move, the piano instead travels through his imagination, picturing forests and clouds and oceans and flowers. A wonderful book by a much-loved partnership that is sure to enchant children of all ages.', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '21 x 19', '36', 1, '232320piano_dreams.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:12:47', 62, '2009-09-08 02:13:32', 62, 1),
(632, 0, 'All About Chameleons', 298, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'Packed full of captivating, colourful pictures of the many types of chameleon that live in the wild. A fun and educational book that introduces chameleons, their habitats and habits, in an easy-to-follow AIUEO syllabary format, the order of the Japanese alphabet. Dedicated fans of these cute, charming little creatures will love it – as will all children with an interest in nature.', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '40', 5, '232340all_about_chameleons.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:15:41', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(633, 0, 'The Seven Wonders of Honjo', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 250, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Welcome to the eerie world of Edo at night, where strange creatures lurk amongst the shadows. Immerse yourself in the delightfully creepy prose and spectacularly spooky illustrations bring to life a floating lantern that tempts you into the dark woods, a river haunted by a dead woman’s ghost, and five other terrifying Edo ghouls and ghostly places.', '', '', '', '', '2009-07-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '331700the_seven_wonders_of_honjo.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:17:31', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(634, 0, 'Mr. Kugu’s Museum of Treasures', 177, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Mr. Kugu is a born collector. His Museum of Treasures, tucked away in a hard-to-find spot, is full of the many mysterious and wonderful items that he has collected during his travels throughout the world. This funny, captivating book introduces the delightful stories of how some of the exhibits came to be part of the museum. Charmingly illustrated throughout.', '', '', '', '', '2009-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '110', 2, '528380mr_Kugus_museum_of_treasures.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:19:28', 62, '2009-09-08 02:20:19', 62, 1),
(635, 0, 'Children’s Songs from Russia', 286, 9, 97, 4, '', 299, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'This stunning edition brings together some of Russia’s most charming traditional songs for children, as collated by Kornei Chukiovskii, who was one of Russia’s most popular children’s authors. The 22 songs are accompanied by enchanting illustrations from 1957, and the rhythmical translation gives the collection a wonderful tempo and timbre.', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '32', 1, '348120childrens_songs_from_russia-.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:22:44', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(636, 0, 'The June Relay', 300, 1, 0, 0, '', 301, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Class D’s relay team is a mixed bunch – Kai and Yuki are fast and Hiroshi and Yo not so, but they’ve all got one thing in common – problems and the desire to take part in the class relay race. Each chapter looks at a single relay member, until they are finally brought together for the finale - a tense relay race held on an unseasonably windy June day.', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-01 00:00:00', '14×20', '148', 0, '646050the_june_relay.jpg', '2009-09-08 02:26:20', 62, '2009-09-08 02:27:14', 62, 1),
(637, 46, 'From Tomorrow, Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|2|11|', '', 'With no detective work coming in, Milky Sugiyama is making a living doing part-time jobs. His detective friend asks him to help catch Monsieur, the Phantom Thief, who is a master of disguise. Milky''s estranged wife lends her detecting talents and the two pals get closer to Monsieur... The book covers two crimes and is divided into case files and solutions.', '', '', '', '', '1995-05-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '142', 3, '345140__From_Tomorrow_Ill_Be_a_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 13:23:15', 62, '2010-09-05 04:56:06', 62, 1),
(638, 46, 'After the Rain, Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'The cakes at a local patisserie have all been smothered in soy sauce. All fingers point to a rival patisserie nearby. Elsewhere, in ‘A Letter from Mush’, Milky at last comes face to face with Mush, his nemesis! And, with his friends, he tries his hand at disguise for the first time. Readers can work with Milky to solve the crimes!', '', '', '', '', '2005-12-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '142', 3, '345260_After_the_Rain_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 13:24:57', 62, '2010-03-11 17:12:54', 62, 1),
(639, 46, 'Before I Knew It, Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|2|11|', '', 'Milky Sugiyama is invited to a party. But, as always, he finds himself caught up in a mystery. Where on earth did the missing diamond go?Together with his daughter, Tomoko, he works to solve the crime. Keep an eye out for the not-so-simple tricks that the thief has used!', '', '', '', '', '1994-06-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '142', 3, '345130_Before_I_Knew_It_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 13:29:57', 62, '2010-09-05 04:55:55', 62, 1),
(641, 46, 'That''s Why I''m a Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'In these three stories about part-time sleuth Milky Sugiyama, our hero solves the case of a stolen diamond ring, chases a crook into a fairground ghost house and participates in a battle of wits with an international art thief. Cartoon story book with dynamic monochrome and colour double-spread pictures.', '', '', '', '', '1998-04-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '150', 3, '345190_Thats_Why_Im_a_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 14:33:08', 62, '2010-03-11 17:11:42', 62, 1),
(642, 46, 'Whenever, Wherever, Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'It''s Christmas, and Milky Sugiyama is making ends meet by delivering presents dressed as Santa Claus. One apartment that he visits is robbed by a thief also dressed as Santa, and Milky finds himself under suspicion. He needs to work quickly to restore his damaged reputation and catch the real criminal.', '', '', '', '', '1997-05-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '150', 3, '345180_Whenever_Wherever_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 15:59:50', 62, '2010-03-11 17:11:27', 62, 1),
(643, 46, 'Somehow I''m a Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'Three more stories in the best-selling series about the exploits of private eye Milky Sugiyama. Readers are invited to guess who dunnit in the cases of a stolen briefcase, a threatening letter and mysterious car crash. Cartoon pictures, colourful characters and imaginative plots.', '', '', '', '', '1999-03-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '150', 3, '345200_Somehow_Im_a_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 16:03:01', 62, '2010-03-11 17:11:58', 62, 1),
(644, 7, 'Nontan & Fleecy Tartan', 40, 0, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|8|10|', '', 'Tartan, Nontan''s younger sister, is crying because she has accidentally let go off the balloon Nontan had just given her. As Nontan leaves her alone crying, Mr. Penguin comes and pokes Tartan. Tartan goes for a walk in the sky with Mr. Penguin and comes across many balloons.  ', '', '', '', '', '2005-10-01 00:00:00', '19×16', '32', 1, '217180_Nontan_and_Fleecy_Tartan.jpg', '2009-11-01 16:41:00', 62, '2009-12-03 01:14:44', 62, 1),
(645, 46, 'Hurrah For Great Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'This is Milky Sugiyama''s 7th title! Private eye Milky Sugiyama takes his two children on holiday to the seaside, but then finds his deductive skills tested after a fellow guest at the hotel has his wallet stolen, but not the money inside. Readers are invited to see if they can solve the case. Also, includes another mystery entitled "The Return of Miss Rabbit". ', '', '', '', '', '2000-12-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '142', 3, '345230_Hurrah_For_Great_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 16:51:46', 62, '2010-03-11 17:12:11', 62, 1),
(646, 46, 'Ready Steady Go! Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'This is the tenth volume of the Milky Sugiyama series. It includes three episodes, one of which sees Sugiyama confronting a pickpocket at a wrestling stadium. With his smart wife living away from home and his two kids around to help, how will the great Detective solve the problems?', '', '', '', '', '2007-09-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '142', 3, '345280_Ready_Steady_Go_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 16:55:34', 62, '2010-03-11 17:13:09', 62, 1),
(648, 46, 'What If? Private Eye', 302, 0, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|0|', '', 'The first outing for Milky Sugiyama, private eye. Each story is divided into a case file and its solution. Readers can work alongside Milky to discover who stole a famous painting from the local gallery, retrieve a valuable book for an old man, and participate in all the other mysterious things that happen along the way.', '', '', '', '', '1992-04-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '146', 3, '345100_What_If_Private_Eye.jpg', '2009-11-01 23:46:21', 62, '2011-03-04 17:11:06', 62, 1),
(652, 48, 'Drawer', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '|10|', '', 'All of the things that baby needs to get dressed are in the drawer! Parents and baby can enjoy the musical tempo that flows through the book as they call Mr. Pants, Mr. Shirt, Mr & Mrs Sock, Mrs Bag, Blanky and Teddy out of the drawer. Another charming addition to this unique board book series. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '102740drawers.jpg', '2009-11-29 12:29:29', 62, '2011-02-24 15:18:40', 62, 1),
(653, 0, 'The Full Moon', 65, 1, 0, 0, '', 304, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '', '', 'The bright yellow full moon looks so tasty that I just want to eat it all up! This lovely book, the perfect size for little hands, shows how the moon can appear as different types of food to the hungry watcher! The lyrical text by poet Shoichi Nejime is complemented by Shinobu Saito’s wonderful hand-painted illustrations. \r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '17 x 16', '24', 1, '215410full_moon.jpg', '2009-11-29 12:31:53', 62, '2009-11-29 12:33:43', 62, 1),
(654, 0, 'Friends in the Garden', 305, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'In the corner of the garden sit two flower pots, one tall and one wide. Nobody pays much attention to them, but as time passes they start to feel something growing out of their heads…! This adorably illustrated book captures the passing of the seasons and the role of a garden’s many creatures in the natural cycle. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '331760friends_in_the_garden.jpg', '2009-11-29 13:20:36', 62, '2009-11-29 13:22:07', 62, 1),
(655, 0, 'My Daddy the Hippo', 306, 1, 0, 0, '', 314, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Mummy’s out for the evening, so Daddy and the kids hop into bath together – where Daddy turns into a giant hippo! Join this happy trio as they splash and slide and swim and play! And still make it home in time for bed. With delightful illustrations, this is a perfect book for children to read with Daddy.', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '331750papa_hippo.jpg', '2009-11-29 13:24:09', 62, '2009-11-30 21:03:46', 62, 1),
(656, 0, 'Sushi for Cats', 92, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'All the cats in the village are delighted when the “Sushi for Cats” van arrives! After eating their fill of delicious sushi, they set off with the owner and his cat helper in his van – that turns into a submarine! -to fish for more tasty toppings. The illustrations are filled with warmth and charming detail.  ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '232350cats_sushi.jpg', '2009-11-29 13:39:44', 62, '2009-11-30 21:04:37', 62, 1),
(657, 0, 'Welcome to Wolf School', 285, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'At the top of the hill, a new playschool has opened. All the children are excited, but when they visit the playschool, the teachers are big, scary, loud wolves! At first, the children are scared of them, but when they go on an accidental ride around the countryside, they soon change their minds…', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '331730welcome_to_wolf.jpg', '2009-11-29 13:53:39', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(658, 0, 'Baby Bean Cake', 308, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'One day, something comes rolling into the garden. It’s a little baby bean cake! Mr and Mrs Grass Lizard decide to take care of Baby Bean Cake, and soon they are helped by all their little creature friends in the garden! But what will happen when Baby Bean Cake wanders into the dark place under the decking? \r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '23 x 25', '36', 1, '331770ohagi_chan.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:04:30', 62, '2009-11-29 14:05:07', 62, 1),
(659, 0, 'The Great Big Mix-Up', 286, 1, 97, 4, '', 309, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'Kittens oink, sparrows moo, frogs fly and mice chase cats! In Chukovskii’s world, everything is turned upside down and around about in a great big mix-up! Tanaka’s translation effortlessly captures the rhythm and tempo of Chukovskii’s vivid, mimetic poetry, and Yarbusova’s lovely illustrations evoke traditional Russian folk art to complete this wonderful book.  ', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '24', 1, '348130metya_kutya.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:07:29', 62, '2009-11-29 16:12:23', 62, 1),
(660, 0, 'Bruno: my most special memories', 310, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'Big, fluffy, lovely Bruno. He was our beloved family pet, but we couldn’t look after him anymore, so we had to abandon him in the woods…but my memories of him are still my most special of all. The bittersweet yet heart-warming tale of Bruno and his loving family is wonderfully illustrated with bold, bright pictures. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '331690guruguru.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:11:11', 62, '2009-11-30 21:06:03', 62, 1),
(661, 0, 'The Assistant Major Counsellor and the Dancing Mushrooms', 279, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'Long ago there lived an Assistant Major Counsellor…who was a very greedy pig. He couldn’t stop himself from eating anything and everything that looks tasty! So when he found some magical mushrooms in the mountains, he just couldn’t help himself…a lovely picture book version of an ancient tale, taken from the Anthology of Tales from the Past. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '427210dancing_mushroom.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:14:20', 62, '2009-11-30 21:06:40', 62, 1),
(662, 0, 'Letters: to my dearest friend', 311, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'A charming collection of correspondence between friends, spanning country, species and planet!  Each letter is accompanied by illustrations filled with warmth and humour, and unusual and beautiful stamps from around the world. This book evokes the importance of friendship, and even in this age of technology will have children reaching for their pens once finished. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '21 x 14', '40', 1, '331720letters.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:15:44', 62, '2009-11-29 14:16:41', 62, 1),
(663, 0, 'Go! Go! Morumo!', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 280, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '', '', 'Farewell, depression! Goodbye, bad mood! Just a moment or two with Morumo the Guinea Pig will have you feeling like it’s a festival! Join Morumo on his adventures as he marches through the town, hopping from head to head and bringing joy wherever he goes. A slightly surreal, foot-tappingly rhythmical, enchantingly unique book. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-09 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '72', 3, '439360go_go_marumo.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:18:44', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(664, 0, 'My name is Drifter, from the Seaweed Forest', 31, 1, 0, 0, '', 235, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|10|', '', 'The fourth story in the Whale Sea series. This time, too, a letter becomes the key to a new friendship. Drifter the Sea Otter thinks of himself as a ‘lone otter’ but somehow he ends up playing host to a travelling turtle. But is the turtle all that he seems? Drifter must work to find out the truth! ', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '106', 2, '501100pukapuka.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:20:51', 62, '2011-02-23 20:36:21', 62, 1),
(665, 0, 'Snowy the Snowgirl', 312, 1, 313, 16, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Snowy is a wild snowgirl; she floated down from the sky one night, and landed in a tiny mountain village. Snowy is active, curious and full of joy – at the wonderful adventure of life! Elegant copperplate engravings by the renowned Yoko Yamamoto accompany the lyrical text. The first children’s novel by Ekuni, an acclaimed writer of adult fiction. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-09-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '234', 1, '643060koyuki_the_snowman.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:22:24', 62, '2009-11-29 16:07:37', 62, 1);
INSERT INTO `jos_publications_titles_2011-08-26` (`id`, `series_id`, `title`, `author_id`, `author_type`, `author2_id`, `author2_type`, `author_ext`, `illustrator_id`, `illustrator2_id`, `photographer_id`, `photographer2_id`, `cat_id`, `age_group_id`, `country_id`, `country_ext`, `synopsis`, `sub1_title`, `sub1_text`, `sub2_title`, `sub2_text`, `publication_year`, `book_size`, `pages`, `book_colour`, `imageurl`, `created`, `created_by`, `modified`, `modified_by`, `published`) VALUES
(666, 0, 'Wonderful Lou', 94, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|10|', '', 'Little Tsun loves her aunt, Lou. Lou is a painter and a teller of wonderfully strange stories; she shows that everything is not always it seems. Taking the form of Little Tsun’s diary, this book takes the reader on a charming journey of fun and fantasy! This revised edition of the 1993 classic features a new cover and beautiful illustrations throughout.', '', '', '', '', '2009-10-10 00:00:00', '19 x 16', '110', 3, '528390lu_chan.jpg', '2009-11-29 14:24:54', 62, '2010-05-11 11:47:06', 62, 1),
(667, 23, 'Guardian of the Awful God Volume 1: God’s Appearance', 105, 1, 0, 0, '', 166, 0, 0, 0, 2, 12, '|8|11|', '', 'Heroine Balsa encounters a brother and sister being sold by a slave trader in the market. The girl, who seems to have a strange aura, is called Asra. Impulsively Balsa takes her away. However, later she comes to wonder if the girl is a divinely appointed guardian or a child of disaster. Author Uehashi likens her multi-award-winning "MORIBITO (Guardian)" series to a tree that keeps growing new branches of rich foliage. Illustrator Futaki is an animator for Studio Ghibli, creator of international hits "Princess Mononoke" and "Spirited Away."', 'Award', '2003 SHOGAKUKAN CULTURAL PRIZE IN PUBLISHING FOR CHILDREN''S BOOKS', '', '', '2009-01-00 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '290', 3, 'guardian_of_the_awful_god_volume_1.jpg', '2009-11-29 16:23:55', 62, '2009-12-03 01:09:31', 62, 1),
(668, 0, 'Koban the Shark''s Sea Tour', 311, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Bears, raccoons, squirrels, mice and other forest animals join an underwater sea tour run by Koban the Shark. Carried along by a whale, they view a sunken pirate ship and enjoy a party on the whale''s back. However, on the way home, some little squirrels get lost and have to be rescued by a group of penguins.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2000-00-00 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '204970koban_tour_ltd.jpg', '2009-12-03 00:15:38', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(682, 47, '2. Animal Noses', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'How much do you know about noses? The animal world is full of noses – furry, feathery, soft, scary – and this book introduces the reader to some of the special ways in which animals use their noses to survive in the wild. Packed with fascinating scientific facts, it’s a great way to get young children learning about the natural world. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-01-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414420dobutsu_no_hana.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:49:55', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(698, 0, 'Stomp Stomp Daddy', 28, 1, 0, 0, '', 326, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '', '', 'Daddy Wild Boar is full of life – and fun! Follow his adventures as he stomps around the countryside, with his ten children in tow, learning how to be the best daddy he can be. This all-colour book is in four parts, one per season, each with action-packed illustrations and a simple recipe using ingredients from the story.', '', '', '', '', '2010-05-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '72', 1, '313600otochan_dododo.jpg', '2010-06-01 14:26:33', 62, '2010-08-02 16:09:55', 62, 1),
(681, 47, '1. Animal Eyes', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'There are so many kinds of animal eyes: small, big, narrow, wide. This wonderful book, the first in a series of six, looks at how and why different animals have differently shaped eyes – it’s all to do with the way they live. The question and answer format will entertain younger children, whilst older readers enjoy the stunning photography.', '', '', '', '', '2010-01-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414410dobutsu_no_me.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:48:40', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(672, 0, 'An Underground House of 100 Stories', 151, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|10|11|', '', 'A mysterious home, stretching deep under the ground. Who on earth could be living there? This book follows on from the sell-out success of A House of 100 Stories, only this time we are led underground to see what magical and mysterious secrets are waiting to be told! This book is opened vertically and read down the page.', '', '', '', '', '2009-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 31', '32', 1, '331660ground_100.jpg', '2010-03-11 15:39:23', 62, '2010-03-11 17:10:18', 62, 1),
(673, 0, 'A Home for an Old Man', 281, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'This touching tale lets the reader join the travels of an old man, a drifter with no companion in the world other than his dog. As he roams, he comes across many characters with many different homes. But where is home for the old man? A poignant meditation on what makes a home.  ', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '022010_A_Home_for_an_Old_Ma.jpg', '2010-03-11 15:41:26', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(674, 0, 'Fedora’s Woe', 286, 1, 97, 4, '', 218, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'The latest in Kaiseisha’s series of new translations of classic tales by one of Russia’s most beloved children’s poets. This dynamic translation is rich with onomatopoeia, delightfully evoking the clattering of Fedora’s plates and cutlery and pots and pans making an escape from her dusty, dirty house. A perfect book for reading aloud, just as Chukovskii intended. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '28', 1, '022010_Peaopnho_rope.jpg', '2010-03-11 15:45:17', 62, '2010-03-11 17:03:46', 62, 1),
(675, 0, 'The Little Lost North Wind', 315, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|', '', 'Hannah’s life is changed forever when she gives a home to a little North Wind boy who has lost his family. The friends spend the warmer months together before winter comes and they must say goodbye. The ageless illustrations are rendered in beautifully muted colours, and reveal Hannah’s private world of play, laughter and tears.', '', '', '', '', '2010-01-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '022010_The_Little_Lost_Nort.jpg', '2010-03-11 15:48:12', 62, '2010-12-08 22:48:35', 62, 1),
(676, 0, 'How Niteczka the Tailor came to be King', 317, 1, 318, 4, '', 319, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'An enduringly popular children’s tale from one of Poland’s best loved authors.  Niteczka the tailor, armed with just his needle and thread, sets out on an adventure to find the kingdom which will give him his crown. Adachi’s rhythmical translation captures Makuszyński’s magical world, rendered beautifully by veteran illustrator Orliński, in his first work for a Japanese publisher. \r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '40', 1, '022010_Shitateyo.jpg', '2010-03-11 15:50:48', 62, '2010-03-11 16:15:53', 62, 1),
(677, 0, 'Dangoro Yamagushi, Treasure Hunter: The Hidden Treasure of Captain X', 302, 1, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Dangoro Yamagushi is a treasure hunter by trade. He’s great at digging holes, but he’s not so good at figuring out puzzles. Hikaru is something of a scaredy-cat, but he’s a real whizz at quizzes and codes. Together, they make a top treasure hunting team – and this time they’re on the trail of Captain X’s hidden treasure!', '', '', '', '', '2010-01-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '144', 3, '022010_Treasure_Hunter.jpg', '2010-03-11 16:17:57', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(678, 46, 'The World’s Best Private Eye', 302, 1, 0, 0, '', 303, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '|8|', '', 'The continuing adventures of Milky Sugiyama. Readers can work with Milky to solve three new crimes. A valuable pearl has disappeared – but what has a bream got to do with it? If someone is trying to steal a bejewelled model boat, why are they drilling holes in the wall? And what is Miss Rabbit doing back in town?', '', '', '', '', '2010-01-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '148', 3, '022010_The_Worlds_Best_Priv.jpg', '2010-03-11 16:21:10', 62, '2011-03-04 16:49:58', 62, 1),
(679, 26, 'The Fog of Amakusa', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 235, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'The newest instalment in the story of a magical white fox on a journey of discovery that takes him through time, witnessing many pivotal historical events on the way. This time, the fox encounters the Christian uprising in Shimabara. But who is the mysterious ringleader, Shiro Amakusa, and what are the magical powers he claims to possess? ', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '382', 2, '022010_Tengusa.jpg', '2010-03-11 16:23:22', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(680, 0, 'Will Chimps One Day be Human?', 46, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '|8|11|', '', 'Evolution is something that everyone has heard of, but not many people really understand. This book takes the reader on a journey to the Galapagos Islands, where Charles Darwin first struck upon the ideas that became On the Origin of the Species. Complete with humorous illustrations and engaging prose, this is a great book for budding biologists. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-11-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '174', 2, '528200-chimpansee.jpg', '2010-03-11 16:35:08', 62, '2010-12-08 22:45:27', 62, 1),
(683, 47, '3. Animal Mouths', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'Our mouths are very important – without them, we couldn’t eat! It’s the same for animals, and the way their mouths are shaped can tell us a lot about what they like to eat. Gorgeous photography of the colourful animal world is accompanied by simple yet enlightening text on mouth function by animal expert Mitsuko Masui.', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414430dobutsu_no_kuchi.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:51:18', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(684, 47, '4. Animal Ears', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'The animal world is full of sound, and sometimes being able to hear well can be the difference between life and death. This beautiful book teaches children about how each animal has ears that are perfectly adapted to its lifestyle in the wild, using amazing photography and simple yet fact-filled text, presenting in a fun question and answer format.', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414440dobutsu_no_mimi.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:52:41', 62, '2010-03-12 15:58:51', 62, 1),
(685, 47, '5. Animal Arms and Legs', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'Without arms and legs, animals and humans wouldn’t be able to move around. This book shows how the legs and arms of animals help them to be successful in their natural habitats. Why does a polar bear have such hairy feet? How does an octopus taste its prey? Do birds have knees? All these questions and more are answered inside!', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414450dobutsu_no_tetoashi.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:53:55', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(686, 47, '6. Animal Tails', 320, 11, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 7, '', '', 'Tails are very important to many animals. They need them to balance, to swim, to communicate, to escape from prey, to dangle from trees…. the shape and size of an animal tail depends on what it needs to do. This is a great way to introduce children to the science of the natural world and its endless diversity.', '', '', '', '', '2010-02-01 00:00:00', '28 x 22', '32', 5, '414460dobutsu_no_shippo.jpg', '2010-03-12 15:55:11', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(687, 10, 'Play-Friends', 104, 1, 0, 0, '', 165, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'The tenth instalment in the popular series following the adventures of Fox. This time, Fox meets Marten, a little girl who is new to the woods. She is a wonderful recorder player, but she seems a little spoiled, too. She doesn’t want Fox to play with Wolf – but how can he spend three whole days without his best friend?', '', '', '', '', '2010-03-01 00:00:00', '25 x 21', '32', 1, '232360tomodachi_gokko.jpg', '2010-03-16 19:14:39', 62, '2010-03-16 19:16:19', 62, 1),
(688, 49, 'Which Hand is It In?', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '', '', 'Which hand is it in? This timeless game, popular all over the world, has now been turned into a delightfully illustrated picture book for young children. The characters’ boldly expressive faces will be attractive to even the youngest readers, and the format of the book has been carefully devised for reading and playing aloud.', '', '', '', '', '2010-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '102750docchino_teni.jpg', '2010-05-11 08:30:10', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(689, 49, 'Where are You Hiding?', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '', '', 'Perfect for reading aloud to young children, this interactive book is sure to foster a love of books in little readers! With simple yet charming illustrations, full of movement, the book asks the reader to guess where a series of friendly characters are hiding.  Another sure-fire hit from this popular young author-illustrator.', '', '', '', '', '2010-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '102760docchini_kakureteru.jpg', '2010-05-11 08:32:05', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(690, 0, 'Fixing the Road Together', 95, 1, 0, 0, '', 92, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|11|', '', 'Watch the entire process of a bumpy road getting fixed by hard-working workmen. Lots of special trucks, dumpers and rollers are involved, and the rest of the road is filled with colourful cars and buses, as well as people on the pavement. A wonderful picture book with lots to enjoy and discover, even on repeated reads.', '', '', '', '', '2010-04-01 00:00:00', '21 x 26', '32', 1, '221200dorokoji.jpg', '2010-05-11 08:34:41', 62, '2011-02-23 20:39:01', 62, 1),
(691, 0, 'The Mole Bus', 321, 1, 322, 17, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|10|11|', '', 'Next stop, Underneath the Cupboard! After that, The End of Someone’s Garden. Every day, the Mole Bus tootles around Underground Town, taking people where they need to go. But one day something shoots up from the ground, stopping the Mole Bus in its tracks! Be charmed by Underground Town and its wonderfully cute inhabitants.', '', '', '', '', '2010-04-01 00:00:00', '19 x 26', '32', 1, '331810mogura_bus.jpg', '2010-05-11 08:37:15', 62, '2011-03-04 14:26:24', 62, 1),
(692, 41, 'Little Lives throughout the Seasons: The Insects of Japan', 26, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 11, '', '', 'Award-winning nature photographer Mitsuhiko Imamori’s latest insect-focused work. Imamori uses the microscopic worlds of insects to tell a bigger story about the nature that surrounds us, here profiling 22 different Japanese insects. Includes 25 of his most stunning photographs, here reproduced in glorious colour, and detailed text on each insect and the tiny world it inhabits.', '', '', '', '', '2010-04-01 00:00:00', '26 x 19', '94', 5, '016520nihon_no_konchu.jpg', '2010-05-11 08:39:34', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(693, 50, 'The Friends of Vegetable Village: Spring', 170, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'Meet the vegetables of Vegetable Village, a bunch of charming characters that will soon have even the fussiest eaters interested in their onions and peas. A character-based story is used to introduce each vegetable, together with on their roots, nutritional value and storage. There’s plenty of detail to surprise grown up vegetable fans, too.', '', '', '', '', '2010-03-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '39', 1, '436110yasaimura_spring.jpg', '2010-05-14 14:17:21', 62, '2010-09-28 13:38:32', 62, 1),
(694, 0, 'The Great Migration', 324, 1, 0, 0, '', 325, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'Author Hiroyoshi Higuchi has spent twenty years studying the migratory patterns of birds, using the tools of modern science to reveal what happens every year when birds leave for warmer climates. Where do they go? How long does it take? Why do they go there? All these questions are answered with scientific accuracy and beautifully observed illustrations.', '', '', '', '', '2010-03-01 00:00:00', '24 x 28', '40', 1, '527690wataridori.jpg', '2010-05-14 14:18:45', 62, '2010-05-17 14:10:35', 62, 1),
(695, 51, 'The Wolf''s Feast', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 101, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'As a fox pursues a piglet across the countryside his mind begins to play tricks on him. In his imagination the piglet becomes fatter and fatter. What a feast he will have when he finally catches it! With only this thought on his mind, he ignores rabbits, deer, a cock and other prey.\r\nHowever, by the time that he reaches the piglet his anticipations have become so exaggerated that he does not even recognize it!', '', '', '', '', '1999-04-01 00:00:00', '24×28', '32', 1, 'the_wolfs_feast.jpg', '2010-05-18 11:16:36', 62, '2011-02-23 20:33:37', 62, 1),
(696, 51, 'The Wolf''s Friend', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 101, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'Alone wolf feels frightened when he meets a bear who suggests that they go hunting for food. Could it be a trick to eat him? But the bear gives the fox some honeycomb and together they catch fish. In this way the wolf learns that the bear is in fact a generous and gentle creature. As usual Tashima''s pictures are wonderful.', '', '', '', '', '2001-10-01 00:00:00', '24×28', '32', 1, 'the_wolfs_friend.jpg', '2010-05-18 11:19:19', 62, '2011-02-23 20:33:47', 62, 1),
(697, 51, 'The Wolf''s Secret', 43, 1, 0, 0, '', 101, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'The fierce wolf''s embarrassing secret is that he is frightened of inchworms.\r\nSo frightened that he will run a mile when he sees one. The simple story is enlivened by dramatic illustrations. Artist Tashima is a wonderful colourist who despite his age, also has the enthusiasm and naivety of a child.', '', '', '', '', '2003-05-01 00:00:00', '24×28', '32', 1, 'the_wolfs_secret.jpg', '2010-05-18 11:20:57', 62, '2011-02-23 20:33:28', 62, 1),
(699, 50, 'The Friends of Vegetable Village: Summer', 170, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'In summer, deliciously ripe, mouth-wateringly juicy vegetables are everywhere to be found – especially in Vegetable Village! Meet Tomato, Cucumber, Pumpkin and their friends, and find out all about how they have been used, cooked, stored and enjoyed over the ages. A fun and accessible way to get children thinking about nutrition – as well as reading!', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '39', 1, '436120yasaimura_summer.jpg', '2010-06-30 08:31:03', 62, '2010-09-28 13:38:40', 62, 1),
(700, 20, 'Mermaid Island, Lost in Time', 103, 1, 0, 0, '', 214, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '|8|', '', 'We again meet up with the Shinodas, who have received an invitation to stay at a hotel on a remote island, far to the south. Deciding to take a family trip, the Shinodas soon realise their holiday home is a place of mystery. And how are all the unusual events related to the ancient island legend of mermaids?', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '272', 2, '644050tokinokanata.jpg', '2010-06-30 08:32:59', 62, '2011-02-23 20:32:38', 62, 1),
(701, 0, 'Good Things Happen', 56, 1, 0, 0, '', 285, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '|11|', '', 'A little mouse boy has an argument with his friend and kicks an acorn, setting off a chain of events that brings him an unexpected friend – Old Grandpa Bear – and to a brand new circle of companionship. Three charming stories of friendship and community, delightfully illustrated, that will resonate with adults just as much as children.', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '79', 1, '313590iikotoga_arimashita.jpg', '2010-06-30 08:37:19', 62, '2010-12-08 22:46:23', 62, 1),
(702, 0, 'The Tiny King', 113, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|2|10|25|', '', 'The Tiny King lives in his enormous castle with his enormous army. But in bed at night he is so lonely he cannot sleep. Then the Tiny King meets a Big Princess – and his life changes forever. A heart-warming tale of happiness, illustrated in a bold collage style. This author/illustrator is one to watch.', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '331830chisana_osama.jpg', '2010-06-30 08:39:00', 62, '2011-08-17 19:43:48', 62, 1),
(703, 0, 'My House is My Home', 293, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '', '', '“My house is amazing. It’s a snail, after all! If I get into bother, it comes to collect me, and inside it’s pretty cool too”. The little boy at the heart of this tale is rightly proud of his unusual house, and the bold illustrations, full of movement, create a wonderful dynamism that will spark any young reader’s imagination.', '', '', '', '', '2010-05-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '331820-My_House_is_My_Home.jpg', '2010-09-01 17:59:53', 62, '2010-09-01 18:03:07', 62, 1),
(704, 0, 'A Building for Everyone', 327, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'Some buildings are used by everyone, which is why they are a little bit special. This informative book explains the various design features of public buildings, such as disabled toilets and signs in Braille, thereby providing a gentle introduction to people with disabilities and their needs. A positive and instructive book that will encourage children to consider others. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-01 00:00:00', '25 x 19', '32', 1, '318150-A_Building_for_Every.jpg', '2010-09-01 19:54:52', 62, '2010-09-01 19:55:44', 62, 1),
(705, 0, 'Friends', 329, 1, 0, 0, '', 328, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '', '', 'Where can you find a lifelong dear friend? This book gives a hint by introducing an enchanting friendship between a gentle bear and a fun-loving mouse in a very expressive, poem-like style. The story, in five chapters, feels familiar and warm and sends a beautiful message to children about how joyful it is to find a thriving, lifelong friendship.', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '79', 1, '313610-friend.jpg', '2010-09-01 19:57:26', 62, '2010-09-15 21:17:06', 62, 1),
(706, 0, 'Come Right In, We’re Waiting for You: Seven Scary Stories', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 217, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'The Scary Story Club meets once a month, to frighten each other with terrible tales. This time, the theme is transport; tales of the hidden dangers and terrifying hauntings of trains, rickshaws, and roller coasters. Each teller has a unique style, and Saito’s nuanced, eerie prose will have you spooked for days. Third in the popular series.', '', '', '', '', '2010-07-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '174', 2, '540370-Seven_Scary_Stories.jpg', '2010-09-01 20:00:59', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(707, 0, 'Shigeko From Hiroshima, over the Sea', 330, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'A touching non-fiction account of the life of Shigeko Sasamoto, who moved to America to receive treatment after suffering radiation burns from the Hiroshima atomic bomb. Today, Shigeko lectures at American schools, talking about her experiences of war, and about the importance of peace. 65 years after that momentous period, this book prompts quiet and thoughtful reflection.', '', '', '', '', '2010-07-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '172', 7, '645040-Shigeko.jpg', '2010-09-01 20:03:08', 62, '2010-09-01 20:05:03', 62, 1),
(708, 0, 'Goma''s Clothing Store', 331, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '', '', 'Banepa, Nepal. A changing city, seen through the eyes of Goma, a young girl from the country who has moved to Banepa to get married, and the community members who gather in her store. An honest and warm account of the lives of the people of Banepa, told in striking images and sensitive prose.', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '208', 15, '0003390-Gomas_Clothing_Stor.jpg', '2010-09-01 20:06:51', 62, '2010-09-01 20:08:38', 62, 1),
(709, 0, 'What’s the Meaning of Your Life?', 332, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 13, '', '', 'The first children’s book from Nakajima, a highly respected contemporary philosopher who specialises in the study of time. A letter is delivered to Kurai, who is fifteen, depressed and lonely. It talks about the past, the future, and his own death, helping him to overcome the philosophical questions that puzzle and trouble many teenagers.', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '187', 2, '814310-Whats_the_Meaning_of.jpg', '2010-09-01 20:10:09', 62, '2010-09-01 20:11:26', 62, 1),
(710, 50, 'The Friends of Vegetable Village: Autumn', 170, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'Miss Sweet Potato isn’t just a perfectly purple beauty pageant queen – she’s also a great source of vitamin goodness. And Chilli Pepper – well, he might seem like he’s got a fiery temper, but he’ll give you a good appetite and better circulation too. The third instalment in the series introduces the nutrition-rich, warming, wonderful vegetables of autumn. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-09-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '39', 1, '436130-yasai_ura_autumn.jpg', '2010-09-28 09:06:36', 62, '2010-09-28 13:38:24', 62, 1),
(711, 0, 'Little Apple and her Fabulous Beetle Cards', 61, 1, 0, 0, '', 333, 0, 0, 0, 1, 6, '', '', 'After Little Apple helps four (somewhat familiar) Beetles speaking a mysterious language (“Won’t you please, please help me?”), they give her some magical Beetle Cards. Little Apple uses the cards to get out of scrapes with the Eagles and avoid being squished by a Rolling Stone. A delightfully nonsensical book with lots for grown-ups to smile at too.', '', '', '', '', '2010-09-01 00:00:00', '24 x 24', '32', 1, '331880-apple_beetlecard.jpg', '2010-09-28 09:09:44', 62, '2010-09-28 09:10:50', 62, 1),
(712, 0, 'The Counsellor has Disappeared!', 279, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'A beautiful book set in the Imperial Court of medieval Japan. One day, a Counsellor to the Emperor is spat on by a demon, turning him invisible! He can’t get anyone to notice him, no matter how hard he tries. It takes a careless spark from the Yin-Yang master to reveal just how close the Counsellor really is.', '', '', '', '', '2010-09-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '427220-shonagon.jpg', '2010-09-28 09:12:20', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(713, 0, 'Clean and Green: A Story of The Sun and Photocatalysts', 334, 1, 34, 17, 'with Taketoshi Murakami, Kazuya Nakata, Tsuyoshi Ochiai, Tomoo Nomura', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 11, '', '', 'The sun already warms the earth and provides light; it is our most important source of natural energy. Now, researchers are harnessing its power for photocatalysis, a new technology that with great future potential. Overseen by Satoshi Kato, a pioneer of educational picture books, this excellent resource explains the complex but exciting technology for young and inquisitive minds. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-01 00:00:00', '30 x 24', '36', 1, '437230-the_sun_and_light.jpg', '2010-09-28 09:16:11', 62, '2011-08-10 17:21:46', 62, 1),
(714, 48, 'Toilet', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '|10|', '', 'Hiroyuki Arai’s charming picture book series for very young children has seen massive success, and this latest addition is sure to follow suit. Learning to poo using the toilet is a big step for every child, and this fun flip book, with its soft colours and rhythmical, mimesis-rich text, will help make a daunting task a little less scary.', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '13 x 18', '19', 1, '201010-toilet.jpg', '2010-10-28 21:16:14', 62, '2011-02-23 20:40:54', 62, 1),
(715, 0, 'The Adventures of Numbers', 336, 1, 0, 0, '', 337, 0, 0, 0, 2, 6, '', '', 'Did you know that after dark, numbers come alive? The naughty numbers leap from the pages of books and run around the faces of clocks. These three stories make the magic of numbers come alive, too, and helps introduce children to the idea that number changes their names when used in different ways (one, first, primary). ', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '22 x 19', '78', 1, '201010-numbers.jpg', '2010-10-28 21:18:50', 62, '2010-10-28 21:22:49', 62, 1),
(716, 0, 'Dr. Santa’s Housing Laboratory', 338, 1, 0, 0, '', 339, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'There’s a very special laboratory in the woods. Especially for kids who’ve got problems they can’t talk to their parents and teachers about. Like Nobu and his bogeys. Or Michi and her too-small house. And the strange but super brainy Dr. Santa, who’s in charge, has some very special ways to make their problems go away! ', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '214', 2, '201010-dr_santa.jpg', '2010-10-28 21:25:21', 62, '2010-10-28 21:28:17', 62, 1),
(717, 0, 'It’s My Birthday Everyday', 340, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '', '', 'Little Ikko loves birthdays so much she wants one every day. And Mummy says yes! At first it’s fun, even though she has to learn to make her own cakes. But not everything’s wonderful about always being the birthday girl. With illustrations that are full of warmth, and some easy recipes for readers to make with Mummy and Daddy, too.', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '201010-birthday.jpg', '2010-10-28 21:30:01', 62, '2010-10-28 21:31:39', 62, 1),
(718, 0, 'Marvellous Magic!', 341, 1, 0, 0, '', 342, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Everybody loves to watch magic, but with this illustrated beginner’s guide, you can be well on your way to making it too! Discover how to amaze your family and friends using everyday objects from around the home! Bursting with great tips on everything from where to stand to what to wear, as well as how to present your act. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '23 x 18', '115', 2, '201010-magic.jpg', '2010-10-28 21:35:11', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(719, 0, '100 Animals on Parade', 123, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|2|15|10|', '', '100 bears in the Bear Band, 100 rabbits in the Rabbit Circus…there’s one hundred of each kind of animal, but where are they all heading? There’s so much fun to be had by children and adults alike in the latest colourful and charming book from Masayuki Sebe, from counting parading piggies to finding fruit and frogs and dragonflies!', '', '', '', '', '2010-11-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '24', 1, '201010-animal_parade.jpg', '2010-11-07 10:40:10', 62, '2011-08-03 13:38:10', 62, 1),
(720, 0, 'The Tea Party in the Woods', 343, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|10|', '', 'One wintry morning, Kikko heads to her granny’s house with a cake. On the way she comes across a house filled with the animals of the woods, all having a tea party together. Combining a simple yet delightful story with beautiful illustrations that make striking use of colour, this is a magical tale that will charm any generation. ', '', '', '', '', '2010-11-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '201010-tea.jpg', '2010-11-07 10:41:18', 62, '2011-02-23 20:37:09', 62, 1),
(721, 0, 'The Closing-Down Sale of Specter’s Pharmacy', 30, 1, 0, 0, '', 344, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'Miss Specter runs a pharmacy that’s losing business to the big drugstore nearby. When she decides to close, her cat ornament suddenly comes alive, and all sorts of strange customers start to call in. It’s not until later she discovers that her cat has misspelled her name in his advertising….An enjoyable read full of ghostly fun and games.', '', '', '', '', '2010-11-01 00:00:00', '22 x 16', '153', 2, '201010-pharmacy.jpg', '2010-12-08 22:08:34', 62, '2010-12-08 22:09:44', 62, 1),
(722, 50, 'The Friends of Vegetable Village: Winter', 170, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 9, '', '', 'In this final instalment of the Vegetable Village series, we meet the warm, vitamin-and mineral-rich, and comforting winter veggies, like cute cousins Broccoli and Cauliflower, or Miss Leek, who’s a terrible cry-baby. As always, background information on the origins, nutritional value and storage of each vegetable is presented in accessible language with humorous illustrations.', '', '', '', '', '2010-11-01 00:00:00', '19 x14', '39', 1, '201010-veg_village.jpg', '2010-12-08 22:16:58', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(723, 0, 'The Singing Insects of Field and Mountain', 345, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 9, '|10|', '', 'An exhaustive guide to Japan’s “singing” insects, principally those in the Orthoptera order which includes grasshoppers and crickets. Packed with information on the classification, appearance and habits of 97 insects, this book is also full of charming yet accurate illustrations that show each amazingly adapted insect in its natural habitat. A must-have volume for bug lovers, budding scientists, and educators.', '', '', '', '', '2010-10-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '188', 5, '971180-noyamano_nakumushi.jpg', '2011-01-18 17:51:06', 62, '2011-02-23 20:31:59', 62, 1),
(724, 0, 'Stairs to the Heavens', 26, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 9, '', '', 'Renowned photographer Imamori takes the reader on a journey through the sumptuous colours and textures of the rice terraces in Bali. Beautifully cut into the sides of hill after rolling hill, these terraces, reaching up to the stunning Balinese sky, sustain human and wildlife alike. With thoughtful commentary, this book is as educational as it is visually appealing.', '', '', '', '', '2010-08-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21', '40', 5, '331870-kamisamano_kaidan.jpg', '2011-01-18 17:52:47', 62, '2011-01-18 17:53:36', 62, 1),
(725, 0, 'Hairy Henry', 346, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 3, '|10|11|', '', 'Hairy Henry hates to cut his hair and now it’s a huge hairy mess. He stores his half-eaten snacks in his hair and lets the birds use it as a perch. One day, Hairy Henry slips and falls….inside his own cavernous curls, which are home to a colony of mice. But how will Henry fare inside his own hair?', '', '', '', '', '2011-01-01 00:00:00', '27 x 21', '32', 1, '201102-konmori.jpg', '2011-02-04 15:10:39', 62, '2011-08-17 19:44:09', 62, 1),
(726, 0, 'Wash-‘Em-Clean', 286, 1, 97, 4, '', 347, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '', '', 'A very dirty little boy suddenly finds his sheets and shirts and socks flying away from him. Then Wash-‘Em-Clean, King of the Sinks, appears to scold him, and summon an army of brushes and soaps to scrub him squeaky clean! This rhythmical and humorous poem by Russia’s pre-eminent children’s author has been charming readers for nearly 90 years.', '', '', '', '', '2011-01-01 00:00:00', '29 x 25', '28', 1, '201102-arauyo.jpg', '2011-02-04 15:14:27', 62, '2011-02-24 14:16:42', 62, 1),
(727, 52, 'Igel’s Logbook Volume 3 The Terracotta City of Queens and Monsters', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 257, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'In the latest unmissable instalment in this wonderfully imaginative SF series, Karl continues to explore the mysteries of the sea on board the Igel, a fantastical submarine. This time, their underwater travels take them to a fabulous underwater city of soaring terracotta towers. But the city is in turmoil as they face a thunderous waterfall and flightless dragons.', '', '', '', '', '2011-01-01 00:00:00', '20 x14', '278', 2, '201102_Igel.jpg', '2011-02-14 09:44:07', 62, '2011-02-14 09:50:00', 62, 1),
(728, 0, 'Little Violet’s Off To School', 29, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '|8|', '', 'At last, Little Violet is old enough to go to big school! She’s ready with her brand new school bag – in violet, of course – and uniform but can’t help thinking her little sister is going to cause come trouble. Share Little Violet’s brand new experiences as she grows up, surrounded by family and friends, in this charming sequel.', '', '', '', '', '2007-11-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '152', 3, '20110_violet_school.jpg', '2011-02-14 09:52:34', 62, '2011-02-24 15:45:23', 62, 1),
(729, 0, 'Little Violet’s Hot Summer', 29, 1, 0, 0, '', 129, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '|8|', '', 'As Little Violet gets older, she’s getting more philosophical. After all, the world is a mysterious place and there’s so much to think about. But how can she concentrate on thinking when she has to look after her little sister all the time! The reader is drawn into Little Violet’s world once again in this third book of the popular series. ', '', '', '', '', '2009-07-01 00:00:00', '21 x 15', '138', 3, '201102_Violet_summer.jpg', '2011-02-14 09:54:10', 62, '2011-02-24 15:45:14', 62, 1),
(730, 0, 'Captain Ship and Champion the Kangaroo', 33, 1, 0, 0, '', 219, 0, 0, 0, 2, 7, '', '', 'Captain Ship is so keen to oblige, he can’t say no, whatever he’s asked. So when Champion the boxing kangaroo gets on board, he ends up as sparring mate. Whatever will happen to poor Captain Ship! This is the fifth instalment in this charming series, written for children who are building up enough confidence to start independent reading.  ', '', '', '', '', '2011-02-01 00:00:00', '21 x 16', '72', 3, '201105_ship_captain.jpg', '2011-05-15 08:46:03', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
(731, 0, 'Unforgettable Waters The Mountains, Rivers and Seas of the Henoko and Oura Bays', 348, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 9, '', '', 'The Bays of Henoko and Oura, in the subtropical islands of Okinawa, are home to diverse and beautiful wildlife and natural scenery. This stunning book captures intimate shots of the creatures which inhabit the region, from the mountains to the sea, and the life-giving water upon which they all rely. A book to treasure for children and adults alike. ', '', '', '', '', '2011-03-01 00:00:00', '26 x 21cm', '48', 5, '201105_sea.jpg', '2011-05-15 08:48:34', 62, '2011-05-15 08:50:29', 62, 1),
(732, 0, 'One Million Doves', 154, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'A little girl learns a special secret from her mother, about a plot of land, far far away on the African plains. She tells her secret to a friend, and soon her secret is shared around the world. This beautiful, lyrical book will capture the imagination of children and parents alike with its dreams of far off lands, better places, and peace.  ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '19 x 14', '62', 2, '201105_pigeons.jpg', '2011-05-15 08:52:30', 62, '2011-05-15 08:52:48', 62, 1),
(733, 0, 'Alfred’s Clock Tower', 79, 1, 0, 0, '', 349, 0, 0, 0, 2, 11, '', '', 'Back in his home town, Klaus finds himself somehow drawn to the old clock tower in the town square. Late one night, the wings of the stone Pegasus begin to flap, and the magic of the clock tower begins to reveal itself. This captivating, fantastical novel from prolific children’s writer Hiroshi Saito deals with themes of friendship and time. ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '20 x 14', '154', 2, '201105_clock_tower.jpg', '2011-05-15 08:54:26', 62, '2011-05-15 08:56:05', 62, 1),
(734, 53, 'Choo Choo', 350, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'A little steam engine makes its way around the tracks, chug chug, choo choo! Now it’s heading for a tunnel – but what’s this? The tunnel is moving! This series of books is perfect for little boys (and girls) who love all things to do with transport. The charming illustrations perfectly capture the world of imagination where young children play. ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, '201105_chugchug.jpg', '2011-05-15 08:58:28', 62, '2011-05-15 09:02:43', 62, 1),
(735, 53, 'Chop Chop', 350, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Chop chop, wuppa wuppa. We’re taking off in the helicopter! Off to the top of the mountain, to see an egg laid by a bird. Oh no! It’s fallen off, onto a ledge that looks just like….my Daddy’s hand? This lovely series of transportation-based books, filled with rhythm and mimesis, shows just how Daddy can become an integral part of children’s play.  ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, '201105_patatan.jpg', '2011-05-15 09:01:18', 62, '2011-05-15 09:02:13', 62, 1),
(736, 53, 'Chug Chug', 13, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Chug chug, tug tug. Off we go to sea in a boat, for an adventure! A sea full of strangely-shaped rocks and islands and…is that a giant catfish? Using rhythmical text and illustrations filled with humour, this series paints a picture of how a child’s imagination can transform his or her world – and the people in it – into a magical landscape for adventure.', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '16 x 16', '24', 1, '201105_ponpon.jpg', '2011-05-15 09:04:25', 62, '2011-05-15 09:04:46', 62, 1),
(737, 0, 'A Terribly Terrible Day for Gentle the Goat', 101, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 4, '|8|', '', 'Gentle the Goat is busy eating grass to make milk for her newborn kids. She’s concentrating so she doesn’t notice the grasshopper and accidentally bites its leg. This sets off a chain of increasingly farcical events that make it a terribly terrible day for Gentle. But it’s all alright in the end. Tashima’s original, award-winning illustrations make this a real stand-out. ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '25 x 23', '32', 1, '201105_yagi.jpg', '2011-05-15 09:06:52', 62, '2011-05-19 14:24:29', 62, 1),
(738, 0, 'On an Island to the South', 351, 1, 0, 0, '', 352, 0, 0, 0, 1, 7, '', '', 'A boy recounts the summer he spent on an island to the south with his aunt. Filled with nature and new experiences, this unforgettable summer is rendered with spectacular colour and beauty by Masumi Hara, a renowned artist. The text and illustrations combine to fill the reader with the same wonder and appreciation that enchants the little boy.', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '26 x 22', '32', 1, '201105_island.jpg', '2011-05-15 09:09:48', 62, '2011-05-15 09:12:13', 62, 1),
(739, 49, 'Who’s On Board?', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, '', '', 'The latest in the sell-out series of baby books by this talented young author-illustrator. Simple yet rhythmical language is used with bold illustration to create a guessing game about “who’s on board?” with real page-turning momentum. The repetition will be popular with young children too. The perfect way to make reading fun for baby and parent.', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '201105_who_in_bus.jpg', '2011-05-17 10:31:02', 62, '2011-05-19 09:27:10', 62, 1),
(740, 49, 'What’s Inside?', 290, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, '', '', 'Best-selling author-illustrator Hiroyuki Arai takes familiar objects from around the home and encourages children to guess what’s inside. The language is deceptively simple as each page of the book helps young children to understand what things are made of. Perfect for reading aloud together. ', '', '', '', '', '2011-04-01 00:00:00', '18 x 13', '19', 1, '201105_whats_inside.jpg', '2011-05-17 10:34:06', 62, '2011-05-17 10:38:29', 62, 0),
(742, 0, 'The Mysterious Calendar', 30, 1, 0, 0, '', 353, 0, 0, 0, 2, 9, '', '', 'At the beginning of the year, the owner of a cleaning shop finds a calendar in an old blanket. During the succeeding months, a number of strange and unexpected customers appear in his shop. They include a sheep who wants to know how to wash a sweater, a bear with an enormous curtain and a hungry typhoon man. Later, he realizes that the calendar contains their pictures. ', '', '', '', '', '2000-06-01 00:00:00', '22×16', '118', 2, '201105_calendar.jpg', '2011-05-19 14:29:55', 62, '2011-05-19 14:31:20', 62, 1),
(743, 54, 'The Arrival of a Little Goat', 101, 1, 0, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, '|8|10|', '', 'A series of picture books which come from the actual experiences of Seizo Tahima, picture book artist and farmer. The stories, which trace Shizuka’s development from a kid to a mother, are told against the background of the artist’s family, all of whom are involved in the goat’s care. The vivid, powerful pictures convey the warmth and feeling which the artist views animals. ', '', '', '', '', '1981-05-01 00:00:00', '25×24', '24-32', 1, '201105_koyagi.jpg', '2011-05-19 14:36:06', 62, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1),
